{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 01:55:37", "language": "en", "author": "6645", "url": "http://laith.wordpress.com/?p=2598", "title": "Happy May Day", "blog": "6638", "post_id": "1681474", "tags": ["Broadway", "Camelot", "Lerner &amp; Loewe", "Lusty Month of May"], "blogname": "Laith&#039;s Ramblings", "date": "2012-05-01 20:55:37", "content": "Good evening all, this post is a bit on the late side but I've had this song stuck in my head off and on all day. So I thought I would post this and spread the \"fun\" some more. \"<em>The Lusty Month of May</em>\" from <a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"Lerner and Loewe\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lerner_and_Loewe\" rel=\"wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">Lerner &amp; Loewe</a>'s <a href=\"http://www.ibdb.com/show.php?id=2369\" target=\"_blank\"><em><strong>Camelot</strong></em></a>\r\n\r\n[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4L-4QuVHHRw]\r\n\r\nI'm something of a theater buff so that I get Broadway songs stuck in my head from time to time shouldn't be too much of a shock to those who know me. Anyway while I was digging up a good video of the song to link to I found that the <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0061439/\" target=\"_blank\">film version</a> came out in '67 making this the 45th anniversary.\r\n\r\nSo please enjoy the clip, the show is very good so if you get a chance to see a staging of it or rent the movie take the opportunity, you won't regret it.", "categories": ["Ramblings"], "likes": []}
