arrings. Presto! As you can see the dress speaks for itself!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>GET IT&gt;&gt;</strong></span><em><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">\u00a0<a href=\"http://bit.ly/IkgrMh\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Boatneck Asymmetric Jersey Drape Dress by Rami Kashou</span></a></span></em>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><strong><a href=\"http://bit.ly/IUs2p9\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Shop Rami Kashou for bebe.</span></a></strong></span>", "categories": ["Fashion", "Just One Thing", "Street Seen"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 23:05:03", "language": "en", "author": "18133244", "url": "http://blog.bebe.com/?p=3620", "title": "Bridal Spotlight: Meet Our First bebe Bride!", "blog": "39505", "post_id": "477924", "tags": ["a bride who wore bebe", "bebe", "bebe bridal gowns", "bebe for a wedding", "bebe wedding", "bebe wedding dresses", "bebe wedding gowns", "bridal", "picking the right wedding dress", "Rami Kashou", "rami kashou for bebe", "rami kashou wedding", "shopping for bridesmaids", "tips for brides"], "blogname": "Stylust - The Official bebe Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 16:05:03", "content": "<span style=\"color:#000000;\">We\u2019re thrilled to introduce to you Stacey Smith Vince, the first bride to dazzle in a Rami Kashou for bebe wedding gown! Stacey fell in love with Rami\u2019s <span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/IHoQw5\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Drape Top Lace Mermaid Wedding Dress</span></a></span> at our bebe bridal launch party on Rodeo Drive. Fast-forward just 10 days, and Stacey walked down the aisle in stunning style at a gorgeous Malibu wedding on Easter Day.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\">Stacey was kind enough to fit a quick Q&amp;A with us into her busy newlywed schedule. Read on to hear all about her bebe bridal experience!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\">Which <span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/JUtM01\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Rami Kashou for bebe</span></a></span> wedding dress is your fave?</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bebe.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stylust-bebe-bride.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-3631\" title=\"STYLUST-bebe-bride\" src=\"http://bebe.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stylust-bebe-bride.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"727\" height=\"486\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><em>Photography by <span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><a href=\"http://larossphotography.com\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Lauren Ross</span></a></span></em><em><strong>\r\n</strong> </em><em></em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STYLUST: What was your experience like shopping for your bridal gown at bebe Rodeo Drive?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STACEY:</strong> My experience was nothing short of spectacular! The women at the store were so supportive and cheerful. There was the bonus of Vito from the upstairs salon, who quickly came down and created a look for my hair that was fantastic. He did it all with a comb, some hairspray and a few bobby pins in about four minutes! He was so fun and creative! I ended up copying that same look for my wedding day.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STYLUST: What was it like meeting Rami?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STACEY:</strong> Meeting Rami made my experience unforgettable! He did not try to push anything on me. He was patient, excited and genuinely interested in what looked the best. He was not afraid to tell me the truth. He expressed that his goal was for the dress to make the bride shine, not the reverse. His designs were to work with the bride, not to hang on her. He truly is a dynamic, creative and talented man. We had FUN with it! I am more than honored to be the first bride to wear his bebe bridal design. Thanks, Rami! You are a rock star!</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bebe.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stylust-bebe-bride-stacey-smith.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-3632\" title=\"STYLUST-bebe-bride-Stacey-Smith\" src=\"http://bebe.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stylust-bebe-bride-stacey-smith.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"727\" height=\"1064\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><em>Photography by\u00a0<span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><a href=\"http://larossphotography.com\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Lauren Ross</span></a></span></em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STYLUST: Which Rami Kashou for bebe bridal gown did you choose, and what made you fall in love with it?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STACEY:</strong> I fell in love with the mermaid lace dress. It was simply elegant and sophisticated. I loved his brilliant use of the different materials. I loved the twisted chiffon near my face creating a softer look. It was complemented by an underlying satin and overlying lace for the rest of the dress, which gave it the sleek, sexy mermaid look. It was far more interesting than the usage of one material for this design. I am usually not a lace girl, but this really worked! I was pleasantly surprised. It was heavier than I had anticipated, but I loved that as it made the dress feel structured and substantial.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STYLUST: How did you feel about the fit and quality of your bridal gown?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STACEY:</strong> Without a doubt, I put it on and it felt like magic and top quality. I was so proud to wear it! There was no doubt that THIS WAS THE ONE!</span>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bebe.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stylust-stacey-smith.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-3633\" title=\"STYLUST-Stacey-Smith\" src=\"http://bebe.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stylust-stacey-smith.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"727\" height=\"486\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><em>Photography by\u00a0<span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><a href=\"http://larossphotography.com\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Lauren Ross</span></a></span></em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STYLUST: What type of wedding did you have, and how did your bridal gown fit the location? </strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STACEY: </strong>Ironically, this dress could fit any location. I thought it would be best for a church wedding, but we were married at our home in Malibu, just above the ocean. Thus, the mermaid dress worked perfectly in look and feel even for our outdoor Easter day wedding!<strong></strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STYLUST: Which bebe dress did your bridesmaid choose and why?</strong></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>STACEY:</strong> My sister-in-law chose the champagne ruffle dress for the bridesmaid dress. The minute I saw it, I thought it was perfect. The color was so rich, and I loved the sophisticated design. Structured, yet sassy\u2014it was the perfect fit! She looked drop-dead gorgeous in it. It was so flattering!</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><em>Stacey's wedding makeup by <span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\"><a href=\"http://www.kristinmartinmakeup.com\"><span style=\"color:#ff00ff;\">Kristin Martin</span></a></span>\u00a0(kristin@kristinmartinmakeup.com) and\u00a0</em><em>hair by Melissa Hoffman (melissa.jo.hoffman@gmail.com)</em></span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color:#000000;\">Watch Stacey and Rami at our Rodeo Drive store below!</span>\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_X5Sg6EAxgE&amp;w=727&amp;h=448]", "categories": ["Bridal Spotlight", "Fashion", "Q&amp;A"], "likes": []}
