f=\"http://www.salon.com/2012/04/29/u_s_foreign_policy_brought_to_you_by_exxonmobil/\" target=\"_blank\">U.S. foreign policy, brought to you by ExxonMobil</a> (salon.com)</li>\r\n\t<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.politico.com/news/stories/0412/75756.html\" target=\"_blank\">Fracking and the face of ExxonMobil</a> (politico.com)</li>\r\n\t<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://www.sustainablebusiness.com/index.cfm/go/news.display/id/23679\" target=\"_blank\">T. Boone Pickens Calls Koch Bros Biggest Deterrent to US Energy Policy</a> (sustainablebusiness.com)</li>\r\n\t<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li\"><a href=\"http://bell-book-candle.com/2012/04/27/exxonmobil/\" target=\"_blank\">ExxonMobil</a> (bell-book-candle.com)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<strong>Postscript:</strong>\r\n\r\nIn the heartland they still believe in square roots. Or do they?\r\n\r\n<div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align:left;\">\r\n<div style=\"margin:0 auto 10px;text-align:center;\">\r\n<a href=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-uc001R21C30/T6U3ap6OSjI/AAAAAAAAQdc/8bv4MBgSL5g/s1600/heartland-meme-polpot2.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-uc001R21C30/T6U3ap6OSjI/AAAAAAAAQdc/8bv4MBgSL5g/s400/heartland-meme-polpot2.jpg\" /></a>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;text-align:CENTER;\">\r\n<a href=\"http://picasa.google.com/blogger/\" target=\"ext\"><img align=\"middle\" alt=\"Posted by Picasa\" border=\"0\" src=\"http://photos1.blogger.com/pbp.gif\" style=\"-moz-background-clip:initial;-moz-background-origin:initial;background:transparent none repeat scroll 0 50%;border:0 none;padding:0;\" /></a></div>\r\n</div>", "categories": ["Global Warming Politics"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 16:55:44", "language": "en", "author": "50667", "url": "http://wmmbb.wordpress.com/?p=16756", "title": "FLOODING IN NEPAL", "blog": "51539", "post_id": "309488", "tags": [], "blogname": "DUCKPOND", "date": "2012-05-07 03:55:44", "content": "The floods that occurred in Western Nepal have described as the worst flooding in living memory.\r\n<!--more-->\r\n<em><a href=\"http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/13-killed-40-missing-in-Nepal-floods/articleshow/13016990.cms\">The Times of India</a></em> reports:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Thirteen people were killed as raging flood waters from the swollen Seti river swept away houses and farms near the tourist resort of Pokhara on Saturday. Around 40 people are still missing in the floods triggered by a glacial lake burst in north western Nepal, even as the swollen river smashed into huts and buildings. \r\n\r\nThe calamity occurred in the remote Kaski district, 200-km away from the capital, Kathmandu. \r\n\r\nA number of shacks in Kharapani village were washed away in the deluge. Three foreign trekkers are among those dead. \"Among the dead is Ukranian while three Russians are missing,\" said superintendent of police Shailesh </blockquote>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/south-asia/5-killed-in-avalanche/triggered-flooding-in-Nepal/articleshow/13008559.cms\">An earlier report, like the BBC,</a> had <a href=\"http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17973014\">attributed the flood to an avalanche</a>.\r\n\r\nThis video attributes the cause to a glacier lake outburst and observes climate change is happening:\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8ScHkS_cqk4&amp;w=560&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nThis type of flooding, <a href=\"http://weadapt.org/knowledge-base/using-climate-information/nepal-climate-projections\">if correctly attributed</a> does seem likely to related to climate change. According to the <a href=\"http://books.icimod.org/index.php/search/publication/750\">abstract from a relevant online publication</a>:\r\n\r\n<blockquote>Glacier thinning and retreat in the Himalayas has resulted in the formation of new glacial lakes and the enlargement of existing lakes due to the accumulation of meltwater behind loosely consolidated end moraine dams. Such lakes are inherently unstable and can be subject to catastrophic drainage (glacial lake outburst flood or GLOF), which is a potential source of danger to people and property in the valleys below them.</blockquote>\r\n\r\nIn my mind I was linking the La Nina effect that explains the wet summer we had with something similar with the monsoonal rains arising from the Indian Ocean resulting in heavier rain over the Himalayas which combined with the effects of melting glaciers combining to create the floods. ", "categories": ["Natural Environment"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 17:57:13", "language": "en", "author": "51684", "url": "http://futrzak.wordpress.com/?p=4184", "title": "Umacnianie pokoju i wolno\u015bci obywatelskich", "blog": "52556", "post_id": "1074181", "tags": ["absurdy", "polityka", "USA"], "blogname": "notatki na mankietach", "date": "2012-05-01 09:57:13", "content": "A tymczasem za Wielk\u0105 Wod\u0105 rz\u0105d zabezpiecza sobie ty\u0142y. W zeszlym tygodniu kongres uchwalil ustawe, w mysl ktorej IRS (urzad podatkowy) bedzie mogl zatrzymac paszport obywatelowi, co do ktorego istnieje podejrzenie, ze zalega z zaplata podatkow. Ustawa czeka na podpis prezydenta.\r\n\r\nPytanie za sto punktow: Co zrobi laureat pokojowej nagrody Nobla z t\u0105\u017ce ustaw\u0105?\r\n\r\nRozstrzygni\u0119cie konkursu ju\u017c wkr\u00f3tce....\r\n\r\nZwyciezcy moga liczyc na majowe przetrzepanie jajek na bramce przez fachowcow z TSA, tudziez wdychanie swie\u017cego aromatycznego pieprzu przy probie oporu w czasie znajdowania sie w niewlasciwym miejscu i o niewlasciwej porze....", "categories": ["absurdy", "polityka"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 23:32:45", "language": "en", "author": "51684", "url": "http://futrzak.wordpress.com/?p=4242", "title": "Calkiem niez\u0142y pomys\u0142 na biznes", "blog": "52556", "post_id": "1134350", "tags": ["biznes", "Polska", "praca"], "blogname": "notatki na mankietach", "date": "2012-05-02 15:32:45", "content": "Tworzymy bloga o modzie, umieszczamy w nim zupelnie bezp\u0142ciowe i nieciekawe teksty napisane przez politycznie poprawnych marketdroid\u00f3w. Calosc okraszamy profesjonalnie (no, w miare, zeby nie wyszlo, ze to sciema :) zrobionymi zdjeciami z sympatyczna modelk\u0105 o wygl\u0105dzie dziewczyny z s\u0105siedztwa. Zaprezentowane \"stylizacje\" r\u00f3wnie\u017c powinny nie wykracza\u0107 poza ten poziom.\r\n\r\nPracowicie \"pozycjonujemy\" blog oraz zapewniamy mu reklame. Od pewnej ilosci wej\u015b\u0107 uderzamy do biznesow zwiazanych z moda, sprzedajacych ubrania, buty, kosmetyki etc. ale tez do wlascicieli modnych i drogich restauracji, kawiarni etc.\r\n\r\nW miare jak rosnie popularnosc bloga, rosna tez pieniazki z reklam.\r\n\r\nMo\u017cna? Mo\u017cna. Wystarczy tylko miec s\u0142awne nazwisko np. Kasia Tusk...", "categories": ["Polska", "praca"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 23:40:33", "language": "en", "author": "51684", "url": "http://futrzak.wordpress.com/?p=4244", "title": "Jak zorganizowa\u0107 skuteczny strajk", "blog": "52556", "post_id": "1850653", "tags": ["argentyna", "polityka", "strajk", "zwiazki zawodowe"], "blogname": "notatki na mankietach", "date": "2012-05-04 15:40:33", "content": "Celem strajku powinno byc zagrozenie finansow firmy/wlasciciela/polityka, przeciwko ktoremu wymierzony jest strajk. To MUSI byc konkret, inaczej nic sie nie da osiagnac. Rownocze\u015bnie strajk nie moze byc ucia\u017cliwy dla os\u00f3b postronnych - inaczej masy obr\u00f3c\u0105 si\u0119 przeciwko nam. Dodatkowo, nale\u017cy mie\u0107 nie wi\u0119cej ni\u017c jeden-dwa postulaty do spelnienia. Najlepiej - jeden.\r\n\r\nPrzyklad: strajk pracownikow metra w Buenos Aires. Postulat: domaganie sie podwyzki o 28% od prywatnej firmy metrovia posiadaj\u0105cej koncesj\u0119 na obs\u0142ug\u0119 metra. Pow\u00f3d: podwy\u017cka cen jednostkowego biletu o 127% w styczniu.\r\nSpos\u00f3b wykonania: przez kilka dni metro jezdzi jak zwykle, tyle ze bramki wej\u015bciowe sa otwarte dla wszystkich tj. mozna jechac bez biletu. Dopiero je\u015bli to nie pomaga, zatrzymywane sa wszystkie poci\u0105gi...", "categories": ["argentyna", "polityka"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 02:25:46", "language": "en", "author": "51684", "url": "http://futrzak.wordpress.com/?p=4249", "title": "Podr\u00f3\u017c z Buenos Aires do Bahia Blanca", "blog": "52556", "post_id": "216453", "tags": ["absurdy", "argentyna", "koleje", "polityka"], "blogname": "notatki na mankietach", "date": "2012-05-04 18:25:46", "content": "mo\u017cna pokona\u0107 poci\u0105giem. Gdy popatrzymy na mapie, nie wyglada to na nic wielkiego - ot 700 kilometrow.\r\nWell. Pociag jedzie 16 godzin w takich warunkach:\r\n\r\n[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4rNTqXfYPGI]\r\n\r\nA myslalam, ze trudno znalezc koleje w gorszym stanie niz w Polsce. Okazuje sie, ze mozna. I ze jest cos gorszego, niz calkowicie panstwowe koleje. W wypadku Argentyny panstwo jest wlascicielem torow i infrastruktury ORAZ wagonow i lokomotyw. Za to udzielilo koncesji prywatnym firmom, ktore organizuja przejazdy i maja prawo ustalac sobie cennik i calosc zyskow brac sobie. Firmy zatrudniaja maszynistow i innych pracownikow, ale szkola je juz zwiazki zawodowe.\r\n\r\nEfekt: NIC nie dziala, a wszyscy maja pretensje do wszystkich. Firma z koncesja ma pretensje do zwiazkow zawodowych, ze nie ma wystarczajacej liczby kolejarzy oraz do panstwa, ze nie remontuje infrastruktury. Panstwo ma pretensje do firmy, ze nie utrzymuje w przyzwoitym stanie uzytkowanego taboru. Zwiazkowcy maja pretensje do firmy o to, ze wyprowadzaja kase panstwowa i nie utrzymuja nalezytych stndardow bezpieczenstwa oraz do panstwa, ze pozwala na taki chory stan.\r\n\r\nA na koniec najwiekszy smaczek. Kto jest odpowiedzialny za taki stan rzeczy i dlaczego nic sie nie zmienia?\r\nOdpowiedzialnym jest liberalny rz\u0105d Menema, ktory na zasadzie jak wy\u017cej dokona\u0142 \"prywatyzacji\" kolei. Nie zmienia sie nic, poniewaz umowy zostaly podpisane na 30 lat...(chociaz ostatnio rozwi\u0105zano kilka koncesji ze wzgledu na skandaliczne zaniedbania firm).\r\nGwoli usprawiedliwienia trzeba dodac, ze koleje JUZ byly w zlym stanie w momencie ich \"prywatyzacji\" a w koncesjach na eksploatacje zawarte byly warunki wymagajace remontu, napraw etc. \r\n\r\nPrawdziwy w\u0119ze\u0142 gordyjski. Kazda ze stron zachowuje sie w pelni racjonalnie, niestety system jest tak ustawiony, ze nie ma prawa dzialac. Znacjonalizowac wszystko? Niby mozna, ale biorac pod uwage poziom wrzasku i histerii \"na wolnych rynkach\" po wywlaszczeniu YPF-u, bylby to gwozdz do trumny rzadu Kirchnerowej. Sprywatyzowac dokladnie wszystko? To skonczy sie jak zwykle, czyli przyjda zachodnie koncerny, wykupia prywatne firmy, wyeksploatuja do cna to co jest, poczem rozbiora tory i sprzedadza jako zlom. Czemu? Bo gdyby kolej w Argentynie dzialala skutecznie i wydajnie, to produkcja rolna tego kraju bylaby ogromna konkurencja dla USA i EU.\r\nI kolko sie zamyka...", "categories": ["absurdy", "argentyna", "polityka"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 17:36:14", "language": "en", "author": "51684", "url": "http://futrzak.wordpress.com/?p=4246", "title": "Jak zaprojektowa\u0107 mieszkanie dla te\u015bciowej", "blog": "52556", "post_id": "348822", "tags": ["absurdy", "humor", "obyczajowe", "projektowanie wn\u0119trz"], "blogname": "notatki na mankietach", "date": "2012-05-06 09:36:14", "content": "Zaczynamy od antresolki. Antresolka rewelacyjna rzecz, zwlaszcza jesli ma sie mieszkanie wysokie, a niedostatek miejsca. \u0141o\u017ce wygl\u0105da nader <a href=\"http://www.wysokieobcasy.pl/wysokie-obcasy/51,53581,11617468.html?i=0\" title=\"antresolka\" target=\"_blank\">zachecaj\u0105co.</a>\r\n\r\nWejscie na antresolk\u0119 te\u017c wygl\u0105da zach\u0119caj\u0105co, zwlaszcza dla synowej i zi\u0119cia, ktorzy jako ludzie wysportowani, nie b\u0119da mieli problemu z potr\u00f3jnym tulupem podczas <a href=\"http://www.wysokieobcasy.pl/wysokie-obcasy/51,53581,11617468.html?i=1\" title=\"porecz\" target=\"_blank\">schodzenia.</a>\r\nZa to istnieje szansa, ze tesciowa umieszczona czule w najprzytulniejszym pokoju w domu podczas schodzenia w nocy na siusiu nie da rady wykonac tulupa i po prostu albo zjedzie na plecach, albo je sobie z\u0142amie, gdy opsnie si\u0119 jej noga na sliskim schodku, a r\u0119ka nie trafi na nieistniej\u0105c\u0105 por\u0119cz.\r\n\r\nPrzejdzmy do salonu. Na wszelki wypadek, na glownym ci\u0105gu komunikacyjnym improwizujemy wielofunkcyjne siedziska w postaci pi\u0142ek <a href=\"http://www.wysokieobcasy.pl/wysokie-obcasy/51,53581,11617468.html?i=2\" target=\"_blank\">lekarskich</a>\r\nSa one wyjatkowo wygodne w pozniejszych tlumaczeniach - wystarczy je wsadzic do szafy a potem rzucic niedbale, ze tesciowa juz tak ma - potyka sie i przewraca na prostej drodze...\r\n\r\nCzas na lazienk\u0119. Panuje tu modny funkcjonalizm w pol\u0105czeniu z modernizmem. Podloga pokryta zywica zapewnia wystarczajaca powierzchni\u0119 poslizgow\u0105, brak mocowania prysznica pozwala na codzienne umycie wisz\u0105cego nad wanna obrazu. Stylowy mebel pod umywalke dostarczy ci\u0105g\u0142ej tworczej pracy w postaci wycierania, szlifowania i lakierowania tu\u017c po <a href=\"http://www.wysokieobcasy.pl/wysokie-obcasy/51,53581,11617468.html?i=3\" target=\"_blank\">rozmieknieciu.</a>\r\n\r\nWreszcie kuchnia. Mily dla oka i nowoczesny projekt zapewnia codzienne wyzwania pod tytu\u0142em jak zmie\u015bci\u0107 wszystkie garnki i utensylia w ograniczonej ilosci szafek, oraz gdzie znalezc wi\u0119kszy kawa\u0142ek blatu niezb\u0119dny do przygotowania <a href=\"http://www.wysokieobcasy.pl/wysokie-obcasy/51,53581,11617468.html?i=5\" target=\"_blank\">obiadu.</a>\r\nUmocowanie plyty grzejnej zaraz nad glowami siedz\u0105cych na kanapie gosci zostawia nam szerokie pole manewru w wypadku, gdybysmy chcieli sie ich pozbyc. Wystarczy popchn\u0105\u0107 niechacy gor\u0105cy garnek b\u0105dz patelnie w stron\u0119 salonu...A potem wszystko wynagrodzi nam pi\u0119kny widok przez okno na panoram\u0119 Warszawy podczas mycia naczy\u0144, slad\u00f3w krwi i przypalonych garnk\u00f3w :)", "categories": ["absurdy", "obyczajowe", "rozrywka"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 05:48:44", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6200", "title": "The Church of Jesus Christ; A Commitment to One Another", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "1757014", "tags": ["Church", "Church of Jesus Christ", "Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-04-30 00:48:44", "content": "\u201c<strong>And you are to love those who are aliens, for you yourselves were aliens in Egypt.</strong> Fear the Lord your God and serve him. Hold fast to him and take your oaths in his name. He is your praise; he is your God, who performed for you those great and awesome wonders you saw with your own eyes.\u201d (<span style=\"color:#000080;\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=Deuteronomy+10%3A19-21\" target=\"_blank\">Deuteronomy 10:19-21</a></span></span> )\r\n\r\nThere is someone who works in the same building that our offices are in that has a Canadian flag bumper sticker on his car. I had opportunity to ask him if he was indeed Canadian. He blithely said, \u201cNo, I was up in Vancouver and say it. It looked real red and since my car was red, I thought it would look good on it.\u201d I does.\r\n\r\nBut that is not the point, or at least not the point that I was trying to make when I said, \u201cThe reason I am asking is because I AM Canadian.\u201d I don't think he got the point.\r\n\r\nWe all look for was to orient ourselves to where we are, especially when we are away from home or outside of our comfort zone. When we find something familiar that reminds us of home or makes us feel not so lost, we cling to that with gratitude and it helps us cope with what is presented to us. Days when I feel tired and weary, and wonder if I am making a difference, it helped to see that reminder of where I started my life journey. And to my happy surprise, the fact that the owner of that car and by default bumper sticker is NOT Canadian does not diminish my feelings when I see the Canadian flag proudly \u201cwaving\u201d on his car's bumper.\r\n\r\nIt would be very easy, gentle reader, to stop at this point. But there is something troublesome to me here also. I find these verses from Deuteronomy interesting in light of what the Israelites did to those who were aliens and different from them. How is it that the same God who told them to love the aliens also told them to destroy everything as they took Canaan and Jericho? When Joseph's family first came to Egypt, they were made welcome. Of course it helped that Joseph was close to Pharaoh. Certainly things changed for the Israelites and that is why they eventually fled. But is that enough cause to put the alien \u201cto the sword\u201d? It is strange and troubling, gentle reader.\r\n\r\nThese verses are cited in support of church of Jesus Christ. The <em>Confession</em> says, \u201cCommitment to one another is shown in loving one another as God loves, in sharing material and spiritual resources, in exercising mutual care and discipline, <strong>and in showing hospitality to all</strong>.\u201c [Emphasis mine.] Who decides who the \u201call\u201d is? Think and answer carefully in light of verse 19. All of us at one time or another have been where we have felt \u201calien\u201d. How would we want the \u201cnatives\u201d to respond to us. And all of us at one time or another have encountered someone who is \u201calien.\u201d How would Christ have us respond to that person? Do we give them a friendly sign? Show them that we are not so different? Help them feel more at home?\r\n\r\nMay you gentle reader make a commitment to everyone you meet that you will love the \u201calien\u201d. And when you are the alien, gentle reader, may you be greeted with love and acceptance. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 05:30:18", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6203", "title": "The Church In Mission: Living the Commitment", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "1512929", "tags": ["Church in Mission", "Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites", "Missiology", "Mission", "Missional"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-05-01 00:30:18", "content": "\u201cThen Peter began to speak: \"I now realize how true it is that God does not show favoritism but accepts men [and women] from every nation who fear him and do what is right. You know the message God sent to the people of Israel, telling the good news of peace through Jesus Christ, who is Lord of all.\u201d (<a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=Acts+10%3A+34%2D36\" target=\"_blank\">Acts 10: 34-36</a> )\r\n\r\nYesterday we talked about the commitment to love the \u201calien\u201d. Today the same sort of message comes from Peter in the New Testament, on the occasions of Peter coming to Cornelius' house who was a Roman officer. Cornelius and his household become Christians as a result of Peter's visit. And Peter become much more welcoming of non-Jews accepting the Christian faith.\r\n\r\nI had an interesting encounter the other day. Let me back up however, about a week ago; I had found a \u201cBook of Mormon\u201d in our recycling area of the apartment complex. It had obviously been someone's because their name was on the front flyleaf. And the name was prefixed by the word \u201cElder\u201d which is the prefix name that Mormons who travel around evangelizing use. I do not know how it came to be in the recycling area. Assuming that since it had a name in it, it had gotten \u201clost.\u201d It was raining, and it just did not seem right to leave it there. So I brought into the house, not sure what I would do with it. Well, back to my story.\r\n\r\nI was just leaving to go somewhere when two Mormon Elders came walking up the sidewalk. I did not want to engage in conversation because I needed to get somewhere. But I thought it would be the perfect opportunity to return the bible. So I explained that I had found it and said, \u201c I know if my bible had gotten lost or misplaced I would not want it just trashed or left to sit, so I thought the owner of the bible might feel the same way.\u201d They were surprised and taken aback that someone would view their scripture in this way. I guess they do not get a lot of positive affirmation. When I identified myself as Mennonite, they asked how I viewed the Mormons from a Mennonite perspective. I said that there might be some theological differences, but basically we both ascribe to the same tenets of faith.\r\n\r\nThe <em>Confession</em> says, \u201cThe church is called to witness to the reign of Christ by embodying Jesus' way in its own life and patterning itself after the reign of God.\u201d We may encounter people whose faith is not very close to our own, or whose faith is radically different from ours. Faith beliefs, even within the confines of Christianity, can vary widely. But if we spring from the same message of God that Christ brought to humanity, then we should honor our fellow believers. Even if it seems to us that their beliefs seem a far distance from ours. If Peter accepted non-Jews, it seems like a small step to accept fellow Christians.\r\n\r\nMay you gentle reader find fellow believers where ever you go, and may there always be peace and shalom between all of you. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 05:16:00", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6206", "title": "Baptism: Getting out from under the fine print", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "655794", "tags": ["baptism", "Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites", "Salvation"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-05-02 00:16:00", "content": "\u201cHaving been buried with him in baptism and raised with him through your faith in the power of God, who raised him from the dead \u2026 God made you alive with Christ. He forgave us all our sins, <strong>having canceled the written code, with its regulations, that was against us and that stood opposed to us</strong>; he took it away, nailing it to the cross.\u201d (<a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=Colossians+2%3A+12%3B+13b%2D14\" target=\"_blank\">Colossians 2: 12; 13b-14</a> ) [Emphasis mine]\r\n\r\nSometime back I wrote a posting that talked about sin (or was it about salvation) and my realization at a young age that when it came to sin I was not a \u201cmajor\u201d sinner. That, in fact, if I was a sinner it was minor sins and the result of not being perfect. Actually, what my realization, at the tender age of 9, was that I was not such a \u201cbad\u201d person.\r\n\r\nWell a few nights ago I got to thinking about what it is NOW that might tag me as a sinner. I do not think I have gotten any worse as a person. But I had to admit I am not perfect as God is perfect. And what I conclude again was that whatever sins I may commit are the sins of human failing and weakness. And being human it is hard to make the leap to perfection that is of God. And that, gentle reader, is the fine print. We may think we are good and wonderful, not a mark on us; but when you get close and compare our selves and souls to the ultra-white perfection of God, that is when you see the smudges. I am not going to outline or reveal where my smudges are, and I am not asking you to reveal yours. But that \u201ctiny\u201d less then perfection is what the \u201cfine print\u201d points a finger at and says \u201cAh-ha!!!\u201d\r\n\r\nChrist took those rules and regulations that point out and condemn our \u201csmall\u201d sins, and applied it to the cross. I am not sure theologically what that means \u2013 nailing it to the cross. I would guess that the power of the cross \u2013 meaning Christ's sacrifice \u2013 took away the power of the rules and regulations to condemn us. And scripture says where there is not condemnation, there is life. (Romans 8:1)\r\n\r\nThe <em>Confession</em> does not speak about baptism exactly in this way. What I am speaking about is more a combination of salvation and baptism. But then the passage of Colossians is found in the <em>Commentary</em> section as opposed to the article proper, and even there does not contribute a great deal of theology or scriptural support. But you, gentle reader, and I know that we need Christ to do away with the condemnation that follows us for simply being human.\r\n\r\nMay you gentle reader accept Christ's actions on your behalf to cleanse you of human sin. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 05:10:38", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6209", "title": "The Lord's Supper: A gathering of like-minded believers", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "1185962", "tags": ["Communion", "Fellowship", "Lord's Supper", "Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-05-03 00:10:38", "content": "\u201cYou [faithful] are those who have stood by me in my trials. And I confer on you a kingdom, just as my Father conferred one on me, so that you may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom and sit on thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel.\u201d (<a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=Luke+22%3A+28%2D30\" target=\"_blank\">Luke 22: 28-30</a>)\r\n\r\nThere varies from denomination to denomination who may partake of Communion/the Lord's Supper and who may serve it. In the Mennonite tradition anyone in the congregation may serve Communion, but usually it is those who have other duties and calling for church and communal care. Anyone who professes faith in God and Christ may partake of Communion, but typically it is those who belong to the church body or to a similar church body. In the United Methodist tradition only ordained ministers can serve Communion, but anyone who walks in the church door can partake of it. The guidelines for Communion in the Roman Catholic church are pretty clear. And other denominations fall somewhere along the spectrum.\r\n\r\nThe salient point is that the Lord's Supper is served and/or partaken by those who know what it means and can explain to others the purpose and underlying theology. This passage from Luke has Jesus identifying the disciples and explaining why they have been included in Jesus' close circle of trusted friends. The <em>Confession</em> in the article on the Lord's Supper draws on Jesus bestowing on the disciples this special relationship. The <em>Confession</em> says, \u201cAll are invited to the Lord's table who have been baptized into the community of faith, are living at peace with God and with their brothers and sisters in the faith, and are willing to be accountable in their congregation.\u201d While we believers do not judge \u201cthe twelve tribes of Israel\u201d we are to be models for Christian living. I do not know if I would go as far as saying we all are worthy of thrones, I have known several people who live lives that qualify them for Christ's inner most circle. And if one rebuffs such a special designation, remember Jesus was talking about Peter who spoke his mind too often, Thomas who doubted what he could not see, James and John who coveted the seats to Jesus' right and left, and Matthew who came from a dishonorable profession. We might stack up better than we think!\r\n\r\nMay you gentle reader live a life that makes you worthy of all the blessings that Christ has to bestow. And may you celebrate the Lord's Supper with believers who love God and our Lord Christ as you do. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 05:07:41", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6211", "title": "Footwashing: Serving One Another", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "85674", "tags": ["Fellowship", "Foot Washing", "Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites", "Servanthood"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-05-04 00:07:41", "content": "\u201cThe greatest among you should be like the youngest, and the one who rules like the one who serves. For who is greater, the one who is at the table or the one who serves? Is it not the one who is at the table? But I am among you as one who serves.\u201d (<a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=Luke+22%3A25%2D27\" target=\"_blank\">Luke 22:25-27</a> )\r\n\r\nI am writing this in the evening of the today I had an experience that I do not usually have \u2013 I was the caregiver for one of our clients. Normally I do not do care but that means I am not in the office and available if situations arise. But there was a situation where the scheduled caregiver became ill and the replacement could not get there at the time needed, so I covered for about an hour and a half.\r\n\r\nIt is interesting now working as a caregiver, because I approach the situation thinking, \u201cAs a supervisor, what would I want my caregiver to do and be aware of?\u201d That makes me especially aware of each nuance and the attention to the smallest detail of care. It makes for good motivation to do the job well. In fact, I may use it in a training sometime.\r\n\r\nAnother aspect of this is the client is seeing how the care coordinator/supervisor of all the caregivers feels the job should be done. It is quite a responsibility maintaining the high standard that I want all of my caregivers to have. And to be quite honest, it is a responsibility that I find uncomfortable. If one of my caregivers does not do a superior job, well they just need to work better and harder next time. If I do not do a good job, well that sort of sandbags our reputation.\r\n\r\nBut it is also humbling, doing what I would normally have one of my employees do. And in that regard it reminds me of footwashing. I am personally being of service to my client. Me, the person who runs the whole shebang for all of this area. I am the one doing the dishes, cleaning the counters, and providing personal care.\r\n\r\nThe <em>Confession</em> says, \u201cThey thus acknowledge their frequent need of cleansing, renew their willingness to let go of pride and worldly power, and offer their lives in humble service and sacrificial love.\u201d I was not the one being cleansed, but I did do cleansing. And being the one who is sent, and at the beck-and-call of the client necessitates letting go of prestige and position. And each time I go to see a client, whether it be as the caregiver or as the care coordinator, what I want is to be of service to them and support them in their needs. Being who I am, I do it with and out of love.\r\n\r\nYou may not be called upon to wash someone's feet (although I have caregivers who do), but chances are that most days you will have the opportunity to be of service to someone else. May you do it out of love and love for servant-hood. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 05:11:02", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6213", "title": "Discipline in the Church: Knowing right from wrong, and saying so", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "1981582", "tags": ["Discipline in the Church", "Knowing right from wrong", "Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites", "Paul"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-05-05 00:11:02", "content": "\u201cEven though I am not physically present, I am with you in spirit. And I have already passed judgment on the one who did this, just as if I were present. \u201c (<a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=1+Corinthians+5%3A+3\" target=\"_blank\">1 Corinthians 5: 3</a>)\r\n\r\nI sort of wondered about this verse being cited in support of the <em>Confession</em>, but reading the verse in the fuller context convinced me that it is appropriately used; the confusion comes because verse 3 is the summing up of Paul's opinion on the erring young man and his stepmother, and their inappropriate relationship. With this context, it makes sense for Paul to say, \u201ceven if I am not there to see this, I know it is wrong.\u201d\r\n\r\nThat is basically what discipline in the church is about. Believers can know what is right and wrong, and should try to convince the offender to mend their ways, confess their sins, and stay in right relationship with the church and God. The problem comes in who judges the right and wrong, and what is the measuring stick for sin. That is where congregations, churches, conferences, and denominations can get into conflict.\r\n\r\nThe article on \u201cDiscipline in the Church\u201d does not, however make provision for judging a situation in absentia. In fact quite the opposite; the <em>Confession</em> says, \u201cDepending on the person's response, admonition may continue within a broader circle. This usually includes a pastor or congregational leader. If necessary, the matter may finally be brought to the congregation. A brother or sister who repents is to be forgiven and encouraged in making the needed change. If the erring member persists in sin without repentance and rejects even the admonition of the congregation, membership may be suspended. Suspension of membership is the recognition that persons have separated themselves from the body of Christ.\u201d\r\n\r\nThis seems to me a very \u201chands-on\u201d approach that involves not just one person who is \u201cspeaking up\u201d but the entire fellowship who is seeking to help and intervene for the \u201csinner.\u201d Please note, I am not outlining what the sin is, just the process as the <em>Confession</em> outlines. In my experience, there have not been any instances when someone has had their membership suspended. It is a very drastic step.\r\n\r\nYou and I, gentle reader, are not Paul. It is very unlikely we will ever be in the situation of having to bring a concern about a fellow believer before the fellowship. In my experience talking one to one, or having two or three fellow believers talk to the erring believer is sufficient. But we do have a Christian obligation to speak up when something we know or become aware of is harming a fellow believer or believers. I would encourage you to prayerfully proceed, seeking the guidance and support of others.\r\n\r\nMay you gentle reader heed and call on the Holy Spirit in these matters, and may the Spirit guide you through each step. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 06:18:47", "language": "en", "author": "812340", "url": "http://asimpledesire.wordpress.com/?p=6215", "title": "Ministry and Leadership: Sent Out", "blog": "53052", "post_id": "1899893", "tags": ["Mennonite Confession of Faith", "Mennonites", "Ministry &amp; Leadership", "Mission"], "blogname": "a simple desire", "date": "2012-05-06 01:18:47", "content": "\u201cAfter this the Lord appointed seventy-two others and sent them two by two ahead of him to every town and place where he was about to go. He told them, \"The harvest is plentiful, but the workers are few. Ask the Lord of the harvest, therefore, to send out workers into his harvest field.\u201d (<a href=\"http://www.biblegateway.com/passage/index.php?search=Luke+10%3A1%2D2\" target=\"_blank\">Luke 10:1-2</a>)\r\n\r\nThe workers still few. I do not have any statistics or studies to back this up. I have not looked at numbers of congregations anywhere, or numbers of ministers, or number of seminary students graduating. I have not looked at ministerial job postings, nor contacted any church or seminary. I have nothing to verify this. But I know it for a fact \u2013 the workers are still too few. How do I know this? The <em>Confession</em> says, \u201cSuch service is a participation in God's creative work of building up the body of Christ in love and of witnessing to God's righteousness in the world.\u201d There is never too much love and righteousness in the world. It is as simple as that.\r\n\r\nMay you gentle reader be sent out to bring in the harvest and may you go out in the love of God and Jesus Christ. Selah!", "categories": ["Commentary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 14:52:52", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1304", "title": "Balkenende is geen norm", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "1947889", "tags": ["Balkenende-norm", "Presentatoren", "Publieke Omroep", "Rutte", "Verhagen", "Wilders"], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-04-30 10:52:52", "content": "Presentatoren die veel meer verdienen dan de Balkenende-norm. Je kan je er aan storen en het kan hier en daar inderdaad wat minder. \r\n\r\nIkzelf erger me vooral aan mensen die de Balkenende-norm verdienen en uit hoofde van hun beroep ongestraft geld mogen weg schrapen van zwakkeren in onze maatschappij. Mark, Maxime en Geert, die na zeven weken nietsdoen in het Catshuis voor bijna vier miljard aan gemeenschapsgeld aan kostbare tijd hebben verspild.  \r\nEn wij mogen ons druk maken over een Balkenende-norm voor mensen die werken voor de publieke omroep. Dat is toch te triest voor woorden.\r\n\r\nHet wordt tijd dat mensen die tot op de Balkenende-norm zitten te verbieden eenvoudige mensen geld afhandig te maken die ze niet kunnen missen.", "categories": ["Dingen van de dag", "Maatschappij", "Politici", "Politiek", "TV"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 15:10:50", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1307", "title": "Een kabouter heeft het gedaan!", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "1091279", "tags": ["Kabouter"], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-04-30 11:10:50", "content": "Ik moest even schuilen voor een regenbui en koos voor een bushokje. Er stond een flinke waterplas in het hokje. Een verstopt afvoerputje was de boosdoener. Het putje maakte een borrelend geluid. Toen zag ik de putdeksel bewegen. Een rood puntmutsje kwam tevoorschijn. \r\n\"Jij weer?\" vroeg ik. \"Ja ik weer,\" antwoordde de kabouter. Toen trok hij de putdeksel het putje in. Deksel weg, verstopping weg. De waterplas verdween als een dief in de nacht. Ik vloekte, \"verdomd vergeten een foto te maken!\" \r\nEen bus stopte voor me. Terwijl de deur sissend opende zag de chauffeur hoe ik met mijn fototoestel een plaatje poogde te schieten van het putje zonder putdeksel. \r\n\"Een kabouter heeft het gedaan,\" flapte ik er uit, \"met een rode muts!\" De chauffeur schudde zijn hoofd, sissend ging de deur weer dicht.\r\nDe bus reed weg, ik droop af, te voet. Gelukkig was het gestopt met regenen.", "categories": ["Fictie"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 12:53:18", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1310", "title": "Hoe vang je een kabouter?", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "899430", "tags": ["Kabouter"], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 08:53:18", "content": "Die dag besloot ik het kreng te gaan vangen. Ik had nog geen idee hoe, maar een ding stond vast: zodra ik dat ding weer zie spring ik er bovenop, hoe dan ook. \r\nIk besloot de plek waar ik de kabouter voor het eerst zag uit te graven om te onderzoeken wat zich daar onder de grond afspeelde. \r\nGewapend met mollenvallen, een schop en mijn fototoestel wandelde ik naar de bosrand. Toen ik bij de bosrand was aangekomen merkte ik dat ik gevolgd werd. Ik keek om, en toen naar beneden: de kabouter! \r\nHet kreng verdween al in de grond, maar ik sprong boven op zijn rooie muts. Ik had het mormel bij zijn hoofd vast. Maar toch zakte het verder de grond in. Ik liet niet los en werd mee de grond ingetrokken. Toen vielen we samen in een ondergrondse gang. \"Jij weer,\" zei de kabouter. \"Ja ik weer,\" antwoordde ik terwijl ik de modder van me afklopte. \"En waarom ben ik nu even groot als jij?\"", "categories": ["Fictie"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 11:34:20", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1316", "title": "Opgesloten in kabouterland", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "1809470", "tags": [], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 07:34:20", "content": "\"Je bent in een andere wereld terecht gekomen,\" antwoordde de kabouter. \"Wil is de naam,\" en hij maakte een lange neus bij wijze van groet. Ik maakte een lange neus terug: \"Johan, aangenaam.\" \"Je moet even meekomen,\" zei Wil, \"je bent een vreemdeling hier en je zal het een en ander moeten uitleggen. Verder moeten we uitzoeken waarom je mij kon zien.\" \r\n\r\n\"Naam?\" vroeg een kabouter agent. \"Johan,\" antwoordde ik gedwee. Ik voelde me verloren als een verdwaald kind op schiphol. De agent gaf me een pakketje. \"U mag zich daar omkleden.\" \r\nWil had me meegenomen naar de autoriteiten. Ze hadden besloten me voorlopig op te sluiten. Nu ik me had omgekleed zag ik er ook uit als iets wat opgesloten moest worden. Ik droeg een witte romper met zwarte strepen en dito puntmuts. \r\nToen de deur achter me was dichtgegooid liet ik me doodmoe vallen op iets wat leek op een slaapgelegenheid: een baal stro en een juten deken.\r\nIk viel in een diepe, droomloze slaap.\r\nToen ik wakker werd kneep ik mezelf in mijn wangen. Hier lag ik dan, als vreemdeling opgesloten in een belachelijk zwart gestreept rompertje met dito puntmuts in kabouterland.", "categories": ["Fictie", "Kabouter"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 11:19:33", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1332", "title": "Vreemdeling in Kabouterland", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "1075600", "tags": [], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 07:19:33", "content": "De volgende ochtend hoorde ik gerammel aan de gevangenisdeur: het was Wil. Hij had immigratie zover gekregen dat ik met een speciaal pasje vrij mocht rondlopen in kabouterland. Maar dan wel samen met Wil. Gesignaleerd worden zonder Wil stond gelijk aan een enkeltje bajes.\r\nIk kreeg nieuwe kleding want ik mocht mijn eigen kleren niet meer dragen: mensenkleding dragen is strafbaar in kabouterland. Ik kreeg een kabouterpakje aangemeten met blauwe puntmuts. Blauwe puntmuts omdat ik een vreemdeling was. In ieder geval was ik van die idiote romper af. Nadat ik het pasje in ontvangst had genomen maakte ik een lange neus naar de autoriteiten: ik was weer vrij. \"Kunnen we ergens eten en drinken?\" vroeg ik Wil: \"Ik sterf van de honger en dorst.\"\r\n\r\nHij bracht me naar een restaurant genaamd 'De Laatste Molshoop'. Het was er gezellig druk en de bediening was vlot. Een serveerster maakte een lange neus en vroeg me of ik wormen of maden bliefde. Toen merkt ze mijn blauwe vreemdelingenmuts op en richtte zich verder tot Wil. \"Wat blieft hij?\" vroeg ze Wil. \"Doe hem maar een bakje gemalen worm en een glaasje water,\" zei Wil terwijl hij in mijn richting knikte, \"en verse maden voor mij, met een naaktslaksausje.\" \r\nIk voelde me een beetje misselijk worden, maar besloot me aan te passen zoals het een drager van een blauwe puntmuts betaamt.\r\n\"Gemalen wormen en maden?\" vroeg ik Wil nadat hij voor ons besteld had. \"Ik heb toch verse maden besteld?\" reageerde Wil verschrikt toen hij de walging in mijn gezicht opmerkte. Ik knikte instemmend. \"Gelukkig maar,\" zei Wil, \"ik dacht even dat ik vergeten was 'verse' te zeggen.\"\r\nEven later at ik van een gemalen wormen-gerecht. Gelukkig zat er een soort wortel-salade bij die erg lekker smaakte. Zo kon ik mooi om de gemalen wormen heen eten. Er zaten heerlijke zaadjes door de salade die me nog het meest deden denken aan geroosterde zonnebloempitten. \r\n\"Wat zijn dat voor zaadjes Wil?\" vroeg ik nieuwsgierig terwijl ik met smaak zo'n zaadje liet knisperen tussen mijn tanden. \"Dat zijn gedroogde pissebed eitjes,\" zei Wil terwijl hij een tegenstribbelende witte made doormidden beet.", "categories": ["Kabouter"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 11:05:54", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1368", "title": "Vreemdeling in Kabouterland 2", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "110160", "tags": [], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-04 07:05:54", "content": "\"Went wel,\" zei Wil met een bemoedigend schouderklopje nadat ik mijn maag had omgekeerd in het kabouter-toilet van De Laatste Molshoop. \r\n\"Ik ga je je nieuwe woonplek laten zien,\" zei Wil opgewekt, \"maar eerst ga ik je voorstellen aan onze koning, hij heeft al het een en ander over je gehoord.\" \r\n\r\nOnderweg naar de koning keek ik mijn ogen uit. Was het restaurant nog vlak om de hoek bij de gevangenis, nu maakte ik een echte wandeling door kabouterland. \r\nKabouters woonden in paddenstoel-woningen, sommigen vrijstaand, anderen in rijtjes-paddenstoelen of twee-onder-een-paddenstoel.\r\nIk zag hoe moeders verschrikt hun kinderen bij zich hielden, of naar binnen trokken zodra ze mijn blauwe muts zagen. De afwijzende blikken van kabouters stelden me niet echt op mijn gemak. Blijkbaar was ik als vreemdeling een soort 'persona non grata'. Toch waren er ook kabouters die me juist bemoedigend aankeken. Sommigen gaven me zelfs een lange neus.\r\nWil legde me uit dat de gemiddelde kabouter niet zoveel van vreemdelingen moest hebben. \"Vandaar die blauwe muts\" zei hij: \"Dan kunnen we zien of iemand een vreemdeling is.\"  \r\n\"Is het niet handiger voor me een andere muts te dragen zodat men niet kan zien dat ik een vreemdeling ben?\" vroeg ik belangstellend.\r\n\"Nee,\" zei Wil, \"als vreemdelingen geen blauwe muts zouden dragen kunnen we immers niet zien wie er vreemdeling is? Dat zou alleen maar onrust brengen. Er zijn wel kabouters die vinden dat vreemdelingen die geen crimineel zijn vrijer zouden moeten kunnen rondlopen, maar dat is een minderheid.\"\r\n\"Wat vind jij Wil, moeten vreemdelingen meer vrijheid krijgen?\" vroeg ik nieuwsgierig. Wil haalde zijn schouders op: \"Ik bemoei me daar niet mee.\"\r\nWil wees naar een grote, vrijstaande paddenstoel: \"kijk, daar woont koning Kabout nummer 10.\" \r\n", "categories": ["Fictie", "Kabouter"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 14:27:45", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1396", "title": "Vannacht Weerwolvenjacht nacht", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "519144", "tags": ["Volle Maan", "Weerwolven", "Zilver"], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-05 10:27:45", "content": "De actie 'Zilver voor volle maan' heeft een recordhoeveelheid zilver opgeleverd. \r\nZoals bekend krijgt Europa te maken met een extra heldere 'supermaan' in nacht van 5 op 6 mei. \r\nDe productie van zilveren kogels draait op volle toeren en duizenden vrijwilligers gaan vannacht onder de wapenen. \r\nPijlen met zilveren kop voor thuisgebruik zijn niet aan te slepen.\r\nDe Europese Unie verwacht vannacht een behoorlijke slachting aan te kunnen richten onder de weerwolven.\r\n\r\nZoals gewoonlijk kunt u voor iedere gedode weerwolf vijf harde Euro's vangen bij uw lokale zilverhandel\r\n\r\nHandel in illegaal zilver wordt zeer streng aangepakt. \r\nChina en India hebben wederom de markt vervuild met onbruikbaar namaakzilver. \r\nLet op het zilvermerk! \r\nJe bent bent een rund als met zilver stunt! \r\n", "categories": ["Fictie", "Natuur"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 17:45:06", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1398", "title": "Op audi\u00ebntie bij koning Kabout", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "751356", "tags": [], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-05 13:45:06", "content": "Voor een koning was dit een eenvoudig optrekje. Wil wees me de kamer waar de koning resideerde en klopte voorzichtig aan. Een gedempt \"ja!\" was het signaal dat we binnen mochten komen. De koning was druk doende in zijn stoffig kantoortje. Hij rommelde met kaarten en mappen en leek in gepeins verzonken. Verstrooid keek hij me aan. \"Ah menspersoon\" zei hij op een afwezige toon en hij gaf me een onafgemaakte lange neus. Ik maakte netjes een lange neus terug. \"Dit is 'Johan de menspersoon' koning Kabout\" zei Wil op plechtige toon, maakte zich achteruit lopend en buigend uit de voeten en sloot de deur achter zich. \r\nKoning Kabout wees me een stoel. \r\n\r\n\"Jij kan ons zien\" zei Kabout streng: \"en dat betekend dat veel van de basis-magie van kabouters bij jou niet werkt. Normaal gesproken kunnen mensen ons niet zien, behalve enkele uitzonderingen waarvan jij bent een bent. Kabouterland zoekt een persoon die verminderd gevoelig is voor onze magie. Jij bent zo'n persoon. Daarom heeft Wil heeft je in ons land gelokt. \r\nWelnu: Onze zuiderburen, de Alven, hebben een van de verboden boeken gestolen. De verboden boeken geven toegang tot magie die verboden is in onze wereld. De Alven zijn altijd tegen dit verbod geweest en hebben daarom het verboden boek gestolen. We vermoeden dat de Alven de magie van het derde boek willen gaan gebruiken om Kabouterland te veroveren. Voor zover we weten kunnen de Alven de Runen van de verboden boeken niet ontcijferen. Maar zeker weten doen onze spionnen dat niet. Wel is bekend dat de Alven alles zullen doen om het derde boek te kunnen lezen. \r\nAlven beheersen net als ons basis-magie. Jij bent daar verminderd gevoelig voor. Ik wil dat jij het derde verboden boek samen met Wil terug steelt. Wil zal je gids en begeleider zijn. En zet die rare blauwe muts af, die heb je niet meer nodig.\"\r\n\r\nEven later stond ik weer buiten, ik was nu de trotse bezitter van een onopvallende rode muts. \"Jij hebt me hierheen gelokt?\" vroeg ik hoofdschuddend aan Wil. Wil lachte: \"kom we gaan naar huis, morgen wacht ons een drukke dag!\"\r\n", "categories": ["Fictie", "Kabouter"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 14:35:25", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1404", "title": "Naar het land van de Alven", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "1485671", "tags": [], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-06 10:35:25", "content": "Wil maakte me de volgende ochtend al vroeg wakker en had een heerlijk ontbijtje klaar staan: vers geplukte kersen met gepofte hazelnoten, gecompleteerd met een geurige kannetje brandnetelthee. \r\nIk smulde het feestmaal hongerig naar binnen en was blij dat vegetarisme ook bestond in kabouterland. \r\nNa het ontbijt bereidde Wil me voor op de reis die we gingen ondernemen: \r\n\r\n\"Wat je ook doet, zet nooit je rode muts af. Mensen en kraaien kunnen ons dan zien.  \r\nHij gaf me een boog en een koker met pijlen. \r\n\"De pijlpunten zijn giftig voor eekhoorns, muizen en ratten. In kabouterland komen ze weinig voor, maar onderweg zullen we ze zeker tegenkomen. Een afgeschoten pijl zal altijd doel treffen, dus wees zeker van je zaak als je je pijl en boog gebruikt\" \r\nDaarna gaf Wil me een rugzak met proviand.\r\n\"Uit de rugzak kun je zoveel eten halen als je wilt. Het zal nooit leeg raken. Als je anderen eten geeft uit de rugzak zal het wel leeg raken en bovendien zwaarder worden. Wees dus wijs met uitdelen\" \r\nTenslotte gaf Wil me een mes. \r\n\"En scheer die rare snor af maar laat je baard staan. Dan lijk je meer op een van ons.\" \r\nWil proestte het uit: \"die mensensnor van je, geen gezicht!\r\n\r\nEven later stonden we in volle bepakking buiten, ik had mijn snor netjes afgeschoren en droeg nu, net als Wil, een prachtig kabouterbaard. \r\n\r\n\"Die kant op,\" zei Wil en daar gingen we, onder begeleiding van een waterig ochtendzonnetje, de groet van een grutto en een optrekkende mist naar de zuiderburen, het land van de Alven om het derde verboden boek te stelen en terug te brengen naar waar het hoort: kabouterland.", "categories": ["Fictie", "Kabouter"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 17:46:56", "language": "en", "author": "52214", "url": "http://defrysk.wordpress.com/?p=1412", "title": "Vreemdeling in kabouterland voor uw E-reader", "blog": "53087", "post_id": "1826821", "tags": ["E-reader"], "blogname": "Defrysk&#039;s Blog", "date": "2012-05-06 13:46:56", "content": "Speciaal voor de liefhebber maak ik bij wijze van proef een Epub van de eerste verschenen deeltjes van 'Vreemdeling in kabouterland' . \r\nMet programma's als <a href=\"http://calibre-ebook.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Calibre</a> kunt u de Epub converteren voor uw reader. \r\n<a href=\"https://doc-04-7o-docs.googleusercontent.com/docs/securesc/crpc4fbn5m92ub0usck344av62cjkbln/r1t55bsoqctmho4sjqmgq5f0cutvr00f/1336320000000/02814711770923142569/02814711770923142569/0B7QMB7LXQxN2Rk1DOGtqTmIyZk0?e=download\">Hier</a> zijn de eerste acht deeltjes.\r\n\r\nLaat me weten of het goed werkt en of het bevalt: Veel plezier ermee!", "categories": ["Fictie", "Kabouter"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 06:48:57", "language": "en", "author": "52373", "url": "http://solvt.wordpress.com/?page_id=14304", "title": "Winnie", "blog": "53246", "post_id": "929861", "tags": [], "blogname": "Solveigs AGILITY-side og blogg", "date": "2012-04-30 07:48:57", "content": "<span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong><img src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2006/01/strek-blaagroenn.jpg?w=618&amp;h=5\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"5\" />\r\n</strong></span><span style=\"color:#000000;\"><strong>EBRA'S K-LEANDRA LIMELIGHT\r\n</strong></span><strong>\u00abWINNIE\u00bb</strong><img src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2006/01/strek-blaagroenn.jpg?w=618&amp;h=5\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"5\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>Rase: </strong>Kooikerhund\r\n\r\n<strong>Alder: </strong>Winnie\u00a0 ble f\u00f8dt 9. mai 2004.\r\n\r\n<strong>Oppdretter: </strong>Ebras, Eva Brenna i Son.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mor:\u00a0 </strong>Taga's Elie (Kelly)\r\n\r\n<strong>Far</strong>:\u00a0 Int Nord Ch NW-96 SW-94 NordW-94-98 Taga's Leander LImelight\r\n\r\nWinnie var den valpen som alltid sov alle de gangene vi var og tittet p\u00e5 valpene, men oppdretteren mente vi burde ha Winnie, s\u00e5 slik ble det.\r\n\r\nWinnie er fortsatt flink til \u00e5 sove, men ogs\u00e5 flink til \u00e5 leke med seg selv. P\u00e5 sommerstid utend\u00f8rs kan hun rase rundt med en leke det ene \u00f8yeblikket, og noen minutter senere finner vi henne sovende et eller annet sted ute.\u00a0\r\n\r\nHun elsker \u00e5 sitte inntil oss \u00e5 kose, og hun bjeffer aldri annet enn n\u00e5r hun er redd for noe.\r\n\r\nHun har v\u00e6rt litt engstelig for mennesker, noe vi har jobbet bevisst med, og n\u00e5 tar det oftest ikke lang tid f\u00f8r de hun blir kjent med, neste gang blir m\u00f8tt av en smilende kooiker som logrer med hele seg, og hun logrer s\u00e5 intenst at logringen forflytter henne sideveis.\r\n\r\n<strong><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2006/01/strek-blaagroenn.jpg?w=618&amp;h=5\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"5\" />\r\n</strong><strong>UTSTILLING:\r\n</strong><img src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2006/01/strek-blaagroenn.jpg?w=618&amp;h=5\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"5\" />\r\n\r\n<strong>20 aug 2005:\u00a0\r\nNorsk Kooiker Klubb's Hovedutstilling, Rygge\r\n</strong>(ca 20 kooikere deltok):\r\n\r\nWinnie's f\u00f8rste og eneste utstilling:15 mnd gammel:\r\n\r\nBIR &amp; HP &amp; storcert &amp;\r\nBeste norsk-eide hund &amp;\u00a0\r\nBeste norsk-oppdrettede hund\r\n\r\n<em>Dommer: Anja Puumala, Finland</em><em> </em>\u00a0\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.solveigtr.com/start-trippes/dagbok-1-2005.htm#UTSTILLING\"><strong>Solveigs</strong></a><a href=\"http://www.solveigtr.com/start-trippes/dagbok-1-2005.htm#UTSTILLING\"><strong> referat i bloggen </strong></a>fra utstillingen:\r\n<a href=\"http://www.solveigtr.com/start-trippes/dagbok-1-2005.htm#UTSTILLING\">http://www.solveigtr.com/start-trippes/dagbok-1-2005.htm#UTSTILLING</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/ut1.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-14320\" title=\"ut1\" src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/ut1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"584\" height=\"423\" /></a>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong><a href=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/ut2.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-14319\" title=\"ut2\" src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/ut2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"564\" height=\"485\" /></a></strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Flere bilder fra utstillingen\u00a0 - trykk her:\u00a0 </strong><strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a href=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/utstilling-2005n.doc\">utstilling-2005N</a> </span></strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong></strong><strong><img src=\"http://solvt.files.wordpress.com/2006/01/strek-blaagroenn.jpg?w=618&amp;h=5\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"5\" />\r\n</strong><strong>AGILITY / TRICKS\r\n</strong><img src=\"http://so