{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 13:01:07", "language": "en", "author": "69017", "url": "http://first50.wordpress.com/?p=3275", "title": "Add New Post", "blog": "69924", "post_id": "521136", "tags": [], "blogname": "First 50 Words - Writing Prompts for Writing Practice", "date": "2012-04-30 06:01:07", "content": "He took an ax with him when he went into the cedar trees after the cattle. He needed a new cedar post to add to the fence where the damn cattle had pushed one down and gone for a stroll outside the corral. A day wasted because his lazy son hadn't put a post in the ground well enough to hold. He jabbed his horse with his spurs to . . .\r\n\r\nPlease leave a comment with your first 50 words on the topic \"add new post.\"", "categories": ["Children's Writing Prompts", "fiction", "Writing prompt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 14:14:19", "language": "en", "author": "69017", "url": "http://first50.wordpress.com/?p=3277", "title": "My Bucket List", "blog": "69924", "post_id": "429613", "tags": [], "blogname": "First 50 Words - Writing Prompts for Writing Practice", "date": "2012-05-01 07:14:19", "content": "Many of the items on my bucket list involve travel. For example, see Carolina's Outer Banks. Yet travel seems less and less like fun as I grow older and more like an exhausting effort that is too much work. I need to toss my whole bucket list and start a new one with ideas that would be uplifting but close to home. Teach a WordPress class at the senior center: that's an appealing idea to me.\r\n\r\nPlease leave a comment with your first 50 words on the topic \"my bucket list.\"", "categories": ["Children's Writing Prompts", "fiction", "Writing prompt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 13:08:51", "language": "en", "author": "69017", "url": "http://first50.wordpress.com/?p=3279", "title": "I Don't Want", "blog": "69924", "post_id": "1559318", "tags": [], "blogname": "First 50 Words - Writing Prompts for Writing Practice", "date": "2012-05-02 06:08:51", "content": "There are many things I want to do. And there are an equal number of things I don't want to do. For example, I don't want to go to China, nor do I want to climb a mountain. I don't want to eat sushi and I don't want to earn a living as a police officer. I don't want to get in an argument. I don't want to see members of my family unhappy. I don't want to wear a dress. I . . .\r\n\r\nPlease leave a comment with your first 50 words on the topic \"I don't want.\"", "categories": ["Children's Writing Prompts", "Essay", "Writing prompt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 14:08:13", "language": "en", "author": "69017", "url": "http://first50.wordpress.com/?p=3281", "title": "You Talk Funny", "blog": "69924", "post_id": "500780", "tags": [], "blogname": "First 50 Words - Writing Prompts for Writing Practice", "date": "2012-05-03 07:08:13", "content": "She said, \"At me on Twitter.\" No, she actually said, \"@ me on Twitter.\" What a strange thing to say. And she wanted me to follow her. Follow her? Like walk behind her? Huh? Then someone said, \"Jesus wants you to follow him, but not on Twitter.\" Twitter again \u2013 where I can @ you or follow you. Twitter talk is funny.\r\n\r\nPlease leave a comment with your first 50 words on the topic \"you talk funny.\"", "categories": ["Children's Writing Prompts", "fiction", "Writing prompt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 13:18:11", "language": "en", "author": "69017", "url": "http://first50.wordpress.com/?p=3283", "title": "Yo", "blog": "69924", "post_id": "732423", "tags": [], "blogname": "First 50 Words - Writing Prompts for Writing Practice", "date": "2012-05-04 06:18:11", "content": "She wore all black, an array of tattoos, multiple studs, and greasy hair. Yet she walked with purpose and the confident air of owning her space. She made a run at the wide-eyed manager, who actually backed up a step or two in the face of her approach. \"Yo,\" she said. She pointed to a table full of potential diners who looked a lot like her. \"We're waiting for service. We're being ignored. You looking for a lawsuit?\"\r\n\r\nThe manager . . .\r\n\r\nPlease leave a comment with your first 50 words on the topic \"yo.\"", "categories": ["Children's Writing Prompts", "fiction", "Writing prompt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 18:52:18", "language": "en", "author": "69096", "url": "http://tkcollier.wordpress.com/?p=4466", "title": "Trends In The Spread of Civilization", "blog": "70003", "post_id": "1478168", "tags": ["China", "European Union", "Financial Crisis", "South America", "United States"], "blogname": "Terryorisms", "date": "2012-05-03 13:52:18", "content": "In his latest book, Civilization, The West and the Rest, the economic and financial historian Niall Ferguson argues that Western civilization's rise to global dominance over the past 500 years was due mainly to six killer apps, as he calls them: competition, science, rule of law, modern medicine, consumerism, and the work ethic.\r\n\r\nWhile \"the Rest\" lacked these concepts, they might not for much longer, as emerging markets are quickly catching up. Someday, they could even surpass the West. (On May 22 and 29, PBS will air a program based on Civilization.)\r\n\r\nWhat made the West unusual was that risk takers were not only rewarded but honored, whether in science, exploration, or in trade. Spreading across the Atlantic from Europe is an anti-risk culture that manifests itself in two ways. One is the welfare state, designed to remove risk from your life by guaranteeing you an income from the cradle to the grave. That's great because it means that nobody is starving in the streets for want of work. But it isn't great if you create poverty traps and disincentives, so that people in the bottom quintile never work, which is the case in much of Europe.\r\n\r\n<a name=\"U30303630796FEE\"></a>\r\n\r\nThe other way in which the anti-risk culture manifests itself is with the manic regulatory mentality that tries to prescribe rules for every eventuality, including the tiny, tiny risk that an asteroid will hit this building. Regulations that protect from every eventuality end up being paralyzing because the more things are proscribed, the more the ordinary entrepreneur has to be afraid that if he doesn't comply, he will get sued.\r\n\r\nvia <a href=\"http://online.barrons.com/article/SB50001424053111903591504577361932442772376.html?reflink=wsj_redirect#text.email\">Is America Becoming an Anti-Risk Welfare State? - Barrons.com</a>.", "categories": ["Economy &#038; Business", "Geopolitics"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 04:36:21", "language": "en", "author": "69746", "url": "http://ronnierocket.com/?p=2189", "title": "My life with the Beastie Boys", "blog": "70653", "post_id": "1876050", "tags": ["2012", "Adam Yauch", "The Beastie Boys"], "blogname": "RONNIEROCKET.COM", "date": "2012-05-05 04:36:21", "content": "My first concert with the Beastie Boys was in New York City. They were a punk band back then. They released a great punk single, \"Polly Wog Stew\". I imported it to the record store in Copenhagen, where I worked. We probably sold around 20 copies.\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lu5VkypHzoI?rel=0&amp;w=420&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nThen they made a record called \"Cooky Puss\". Back then, we still used landlines (and I used a telex machine to order the vinyl records from around the world!). And telephone calls <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DnswpHvAqLc\">often showed up in songs</a>. This track was especially good. Both entertaining and funky, I personally pushed this record hard in Copenhagen in the eighties. We probably sold a couple of boxes of the 12\" single.\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0DOMxm0o12c?rel=0&amp;w=420&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nThen they got signed to Def Jam. And Def Jam had a deal with Columbia Records (CBS in Europe). The underground days were over. Their first single for Def Jam was \"Rock Hard\". Heavy beats and snotty rap. I don't think the record company had any idea what to do with it. Initially, it was not released in Europe. I imported the American 12\" single. Sold a couple of boxes of that. Then all hell broke loose.\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0ilZshY6uUo?rel=0&amp;w=420&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nThe first album came out and it was a blockbuster. Now, the record company got interested. It went to number 1 on the Billboard charts. But of course the artist did not get payed. They never made an album for that record company again.\r\n\r\nThe next single was \"She's On It\". It was a mix of their old punk rock days and their new found hip hop stardom.\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9PLfjhQG97I?rel=0&amp;w=420&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nI remember seeing The Beastie Boys live again in London at a big event in Brixton. It was a double concert with Run DMC. It was the biggest thing in London that year. All the famous people were there. I remember drinking beer - a lot of beer! - with the actor Matt Dillon [check <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qngT3cn9I6g\">this movie scene</a>!] in the VIP room. It was fun times. It was good times. \r\n\r\nThen came all the hit singles, \"Fight for your right...\" and so on. The Beastie Boys were huge and a teenage phenomenon.\r\n\r\nThen came the \"difficult\" second album. It turned out to be their masterpiece. \"Paul's Boutique\" was a landmark album. Not only in hip hop, but in modern pop music. Again, the new record company Capitol Records (EMI) had no clue. But at least they stuck with the band and continued to release their music. And paying them, I guess. Also, financially supporting their upcoming own label, I think.\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BptQHAW2T5M?rel=0&amp;w=420&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nLater in life, the Beastie Boys made their own record label, Grand Royal Records. They released the first album by one of my favourite artists, Sean Ono Lennon. Here is the first single with a music video directed by Spike Jonze:\r\n\r\n[youtube http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=awoTylLBF9I?rel=0&amp;w=420&amp;h=315]\r\n\r\nHere is <a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/seanonolennon/status/198471137338982400\">a moving tweet from Sean</a>.\r\n\r\nAdam Yauch. You will be missed. R.I.P.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://ronnierocket.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/beastie-boys-cooky-puss_f.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ronnierocket.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/beastie-boys-cooky-puss_f.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"beastie boys - cooky puss_f\" width=\"580\" height=\"570\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2190\" /></a>", "categories": ["Music", "Rock"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 10:28:39", "language": "en", "author": "69746", "url": "http://ronnierocket.com/?p=2196", "title": "Groucho Marx and Diana Ross on the dancefloor", "blog": "70653", "post_id": "656352", "tags": ["1966", "Bobby Darin", "Diana Ross", "Groucho Marx", "Los Angeles"], "blogname": "RONNIEROCKET.COM", "date": "2012-05-06 10:28:39", "content": "<a href=\"http://ronnierocket.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/marx.jpg\"><img src=\"http://ronnierocket.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/marx.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"marx\" width=\"580\" height=\"579\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2197\" /></a>\r\n\r\nSeventy-year-old Groucho Marx showed his youth as he did the frug with Diana Ross, 22-year-old lead singer of the supremes, a female rock \u2019n\u2019 roll group, at an outdoor barbecue party. The party was given by actor-singer Bobby Darin at his Bel-Air home in Los Angeles on August 19, 1966. Groucho later admitted that is was the first time he had been on a dance floor in 20 years. [<a href=\"http://www.washingtonpost.com/groucho-marx-diana-ross/2012/02/10/gIQAU0tB4Q_photo.html\">Source]</a>", "categories": ["Photography"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 04:56:36", "language": "en", "author": "70078", "url": "https://bonniep.wordpress.com/?p=2236", "title": "Mostly Tulips, or adventures in straight horizon line photography", "blog": "70985", "post_id": "1715873", "tags": [], "blogname": "Jaded Optimist", "date": "2012-04-30 21:56:36", "content": "<p>My parents came for spring break a week or two ago, to hang out with the kids while G and I worked. I think the kids had a good time (although C was battling a week long flu-or-cold-or-something and M showed a bit too much Grammy favoritism). Hopefully my parents did too! I did make chocolate custard tart one night for dessert, so that should have helped. </p>  <p>The last day of the visit, we were able to visit the <a href=\"http://www.tulipfestival.org/\">tulip festival</a>. This is our 7th spring here in WA, and every year I have wanted to visit the tulip festival\u2014finally, this was our year. Except for a late start and a GPS that kept wanting me to drive directly down the street that was closed for an art festival, we made it there in time to enjoy good weather. The tulips lived up to their promise. My even camera holding, only sometimes.</p>  <p><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/018.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"018\" border=\"0\" alt=\"018\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/018_thumb.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"181\" /></a><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/030.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"030\" border=\"0\" alt=\"030\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/030_thumb.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"181\" /></a></p>    <p><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/064.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"064\" border=\"0\" alt=\"064\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/064_thumb.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"181\" /></a><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/0441.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"044\" border=\"0\" alt=\"044\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/044_thumb1.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"181\" /></a></p>  <p>&#160;</p>    <p><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/050.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"050\" border=\"0\" alt=\"050\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/050_thumb.jpg\" width=\"181\" height=\"260\" /></a><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/061.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"061\" border=\"0\" alt=\"061\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/061_thumb.jpg\" width=\"181\" height=\"260\" /></a></p>  <p>The girls got their faces painted, and exhibited their usual antics. This seems to have led to the world tipping slightly.</p>  <p><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/013.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-left:0;padding-left:0;padding-right:0;display:inline;border-top:0;border-right:0;padding-top:0;\" title=\"013\" border=\"0\" alt=\"013\" src=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/013_thumb.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"181\" /></a><a href=\"http://bonniep.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/019.jpg\"><img style=\"background-image:none;border-bottom:0;border-le