{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 11:06:48", "language": "en", "author": "87337", "url": "http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=4479", "title": "VIDEO: MOVIES: REVIEW: Thirst aka Bakjwi (2009)", "blog": "88828", "post_id": "1557503", "tags": [], "blogname": "Clint&#039;s blog", "date": "2012-05-03 07:06:48", "content": "<img class=\"alignleft\" style=\"border:0 none;float:left;margin:5px 10px;\" src=\"http://cdn-6.nflximg.com/us/boxshots/large/70114016.jpg\" alt=\" movie cover\" /><img class=\"alignright\" style=\"border:0 none;float:right;margin:5px 10px;\" src=\"http://clintjcl.files.wordpress.com/2009/02/rather_be_watching_tv.gif\" alt=\"I'd rather be watching TV!\" width=\"71\" height=\"119\" />[<a href=\"http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0762073/\">IMDB link</a>] [<a href=\"http://www.netflix.com/Movie/Thirst/70114016?strackid=5be942f612b38108_0_srl&amp;strkid=214240453_0_0&amp;trkid=222336\">Netflix link</a>]\r\n\r\n<strong>PLOT SUMMARY:</strong> A priest accidentally becomes a vampire.\r\n\r\n<strong>UNCOMFORTABLE PLOT SUMMARY (inspired by <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/2009/08/27/comedy-movies-uncomfortable-plot-summaries/\">this</a>):</strong> [<em>highlight for spoilers</em>]<span style=\"font-size:medium;\">\u2192</span> <span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">Vampirism makes Christians suicidal.</span>\r\n\r\n<strong>PEOPLE:</strong> The 12th film directed by <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Park_Chan-wook\" target=\"_target20459\">Chan-Wook Park</a> (<a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=2752\" target=\"_target20874\">Oldboy</a>, <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=3316\" target=\"_target20449\">Sympathy For Lady Vengeance</a>, <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=3526\" target=\"_target20268\">Sympathy For Mr. Vengeance</a>). This is the 4th we've seen. Starring Kang-ho Song (who was in both <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=3316\" target=\"_target20449\">Sympathy For Lady Vengeance</a> AND <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=3526\" target=\"_target20268\">Sympathy For Mr. Vengeance</a>), Ok-bin Kim, Hae-sook Kim, Ha-kyun Shin (also in both 'vengeance' films), Mercedes Cabral.\r\n\r\n<strong>QUIRKS:</strong> A vampire movie, but one dealing with an incredibly moral main character. As a priest, he can't bring himself to kill, so he does what he can to avoid doing so as much as possible.\r\n\r\nAt least, as much as a vampire can avoid such a thing. (Maybe he could take lessons in vampire vegetarianism from the <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=2787\" target=\"_target28642\">Twilight</a> vampires?)\r\n\r\n<strong>VISUALS:</strong> Park always shoots his movies quite well; they look as good as any Hollywood movie.\r\n\r\n<strong>MORALS:</strong> The main character, the priest, has to deal with a set of changing morals. Unwilling to kill, but needing blood to live, comprimises obviously end up having to be made. He loses his virginity too...\r\n\r\n<strong>BAD STUFF:</strong> This is my least favorite of the 4 <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Park_Chan-wook\" target=\"_target39932\">Chan-Wook Park</a> movies I've seen... But it's still quite good.\r\n\r\n<strong>CONCLUSION:</strong> A great vampire flick. Very different. We were, in a sense, slightly disappointed, simply because of how good <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Park_Chan-wook\" target=\"_target43828\">Chan-Wook Park</a>'s *other* movies are. But in another sense, this was waaaaay better <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=4235\" target=\"_target42997\">Let The Right One In</a>, or even <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=2787\" target=\"_target44222\">Twilight</a>.\r\n\r\n<strong>RATINGS:</strong>\r\nClint: <a href=\"http://www.netflix.com\" target=\"_target54482\">Netflix</a>: 4/5 stars. <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com\" target=\"_target54299\">IMDB</a>: 7.4/10. I had a really hard time deciding if it's a 7 or an 8. So I'm saying 7, but barely.\r\nCarolyn: <a href=\"http://www.netflix.com\" target=\"_target58378\">Netflix</a>: 4/5 stars. <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com\" target=\"_target58195\">IMDB</a>: 8/10.\r\n\r\nThe native public rating for this movie is: <a href=\"http://www.imdb.com\" target=\"_target62091\">IMDB</a>: 7.3/10, <a href=\"http://www.netflix.com\" target=\"_target62274\">Netflix</a>: 3.3/5 stars (<a href=\"http://www.netflix.com\" target=\"_target62274\">Netflix</a>'s predicted rating for us was 3.7/5 stars).\r\n\r\n<strong>RECOMMENDATION:</strong> Vampire film fans must see this!\r\n\r\n<strong>SIMILAR MOVIES:</strong> <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=2787\" target=\"_target67594\">Twilight</a>. <a href=\"http://clintjcl.wordpress.com/?p=4235\" target=\"_target66370\">Let The Right One In</a>. Vampire flicks in general...\r\n\r\n<strong>FRIENDS' RATINGS:</strong> <a href=\"http://lonecellotheory.livejournal.com/\" target=\"_target73860\">Ian</a> really liked it. <a href=\"http://www.sourswinger.name/blog/\" target=\"_target73559\">Jordan</a> liked it.<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<strong>Mood:</strong> a bit wet\r\n<strong>Music:</strong> <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kreator\" target=\"_target88640\">Kreator</a> - Mental Slavery", "categories": ["Carolyn", "Clint", "Media", "Movies", "People", "Reviews", "Video"], "likes": []}
