{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 08:33:32", "language": "en", "author": "108141", "url": "http://cobb.wordpress.com/?p=9196", "title": "Greatest - fucking - conversation - ever!", "blog": "109045", "post_id": "1550172", "tags": [], "blogname": "", "date": "2012-04-30 09:33:32", "content": "<blockquote><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jerry</strong> (answering phone):</span> Moscone's Bail Bonds\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> It's Jack Walsh. Put Eddie on.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jerry</strong> (to Eddie):</span> It's Jack.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie</strong> (picks up phone):</span> Yeah. This better be good news, fuckin' Jack, because you got five hours left.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> No it's not Eddie. I'm calling to let you know that you're a dead motherfucker. Do you understand me?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> Wait a minute. Wait a minute.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> You put Marvin on this, you fucking piece of shit! You're fucking deceptive! You vermin! You serpent!\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> You fucking done yet?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> You slime ball in a sea of pus!\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> You blew it!\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> What?!\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> You blew it, allright. You had the guy four fuckin' days Jack. Four days! You could've fucking.. You could've walked him backwards and not fuckin' blown it, but you blew it!\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> When have I ever fu.. When have I ever let you down you fucking RAT!\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> Are you fucking nuts telling Dorfler I offered you $100.000 when I told him I'd give him $25.000?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> Wait.. Wai.. When did you speak to him?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> What's the difference?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> When did you speak to Marvin?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> He called me fucking what...ten minutes ago, yelling and screaming, telling me to go fuck myself. You're telling me to... Everybody's telling me to go fuck myself! What am I supposed to do just sit on my fucking butt!!?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> Eddie. Eddie! EDDIE! What are you fucking talking about?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> Look, you got five hours left. Can you bring the fucking Duke in, yes or no?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> I thought he's bringing him to you...\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> I just talked to fucking Dorfler, he don't have the Duke.\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> What?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> Where's the fucking Duke!? Hello!?\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Jack:</strong></span> ...I'll talk to you later. (Hangs up phone)\r\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><strong>Eddie:</strong></span> JACK?!</blockquote>\r\n<pre>Time frame: <strong>1\u00a0 min 14 sec</strong> \r\nF-word count: <strong>18</strong></pre>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><em>Eddie - Joe Pantoliano</em>\r\n<em>Jack - Robert DeNiro</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-9197 aligncenter\" style=\"border:3px solid black;\" title=\"MidnightRun\" src=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/midnightrun.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"480\" height=\"360\" /></p>", "categories": ["film &#038; s\u00e5nt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 18:08:16", "language": "en", "author": "108141", "url": "http://cobb.wordpress.com/?p=9200", "title": "TV-blogg 010512-140512", "blog": "109045", "post_id": "1416144", "tags": [], "blogname": "", "date": "2012-05-01 19:08:16", "content": "Lite lagom utm\u00e5lande d\u00e5... F\u00f6r ovanlighetens skull. :)\r\n\r\nIdag (1/5) tycker jag att man kan b\u00e4nka sig framf\u00f6r TV6 klockan 21.00, och kolla in <strong>The Replacements</strong>. Skit i att recensenterna mer eller mindre unisont valt att pissa \u00f6ver den - de \u00e4r idioter hela h\u00f6gen! Visst, den f\u00f6ljer ett v\u00e4lk\u00e4nt m\u00f6nster (underdog-sportlag fyllt av bisarra losers k\u00e4mpar mot otroliga odds) och den \u00e4r till viss del f\u00f6ruts\u00e4gbar. Men i det g\u00f6r den inte mindre underh\u00e5llande. :)\r\nMen bara f\u00f6r att ni kollar p\u00e5 TV6, gl\u00f6m inte att tajma dokument\u00e4ren <strong>Senna</strong> p\u00e5 SVT1 kl.22.00. Handlar om Brasilienf\u00f6dda racingf\u00f6raren Aryton Senna (f.1960 - d.1994), vars korta men lysande racingkarri\u00e4r och extroverta personlighet gjorde honom s\u00e5 dyrkad i hemlandet att regeringen utlyste tre dagars landssorg d\u00e5 han dog, och \u00f6ver 200.000 m\u00e4nniskor bes\u00f6kte hans kista i Sao Paolo innan han begravdes. Sev\u00e4rd, for sure!\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 onsdagen (2/5) \u00e4r det Guilty Pleasure-dagen (s\u00e4ger jag), och vad passar b\u00e4ttre d\u00e5 \u00e4n att se en nytolkning av en ganska usel film med David Carradine och Sylvester Stallone fr\u00e5n 1975? -Nytolkningen \u00e4r fr\u00e5n 2008, har Jason Statham i huvudrollen och har absolut ingenting gemensamt med originalet, bortsett fr\u00e5n en ganska gener\u00f6s m\u00e4ngd blod och v\u00e5ld.\r\nMen den \u00e4r underh\u00e5llande \u00e4nd\u00e5, jag lovar, och den heter <strong>Death Race</strong> - visas p\u00e5 TV6 kl.21.00.\r\n\r\nF\u00f6r att ha n\u00e5t att se p\u00e5 torsdagen (3/5) b\u00f6r man ha Discovery Channel.\r\nNytt avsnitt av <strong>Mythbusters</strong> visas n\u00e4mligen d\u00e4r klockan 21.00.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 fredagen (4/5) kan man v\u00e4lja bland allt m\u00f6jligt. Till exempel Adam Sandler som Happy Gilmore - den misslyckade hockeyspelaren som b\u00f6rjar golfa (<strong>Happy Gilmore</strong>, TV6, kl.21.00). Eller varf\u00f6r inte den unga killen med nytaget k\u00f6rkort som f\u00e5r en sunkig gammal bil av sin pappa i f\u00f6delsedagspresent, en bil som visar sig vara en robot fr\u00e5n en annan planet (<strong>Transformers</strong>, TV4, kl.23.00). Man kan \u00e4ven se en film man redan sett tjugofem g\u00e5nger tidigare, i vilken Tom Hanks och Meg Ryan tr\u00e4ffas h\u00f6gt upp i Empire State Building (<strong>Sleepless in Seattle</strong>, TV3, kl.20.00).\r\nMen jag tycker att om man ska v\u00e4lja n\u00e5got denna dag, s\u00e5 b\u00f6r man v\u00e4lja den om tv\u00e5 konkurrerande magiker vars rivalitet leder till svek, svartsjuka och v\u00e4rre. <strong>The Prestige</strong> \u00e4r helt klart kv\u00e4llens film! Visas p\u00e5 TV8 kl.21.00.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 l\u00f6rdagen (5/5) finns det bara en sak som \u00e4r sj\u00e4lvklar att v\u00e4lja, s\u00e5 ignorera <strong>Runaway Bride</strong>, <strong>The Wedding Singer</strong> och <strong>White men can't jump</strong>! Filmen man ska se denna dag \u00e4r <strong>Moon</strong> (SVT2, kl.22.20). Ett finurligt existensiellt drama som utspelar sig p\u00e5 en m\u00e5nstation. Filmens huvudroll - och ENDA roll spelas av Sam Rockwell, och han g\u00f6r det LYSANDE! (Ok d\u00e5, nitpickers, Kevin Spacey har r\u00f6sten till m\u00e5nbasens dator).\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 s\u00f6ndagen (6/5) funderar i alla fall JAG p\u00e5 att se Roman Polanskis <strong>The Ghost Writer</strong>, med Ewan McGregos och Pierce Brosnan i huvudrollen. Verkar sp\u00e4nnande.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 m\u00e5ndagen (7/5) \u00e4r den dags f\u00f6r <strong>Out of Sight</strong>, regisserad av Stephen Soderbergh med George Clooney och Jennifer Lopez i huvudrollerna. Har h\u00f6rt att den ska vara bra, och har fruktl\u00f6st letat efter den p\u00e5 Hemmakv\u00e4ll flera g\u00e5nger. Men nu s\u00e5...\r\nVisas p\u00e5 TV3 kl.22.00.\r\n\r\nSVT1 sl\u00e5r p\u00e5 stortrumman n\u00e4sta tisdag (8/5) och bjussar p\u00e5 tv\u00e5 filmer mer eller mindre p\u00e5 raken. Den f\u00f6rsta \u00e4r <strong>The Greatest Movie Ever Sold</strong>, gjord av dokument\u00e4rfilmmakaren Morgan <em>'Super Size Me'</em> Spurlock. H\u00e4r g\u00f6r han en dokument\u00e4r om produktplacering - HELT finansierad av produktplacering! Intressanta avsl\u00f6janden och m\u00e5nga skratt - gissar jag p\u00e5 i alla fall.\r\nDen andra filmen \u00e4r en filmtolkning fr\u00e5n 2002 av Alexandre Dumas bok<em> The Count of Monte Cristo</em> fr\u00e5n 1844. Jag har aldrig l\u00e4st boken och har aldrig sett n\u00e5gon filmatisering av den, men har l\u00e4nge frestats att se den efter att m\u00e5nga g\u00e5nger ha sett <em>The Shawshank Redemtion</em>...\r\n\r\n[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yGiiy09mCtU]\r\n\r\n<strong>The Greatest Movie Ever Sold</strong> visas kl.22.00.\r\n<strong>The Count of Monte Cristo</strong> visas kl.23.40.\r\n\r\nOnsdagen (9/5) \u00e4r m\u00e4rkligt ointressant, men det g\u00f6r inget - eftersom man f\u00e5r ett nytt avsnitt av <strong>Mythbusters</strong> dagen efter, p\u00e5 torsdagen den 10/5, Discovery Channel kl.21.00.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 fredagen (11/5) lockar TV3 med en film om matlagning och livs\u00f6den. L\u00e5ter som en riktig chickflick, eller hur? Men jag m\u00e5ste erk\u00e4nna att jag \u00e4nd\u00e5 lockas att se <strong>Julie &amp; Julia</strong>:\r\n\r\n[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ozRK7VXQl-k]\r\n\r\nVisas som sagt p\u00e5 TV3 kl.20.00.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 l\u00f6rdagen (12/5) visas en massa filmer jag redan skrivit om femtioelva g\u00e5nger, men d\u00e4r finns en jag bara skrivit om n\u00e5gra f\u00e5 g\u00e5nger. Visst, det \u00e4r en f\u00e5nig komedi med Adam Sandler, men den har hj\u00e4rta, tankv\u00e4rda \u00f6gonblick och en schysst sensmoral - \u00e4ven om den (sensmoralen) kanske \u00e4r lite v\u00e4l \u00f6vertydlig. :)\r\n<strong>Click</strong>, om en man som f\u00e5r tag p\u00e5 en fj\u00e4rrkontroll som g\u00f6r det m\u00f6jligt att styra sitt liv - pausa d\u00e4r han vill, spola tillbaka d\u00e4r han vill och snabbspola f\u00f6rbi alla tr\u00e5kiga \u00f6gonblick - visas i Kanal5 kl.21.20.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 s\u00f6ndagen (13/5) visas visserligen s\u00e5v\u00e4l Tom Cruise-filmen <strong>The Last Samurai</strong> (TV4, kl.21.00) som Guilty Pleasure-komedin <strong>Bird on a wire</strong> (TV6, kl.23.00), men jag tycker att man ist\u00e4llet b\u00f6r se Paul Greengrass film <strong>Green Zone</strong> p\u00e5 TV3 kl.21.00. MYCKET sp\u00e4nnande, h\u00f6gaktuell och troligtvis alldeles f\u00f6r sanningsenlig f\u00f6r att det ska vara bekv\u00e4mt.\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 m\u00e5ndagen (14/5) kan man kolla in Bruce Willis i en massa olika roliga f\u00f6rkl\u00e4dnader...ja, \u00e5 Richard Gere och Sidney Poitier ocks\u00e5 f\u00f6rst\u00e5s. Filmen <strong>The Jackal</strong> visas p\u00e5 TV3 kl.22.00.\r\n<h3>-Vadd\u00e5...<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\">r\u00e4cker</span> inte allt detta?!?!</h3>", "categories": ["film &#038; s\u00e5nt"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 08:02:31", "language": "en", "author": "108141", "url": "http://cobb.wordpress.com/?p=9204", "title": "Stockholmshelg...", "blog": "109045", "post_id": "688595", "tags": [], "blogname": "", "date": "2012-05-05 09:02:31", "content": "\u00c4r nere i Kungliga Hufvudstaden och h\u00e4lsar p\u00e5.\r\nKom hit redan p\u00e5 onsdagen, och eftermiddagen spenderades utomhus, hela torsdagen spenderades utomhus, Hela fredagen spenderades mer eller mindre utomhus och idag ska jag vara \u00e5tminstone halva dagen utomhus... Ser faktiskt fram emot morgondagen - s\u00f6ndagen - d\u00e5 det inte blir mycket utomhus! :)\r\n\r\nP\u00e5 torsdagen gick\u00a0vi fr\u00e5n \u00c5rstaberg till centralen via StEriksplan (och f\u00f6r de som hittar i stan s\u00e5 vet ni att det inte \u00e4r en s\u00e4rskilt kort str\u00e4cka). Vi gick bland annat \u00f6ver V\u00e4sterbron, d\u00e4r jag kollade in fenomenet \"k\u00e4rleksl\u00e5s\" - en kinesisk tradition som g\u00e5r ut p\u00e5 att brudpar s\u00e4tter sina initialer p\u00e5 ett h\u00e4ngl\u00e5s, l\u00e5ser fast det i en bro och kastar nyckeln i vattnet. K\u00e4rleken ska d\u00e5 vara f\u00f6r evigt...\r\nTydligen kom denna tradition till Stockholm 2009, och den verkar vara poppis! :)\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_kc3a4rlekslc3a5s1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-9205\" title=\"Stockholm_k\u00e4rleksl\u00e5s1\" src=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_kc3a4rlekslc3a5s1.jpg?w=150\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"112\" /></a>\u00a0<a href=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_kc3a4rlekslc3a5s2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-9206\" title=\"Stockholm_k\u00e4rleksl\u00e5s2\" src=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_kc3a4rlekslc3a5s2.jpg?w=150\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"112\" /></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><em><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-9207\" title=\"Stockholm_k\u00e4rleksl\u00e5s3\" src=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_kc3a4rlekslc3a5s3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"383\" />\r\nNej, jag\u00a0k\u00e4nner inte\u00a0Henrik och\u00a0Emma, jag ville bara visa ungef\u00e4r hur l\u00e5sen ser ut.</em></p>\r\nP\u00e5 fredagen var det shopping galore som g\u00e4llde (piercingsmycken, origamipapper, kl\u00e4der, origamipapper, thaikryddor och origamipapper). Avslutade med att slappna av i en biosalong i 2\u00bd timme; s\u00e5g Avengers igen, denna g\u00e5ng i 2D, och den var precis lika bra som i 3D - faktiskt b\u00e4ttre eftersom biljetten kostade mindre!\r\n\r\nIdag blir det ett bes\u00f6k hemma hos syster, sv\u00e5ger och v\u00e4rldens b\u00e4sta lilla Oliver! :)\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">Har h\u00f6rt av Inger att det just nu sn\u00f6ar i Ume\u00e5 (sn\u00f6ar - <strong>sn\u00f6ar</strong> - <strong>SN\u00d6AR!!!</strong>),\r\noch passar d\u00e5 p\u00e5 att s\u00e4ga att underbara, v\u00e5riga Stockholm \u00e4r s\u00e5 j\u00e4kla vackert!</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><a href=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_utsikt-frc3a5n-vc3a4sterbron.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-9208\" title=\"Stockholm_utsikt fr\u00e5n V\u00e4sterbron\" src=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_utsikt-frc3a5n-vc3a4sterbron.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"382\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong>MEN...</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">...v\u00e5ren f\u00f6r s\u00e5klart med sig andra \"roliga\" inslag.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-9209\" title=\"Stockholm_POLLEN\" src=\"http://cobb.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/stockholm_pollen.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"154\" />\r\n<em>Jag kallar den:</em> 'Pollen-\u00f6gon'<em>.</em></p>", "categories": ["globetrotter", "none of the above"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 00:50:35", "language": "en", "author": "108791", "url": "http://throgos.wordpress.com/?p=748", "title": "\u039a\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac\u03c4\u03b6\u03b1\u03c1\u03bf\u03b9", "blog": "109684", "post_id": "1483487", "tags": [], "blogname": "Ohm", "date": "2012-05-03 02:50:35", "content": "<p>\u03a3\u03c5\u03c7\u03bd\u03ac \u03be\u03c5\u03c0\u03bd\u03ac\u03c9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03c1\u03c9\u03b9\u03bd\u03ac \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b1\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03c1\u03cd\u03b6\u03c9 \u03ad\u03bd\u03b1\u03bd \u03ba\u03cc\u03c3\u03bc\u03bf \u03c0\u03bf\u03c5 \u03b4\u03b5\u03bd \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03af\u03bc\u03b5\u03bd\u03b1. \u0395\u03af\u03bd\u03b1\u03b9 \u03bb\u03b5\u03c2 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9, \u03b1\u03c6\u03cc\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u03c0\u03ad\u03c3\u03c9 \u03ae\u03c3\u03c5\u03c7\u03bf\u03c2 \u03b3\u03b9\u03b1 \u03cd\u03c0\u03bd\u03bf \u03b3\u03c1\u03b1\u03c0\u03ce\u03bd\u03bf\u03bd\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2 \u03c4\u03bf \u03bc\u03b1\u03be\u03b9\u03bb\u03ac\u03c1\u03b9 \u03bc\u03bf\u03c5, \u03b5\u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03bf\u03bc\u03bc\u03cd\u03c1\u03b9\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03bb\u03b9\u03ba\u03ac\u03c4\u03b6\u03b1\u03c1\u03bf\u03b9 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03ba\u03bf\u03c6\u03c4\u03b5\u03c1\u03ac \u03b4\u03cc\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9\u03b1 \u03c1\u03bf\u03ba\u03b1\u03bd\u03af\u03b6\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03c4\u03bf \u03b4\u03ad\u03bd\u03c4\u03c1\u03bf \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u03c0\u03c1\u03b1\u03b3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c4\u03b7\u03c4\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b5\u03bd\u03cc\u03c3\u03c9 \u03ba\u03bf\u03b9\u03bc\u03ac\u03bc\u03b1\u03b9 \u03b3\u03b1\u03bb\u03ae\u03bd\u03b9\u03bf\u03c2. \u03a3\u03af\u03b3\u03bf\u03c5\u03c1\u03b1 \u03b4\u03b5\u03bd \u03ae\u03c4\u03b1\u03bd \u03ad\u03c4\u03c3\u03b9 \u03c4\u03b1 \u03c0\u03c1\u03ac\u03b3\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03b1 \u03c7\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2. \u03a0\u03cc\u03c3\u03bf \u03bc\u03ac\u03bb\u03bb\u03bf\u03bd \u03c0\u03c1\u03bf\u03c7\u03c4\u03b5\u03c2. \u039d\u03b1 \u03b4\u03bf\u03cd\u03bc\u03b5 \u03c0\u03bf\u03b9\u03b1 \u03ba\u03bf\u03bc\u03bc\u03ac\u03c4\u03b9\u03b1 \u03b8\u03b1 \u03bb\u03b5\u03af\u03c0\u03bf\u03c5\u03bd \u03b1\u03cd\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf.</p>", "categories": ["\u0394\u03b9\u03ac\u03c6\u03bf\u03c1\u03b1"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 21:50:05", "language": "en", "author": "109020", "url": "http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/?p=2236", "title": "Recurrent Low Back Pain", "blog": "109912", "post_id": "1665466", "tags": ["Back pain", "chiropractic care", "low back pain", "low back pain recurrence"], "blogname": "Everett Chiropractic Center Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 21:50:05", "content": "It was a year ago that an article published in the <em>Journal of Occupational and Environmental Medicine</em> looked at the impact of \"maintenance treatment\" in recurrent low back pain. Here are their conclusions: \"In work-related nonspecific low back pain (LBP), the use of health maintenance care provided by physical therapist or physician services was associated with a higher disability recurrence than in chiropractic services or no treatment.\"\r\n\r\n<strong>Some other quotes from the article:</strong>\r\n\r\nLow back pain is \"one of the costliest work-related injuries in the United States in terms of disability and treatment costs.\" \"An additional, important component of the human and economic costs is the recurrence of LBP.\"\r\n\r\n\"Health maintenance care is a clinical intervention approach thought to prevent recurrent episodes of LBP. ... with the aim of improving health status and preventing recurrences of a previous health condition.\"\r\n\r\nChiropractic patients had \"fewer surgeries, used fewer opioids, and had lower costs for medical care than the other provider groups.\"\r\n\r\n\"After controlling for demographic factors and mulitple severity indicators, patients suffering nonospecific work-related LBP who received health services mostly or only form a chiropractor had a lower risk of recurrent disability than the risk of any other provider type.\"\r\n\r\n\"Our findings seem to support the use of chiropractor services, as chiropractor services generally cost less than services from other providers.\"\r\n\r\nChiropractic patient had \"less expensive medical services and shorter initial periods of disability than cases treated by other providers.\"\r\n\r\n<strong>References:</strong> 1. Health Maintenance Care in Work-Related Low Back Pain and Its Association With Disability Recurrence. Journal of Occupational and Environmental Medicine. 2. Manuel Cifuentes, MD, PhD, Joanna Willetts, MS, Radoslaw, PhD, MA, MSc April 2011; Vol. 53, No 4 pp. 396-404 American Journal of Clinical Chiropractic", "categories": ["Back pain", "Be careful who you listen to!", "Chiropractic", "Workplace Wellness"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 22:03:06", "language": "en", "author": "109020", "url": "http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/?p=2241", "title": "Safety Training Follow Through: Bending &amp; Lifting", "blog": "109912", "post_id": "177881", "tags": ["back injury", "Back pain", "corporate wellness", "low back pain", "safety training"], "blogname": "Everett Chiropractic Center Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 22:03:06", "content": "In a recent study of \u00a03,000 training managers it was found that 60% did not have a formal process for determining whether or not employees had actually applied their safety training to job duties. (In the context of proper bending and lifting techniques, supervisors and managers can simply notice - or they can screen employees, formally or informally.)\r\n\r\nOnly 23% of the training managers claimed that their managers sought follow-up programs and feedback to determine the effectiveness and application of employee training sessions. In the context of proper bending and lifting technique, effectiveness and application are self-evident; follow-up and feedback are built into screenings and daily practice of the screening movement.\r\n\r\nThe unfortunate truth: safety programs are endorsed at the beginning but then are rarely seen through to become successful in creating a safe, positive company culture. In the context of bending and lifting every employee who begins to bend and lift properly will appreciate the difference. They will appreciate an employer who cares enough to screen their technique and offer training - and they will feel the difference immediately!\r\n\r\nOne way to ensure that employees take safety training seriously and apply it to their jobs is to provide post-training reinforcement. In the context of bending and lifting reinforcement can be provided daily by supervisors and managers who notice good technique and offer opportunities to stretch and practice movement patterns. More and more companies offer employees the opportunity to practice their training daily at work while on the clock - they do not want to risk not getting the benefits of the training. Depending on how they structure these sessions <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2011/09/19/mayo-clinic-research-urges-corporations-to-do-tai-chi/\">the benefits can be multiplied across many different aspects of health and safety components simultaneously</a>.\r\n\r\nMusculoskeletal disorders remain the leading cause of workplace injury and illness in this country with the low back pain \"epidemic\" being the single largest cause of disability. Direct and indirect costs range from $100 and $200 Billion. Conventional medicine's use of opioids, epidural steroid injections, and spine surgeries continues to increase in the face of research revealing their high cost and ineffectiveness. Over 80% of us will get low back pain. And yesterday's Post was about <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/05/01/recurrent-low-back-pain/\">the recurrence of low back pain</a>.\r\n\r\nIt seems worth it to try to prevent lifting injuries to the low back. It seems reasonable to address measurable risk factors and invest a little time and effort given the scope of the consequences for not doing so.\r\n\r\nContact us an offer that provides the training for Bending and Lifting (425) 348-5207.", "categories": ["Back pain", "Exercise", "Workplace Wellness"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 19:05:37", "language": "en", "author": "109020", "url": "http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/?p=2256", "title": "Bad Apples", "blog": "109912", "post_id": "1171077", "tags": ["chiropractic care", "Chiropractor", "Everett Chiropractic Center"], "blogname": "Everett Chiropractic Center Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 19:05:37", "content": "Your family and friends, neighbors and co-workers get exposed to all kinds of experiences and stories about chiropractic care. They aren't all favorable. You can help balance the scale in their minds and help them get the care they need by telling them your story. Tell them what it's like for you getting care in our office: How long you wait; whether you get all the attention and time you want and need; whether it hurts or not; whether you get good results; and whether or not you recommend us.\r\n\r\nWhy? Because there are a lot of different types of chiropractors and a lot of different types of office experiences.\r\n\r\nI heard this story today. A 21-year old college student who also happens to have \"Boeing insurance\" (which means good insurance) goes to a chiropractor in a nearby town. She is offered a two year contract which will involve her being seen first three times per week for a very long time, then twice a week for an even longer time, then once a week, then every two weeks until the two years are up. The cost to her? $4,000 on top of what her insurance company will pay.\r\n\r\nThis post isn't about whether or not and why this chiropractor may or may not be a crook. And it's not about all the efforts on the part of the State regulatory folks to prevent such practices.\r\n\r\nI simply want you to know that people do have these experiences and they do not leave a good impression about Chiropractors or about Chiropractic. If you had a different experience in our office, the people you know and interact with won't know any different unless you tell them.", "categories": ["Back pain", "Be careful who you listen to!", "Chiropractic"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 00:56:57", "language": "en", "author": "109020", "url": "http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/?p=2259", "title": "The Rise of Workplace Wellness", "blog": "109912", "post_id": "82180", "tags": ["Chiropractic", "Corporate Wellness Programs", "Everett", "WA", "workplace wellness"], "blogname": "Everett Chiropractic Center Blog", "date": "2012-05-06 00:56:57", "content": "That is the title of the lead article in the latest issue of <a href=\"http://www.ideafit.com/idea-fitness-journal\">Fitness Journal</a>. (Note: There are a lot of links so I have starred (*) the most important ones.)\r\n\r\n<strong>The Bad News: \"America Needs Help.\"</strong>\r\n\r\nLike most articles they start with the bad news. Here are three factoids: There has been a 36% hike in healthcare spending associated with <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2011/08/10/tai-chi-weight-loss-a-chiropractic-approach/\">obesity</a> in the recent years. Inactively, smoking and poor <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/01/27/would-you-take-this-pill/\">nutrition</a> are responsible for 70% of all chronic diseases. Chronic diseases are responsible for 84% of all healthcare costs.\r\n\r\nHere is one more: <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/04/24/the-more-it-costs-the-more-you-save/\">\"Employers in 2010 spent an average of $10,387 per employee on health care.\"</a>\r\n\r\n\"All companies are focused on cost - cost containment, cost reduction, cost-sharing, and cost avoidance.\" And this, <strong>\"The largest cost to businesses is the soaring rate of health insurance premiums.\"</strong>\r\n\r\nThe article gives details on all of that and mentions some of the important features in common among corporate wellness Best Practices. Here they are: (1) strong leadership support, (2) environments that support healthy behaviors, (3) behavior-change programs (screens, risk assessments, etc.), (4) participation incentive programs, and (5) good evaluations. \"The goal of corporate wellness programs is to maximize employee satisfaction and engagement, while managing costs associated with health plans, worker's compensation, productivity, etc.\" These are important!\r\n\r\n<strong>Return On Investment</strong>\r\n\r\nThey mention the studies done on workplace wellness programs and the savings of $3.27 in medical costs and an average savings of $2.73 in absenteeism for every dollar spent. Then they quote an expert who claims that a 2:1 ROI is more realistic. It is also mentioned that these savings can take three years to realize.\r\n\r\n<strong>Value Of The Investment</strong>\r\n\r\n\"Employers are realizing that it's not just about getting your employees to not be sick.\" Here is what else might have value to the progressive company: (1) creating a culture of health, (2) being viewed as caring about employees, (3) providing competitive and/or exceptional benefits to attract the best employees, (4) increasing employee satisfaction and retention, (5) having higher employee morale, (6) improving productivity, (7) motivating employees to think that they are part of a higher purpose, not just \"cogs in a wheel\" but rather people who contribute individually and are important, (8) being recognized as one of the healthiest companies in the community.\r\n\r\nIn the context of a workplace wellness program it is important to know what you hope to achieve. It helps if you can measure it somehow (you can). And it helps if the outcome hoped for, achieved and measured is <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2011/12/15/1-treatment-for-back-pain/\">one that makes a difference</a>.* Or as Seth Goddin said on his blog this morning, \"A useful metric is both accurate (in that it measures what it says it measures) and aligned with your goals.\"\r\n\r\n<strong>\"It's The Wild West...\"</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter mentioning that three years, \"does not align with the way most organizations track financial outcomes...\" they talk about the lack of industry-wide performance standards, even going so far as to say that \"some vendors make promises that they can not keep.\" (It's<a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/05/03/bad-apples/\"> buyer beware in health care</a>, so it really does matter who you listen to.)\r\n\r\nWorkplace wellness programs are an opportunity to put <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/01/01/corporate-wellness-through-tai-chi/\">great solutions</a>* way upstream of many very serious problems and make a real difference in the company's bottom line as well as in people's lives. this is especially true nowadays when many employees are doing the work of two people. Companies are in a tough spot though. They know that they need something. The money is already going mostly to the medical industrial complex (think status quo). And the people at the company who would be thinking about all of this are already overworked themselves. Companies have to be very careful of <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/04/25/workplace-wellness-solutions-things-to-consider/\">compliance and employee-employer relations issues</a>. It isn't an easy conversation because for most people within the company and most people claiming to be experts it's kind of a new conversation, and the experts are \"selling\" with slick marketing; the buyers are hard pressed to clearly justify what they are buying. And as noted in the <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/05/02/safety-training-follow-through-bending-lifting/\">post on the follow up to most safety training initiatives</a>, the outcomes can be vague and not very meaningful.\r\n\r\nIt is an important and worthwhile conversation though. <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/01/01/corporate-wellness-through-tai-chi/\">It doesn't have to be as complicated as it is being made out to be.</a> The article in Fitness Journal comes with more than a dozen links and a whole new industry of people offering to sell other people on how to be experts on how to sell corporate wellness programs to companies. I invite you to take a look at some simple solutions that any company can implement to reduce risk and save money - see \"Corporate Wellness\" in the <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2011/08/13/index-of-chiropractic-tai-chi-and-other-wellness-posts/\">Index of Blog Posts</a>.", "categories": ["Be careful who you listen to!", "Workplace Wellness"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-06 19:56:23", "language": "en", "author": "109020", "url": "http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/?p=2274", "title": "Tai Chi Study In Fitness Journal", "blog": "109912", "post_id": "63315", "tags": ["Everett WA", "Research", "tai chi", "Tai Chi Chuan", "workplace wellness"], "blogname": "Everett Chiropractic Center Blog", "date": "2012-05-06 19:56:23", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.doctordilday.com\"><img class=\"alignleft size-medium wp-image-2279\" title=\"Tai-ChiWinterQuarter2\" src=\"http://doctordilday.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/tai-chiwinterquarter2.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\r\n\r\nLike almost every other issue of the <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2012/05/06/the-rise-of-workplace-wellness/\">Fitness Journal</a>, the current issue has a mention of research studying the benefits of Tai chi. Published in the Journal of Evidence-Based Complementary &amp; Alternative Medicine, this study found that Tai chi provides mental and emotional benefits, in addition to the very long list of physiological benefits (See \"Tai Chi\" in the <a href=\"http://doctordilday.wordpress.com/2011/08/13/index-of-chiropractic-tai-chi-and-other-wellness-posts/\">Index of Blog Posts</a>.).\r\n\r\nIt also noted that these benefits are found across the spectrum from children, teens, healthy young adults, healthy adults, the elderly, and adults with chronic diseases. (Note: remember from yesterday's Post that \"Chronic diseases are responsible for 84% of all healthcare costs\" if that is of interest.)\r\n\r\nI would also add that Tai chi is ideal for people going through the phases of Relief, Rehabilitation, and Recovery from many types of musculoskeletal injuries (think back or neck for example).\r\n\r\nBasically, if you can walk and you can stand on one leg, you can do Tai chi and benefit.", "categories": ["Back pain", "Breath work", "Energywork", "Exercise", "General Health &amp; Wellness", "Meditation", "Sustainability", "Tai Chi Chuan", "Wellness care", "Workplace Wellness"], "likes": []}
