{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 17:10:38", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19141", "title": "Big Field", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1438666", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-04-30 11:10:38", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/tattoos-could-lead-to-id-of-body-found-in-east/article_3eea946e-9245-11e1-81d2-0019bb30f31a.html\">P-D</a>:\r\n<blockquote>EAST ST. LOUIS \u2022 East St. Louis police hope tattoos will help identify a woman whose body was found early today in the 1300 block of North 39th Street.\r\n\r\nThe tattoos include \"Princess\" on the back of her neck, plus \"Love\" and \"Pain\" on her chest. In addition, the number \"4\" is on the back of her right hand and \"NeNe\" is across the top of her right foot.\r\n\r\nPolice say the woman had no identification when her body was discovered along the street shortly before 1 a.m. Anyone with information is asked to call East St. Louis police.</blockquote>\r\nTats on a black woman that read, \"Princess,\" \"Love,\" \"Pain,\" and \"NeNe.\"\r\n\r\nIn related news, an old person in Florida is missing.", "categories": ["Black Crime", "Illinois &#038; Metro East"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 17:11:27", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19143", "title": "Do-Gooder Does Bad", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "267142", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-04-30 11:11:27", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/poster-child-missing-children-headed-prison-raping-10-year-old-girl-article-1.1069453\">The family history could have predicted it.</a>\r\n\r\nI have an automatic suspicion of adult men who are too interested in the cause of missing/runaway/exploited children.\u00a0 Either they want to get their hands in the cookie jar, metaphorically speaking, or they're overcompensating for guilt for having their hands in said jar, or having fetishes and fantasies in that direction.", "categories": ["Uncategorized"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 02:22:04", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19147", "title": "Let's Get This Party Started", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1574971", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-04-30 20:22:04", "content": "Even though we're still more than three months from Primary day, the conga line of candidate mailings has already started.\r\n\r\nHere's a sample collected from my sources.\u00a0 As usual, click to enlarge to full size:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/boydletter.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19148\" title=\"boydletter\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/boydletter.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"702\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/boydcard-front.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19149\" title=\"boydcard-front\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/boydcard-front.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"720\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/boydcard-back.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19150\" title=\"boydcard-back\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/boydcard-back.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"769\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis was sent to someone I know who lives in Southwest City and voted in the Republican Primary for President in February (he wrote in Newt Gingrich, btw).\u00a0 Boyd seems to bemoan that there were only some 12,000 city voters that voted in that primary.\u00a0 The genius must not realize that the turnout was bound to be low for two reasons:\u00a0 The Democrat Primary was uncontested (Obama only), so there was no incentive for Democrats to turn out, and it was known well in advance that this was a useless beauty contest that didn't factor into delegate apportionment on the Republican side, (thank you, anal-retentive RNC), and on top of that, one of the major remaining contestants at the time of the vote (Gingrich) didn't even make the ballot, so Republican turnout would have been lethargic, and on top of that, there aren't many Republicans in the City anyway (hint:\u00a0 83% Obama in November 2008).\r\n\r\nSo this genius, running for City Treasurer because Larry Williams is finally stepping down, thinks he can get votes by sending people who were die hard Republican enough to vote in the useless Republican Primary in a Democrat city this literature of him reading a David Plouffe book (Obama adviser), and an Obama poster over his head, and a laudatory quote from the <em>Riverfront Times</em>.\u00a0 That'll go over like a lead balloon.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/cummings-front.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19151\" title=\"cummings-front\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/cummings-front.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"360\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/cummings-back.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19152\" title=\"cummings-back\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/cummings-back.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"365\" /></a>\r\n\r\nHe's for \"education.\"\u00a0 Now there's a bold, courageous stand.\u00a0 He would be a Freshman Democrat from an urban area in a legislative body that will very likely remain heavily Republican, so don't look for the City to become one big WiFi hotspot any time soon.\u00a0 And WTF is \"vertical urban farming?\"\r\n\r\nThe odd part about this is that he's running in the new H-78, which runs from Hyde Park down to Old North Side into Downtown then into Soulard, Benton Park and parts of Dutchtown.\u00a0 Save Soulard and Benton Park, that district will be heavily black, so I expect someone of Mr. Cummings's complexion to win it even if he doesn't.\u00a0 The person who received this lives in what will be H-81, which borders H-78 to the south.\u00a0 And this person doesn't live in H-81 on the boundary of H-78, where it would have been understandable for the Cummings campaign to send this mailer outside the district, he lives far south in H-81, almost into the soon-to-be district south of that!\r\n\r\nNotice the QR codes on both Cummings's and Boyd's mailings.\u00a0 I was wondering when QR codes would become commonplace on campaign literature.\u00a0 I guess smartphones weren't quite ubiquitous enough two years ago to justify them.\u00a0 I fully expect most mailings, handbills and yard signs to have them.\r\n\r\nThe best part of having the suffix \"III\" next to your surname is that you know precisely for sure who your father and grandfather are.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-1.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19153\" title=\"rcarnahan-1\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"275\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-2.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19154\" title=\"rcarnahan-2\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"275\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-3.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19155\" title=\"rcarnahan-3\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"282\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-4.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19156\" title=\"rcarnahan-4\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/rcarnahan-4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"277\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThis is campaign literature from Russ Carnahan disguised as franking.\u00a0 How can I tell?\u00a0 First, the third image.\u00a0 Second, the fact that only his South City constituents have gotten this mailing -- AFAIK, nobody I know who lives in South County or Jefferson County who would get this as they have gotten Carnahan and Gephardt frankings in the past have received this one.\u00a0 This is designed for his primary run against Lazy Clay in the new CD-1, pandering to blacks who live in South City and who happen to be his constituents for the current Congress.", "categories": ["Campaign 2012", "St. Louis Local"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 12:39:57", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19161", "title": "I Was Only Half Right", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "335938", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 06:39:57", "content": "<a href=\"http://countenance.wordpress.com/2012/04/07/the-world-didnt-end/\">Me, April 7</a>:\r\n<blockquote>Yes, I know, it\u2019s too early.\u00a0 But on May 1, when we\u2019re in first place, and Mr. Universe is hitting .260-something with 4 HRs and 15 RBI in the month of April, then you\u2019ll know the world didn\u2019t end when he left town.</blockquote>\r\nHow could I get it so wrong?\u00a0 .217, 0 HR, 4 RBI.", "categories": ["Athletics and Sports"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 16:40:52", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19163", "title": "Uh Oh", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1201554", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 10:40:52", "content": "Steelman already has buys during Rush Limbaugh breaks on KMOX.\r\n\r\nIf she runs well enough in St. Louis and St. Charles Counties to where she finishes close to my guy, Todd Akin, but doesn't win those two counties, it's all over.", "categories": ["Campaign 2012", "Missouri", "St. Louis Local", "Talk Radio"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 18:36:16", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19176", "title": "Who Said This?", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1496135", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 12:36:16", "content": "Guess the speaker:\r\n<blockquote>1) Adherence to a religion must be a personal choice;\r\n\r\n2) no religion should demand that those who leave it be killed;\r\n\r\n3) a religion must never mandate the subjugation of those who do not belong to it;\r\n\r\n4) a religion must be in accord with basic human rights.</blockquote>\r\nWas it:\r\n\r\nA.\u00a0 Someone with the ACLU\r\n\r\nB.\u00a0 Someone with People United for the Separation of Church and State\r\n\r\nC.\u00a0 Someone with the ADL\r\n\r\nD.\u00a0 Someone with the SPLC\r\n\r\nE.\u00a0 None of the Above\r\n\r\nThe answer?\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.vdare.com/posts/geert-wilders-visits-new-york-city-with-new-book\">E.\u00a0 None of the Above.</a>", "categories": ["Religion"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 21:01:47", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19182", "title": "Some Good Breaking News (For a Change)", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "259097", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 15:01:47", "content": "A state circuit judge in St. Louis County has ruled for Clayton in <em>Turner vs Clayton</em>.\u00a0 Meaning no vicarious deseg for the time being.\r\n\r\nThe basis of his ruling was the Hancock Amendment -- Clayton et al. argued that allowing these transfers without requisite additional state funding would have amounted to <em>de facto</em> tax increases on their districts' property tax bases.\u00a0 And the judge bought it.\u00a0 Here's hoping the Appellate Courts and the State Supreme Court buy it.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;", "categories": ["Courts &#038; Judiciary", "Desegregation in Schools", "St. Louis Local"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 22:54:19", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19188", "title": "Dime Store Indian", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1888511", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 16:54:19", "content": "<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/elizabeth-warren.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19189\" title=\"elizabeth-warren\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/elizabeth-warren.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"160\" height=\"213\" /></a>\r\n\r\nShe used her 1/5448455315184112329045th Indian ancestry <a href=\"http://althouse.blogspot.com/2012/05/nyt-reports-that-officials-involved-in.html\">to get on the Harvard Law faculty.</a>\u00a0 A distant ancestor was Chief of the Slapahoes, probably.\r\n\r\nMany white Americans, especially in the South, have some Indian ancestry, because when their great-great......-great grandfathers went exploring, they didn't bring any women, and when it came time for that, they did it with Indian women.\u00a0 And the nine month later inevitable results were assimilated into white society.\r\n\r\nAs an aside, this explains why I'm for Todd Akin...I want him to win the Primary and defeat Claire McCaskill in November, because this is the John Danforth seat.", "categories": ["Affirmative Action", "Campaign 2012"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:42:01", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19194", "title": "Out of Touch", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1962015", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 17:42:01", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.mediabistro.com/fishbowldc/starbucks-faces-the-wrath-of-mark-knoller_b72233\">Media Bistro</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Starbucks Faces Wrath of White House Reporter</strong>\r\n\r\nCBS Radio White House Correspondent Mark Knoller has become legendary for his rants on Twitter. Today, he is having a hard time with his local Starbucks. On his way into the White House, Knoller stopped off for breakfast and tried to use a 50 dollar bill (must be nice) to pay for his breakfast, which was less than 10 dollars. When they explained they don\u2019t take bills as large as $50, he took to Twitter and did what any normal person would do \u2014 he wrote the Secretary of Treasury...</blockquote>\r\nWho whips out a L-note to pay for a breakfast\u00a0that costs him \"less than\" (but probably close to) ten bucks at the generic coffee house whose logo contains the visage of a suggestively naked long-haired white woman?\u00a0 A one-percenter, that's who.\u00a0 I guess it's time for Occupy CBS Radio.\r\n\r\nMark Knoller knows that people out there are struggling and hurting...because someone told him.\r\n\r\nMeanwhile, the prorated unit cost of what I typically eat for breakfast is probably no more than a buck and a half.\u00a0 Coffee, with milk and sweetener, a cup of OJ, a cup of AJ, a cup of GJ, a cup of plum juice, and a bowl of my mixola concoction of cereal -- Total, Wheaties and Crispix mixed into a huge container and consumed one bowl at a time.\u00a0 That's pretty much been my culinary routine most mornings since the seventh grade.\u00a0 Yes, that includes the coffee.\r\n\r\nI don't like to give myself away on this medium, but if you see someone in a Schnucks or Shop-N-Save along or close to Manslaughter Road in West County with one box each of Total, Wheaties and Crispix in his cart, it's probably your blogmeister.\u00a0 I'm probably the only person on Earth who likes the taste of Total, but I should say that their experiment with corn flakes absolutely sucked.", "categories": ["Mainstream Media", "Personal"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:01:00", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19165", "title": "Schizophrenic Court of the United States", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "825117", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 18:01:00", "content": "<a href=\"http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2012/04/supreme-court-rejects-bid-to-shield-sheriff-lee-baca-from-lawsuit.html\">LAT</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Supreme Court rejects bid to shield Sheriff Lee Baca from lawsuit</strong>\r\n\r\nThe U.S. Supreme Court refused Monday to shield Los Angeles County Sheriff Lee Baca from being sued for racial gang violence in the jails he supervises.\r\n\r\nThe justices without comment turned down an appeal from the county\u2019s lawyers, who argued Baca cannot be held personally liable for the stabbing of an inmate since he had no personal involvement in the incident.\r\n\r\nInstead, the court let stand a decision of the U.S. 9th Circuit Court of Appeals, which said Baca can be sued for \u201cdeliberate indifference\u201d to the inmate\u2019s rights since he was on notice of the jailhouse violence and failed to take action to stop it.</blockquote>\r\nI'm hardly a Lee Baca fan, but now he's stuck between a rock and a hard place, with SCOTUS on both sides.\u00a0 If he doesn't prevent racial violence in the hoosegows, SCOTUS says that the victims can sue him.\u00a0 If he does prevent the violence, SCOTUS will tell him that segregating inmates based on race is unconstitutional.", "categories": ["Courts &#038; Judiciary"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:02:28", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19167", "title": "Big Sky Cover Up", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1408714", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 18:02:28", "content": "<a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/justice-department-probes-university-montana-student-rape-reports-031102558--spt.html\">Reuters</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Justice Department probes University of Montana student rape reports</strong>\r\n\r\n(Reuters) - The U.S. Justice Department has opened an investigation into the handling of numerous sexual assault allegations involving students at the University of Montana, where at least two members of the football team are accused of rape.\r\n\r\nUniversity President Royce Engstrom told Reuters he was informed of the inquiry during a meeting on Monday with Justice Department officials who told him the probe would examine the response of the Missoula-based university, city police and county prosecutors.\r\n\r\nA spate of alleged rapes, the implication of student athletes in some of them, and the abrupt dismissal last month of the football coach and athletic director has shaken the campus and battered the image of a school celebrated for its Big Sky Conference champion football team, the Montana Grizzlies.\r\n\r\n(snip)\r\n\r\nCriminal charges have been filed so far in just one case under scrutiny -- against Grizzlies' running back Beau Donaldson, who is accused of raping a woman at his residence while she slept following a night of heavy drinking.</blockquote>\r\nWhy the cover-up?\u00a0 The probable answer is ironic, considering who is opening a probe.\r\n\r\nAnswer:\u00a0 Black + Football.\r\n\r\nConveniently, the only player facing formal criminal charges so far is white.\r\n\r\nThis is why I've been saying that football, everything from the NFL down to Pee Wee League, needs to take a season off, while we do a collective catharsis of all the crimes that we have tolerated in the name of football, and to deny the figurative drug to our numerous drug addicts.\r\n\r\nOn top of that, deep down in the noise floor in the hoopla about the non-existent contrived \"war on women,\" we have found out about all the covered up rapes on college campuses.\u00a0 Again, it's either black, football/basketball, and usually both.\u00a0 The professional feminists are too scared to talk about race, though.", "categories": ["Athletics and Sports", "Black Crime"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:03:03", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19170", "title": "RIP, Nick", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1355003", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 18:03:03", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.euronews.com/2012/05/01/le-pen-dodges-chance-to-endorse-sarkozy\">Payback's a beyotch, isn't it?</a>\r\n\r\nMLP's refusal to endorse Sarkozy (or Hollande) is in essence a political death sentence for Sarkozy.\u00a0 Plus, I think she's being Machiavellian here:\u00a0 She probably thinks that if Sarkozy goes down, his party stands a chance of disappearing from public life, setting up the FN as the only real conservative party in the French body politic.\u00a0 Turning that trick against the socialists would be much harder, as there is an automatic no-matter-what come hell or high water built in constituency for any socialist center-left party, in its black and Muslim voters.", "categories": ["France"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:04:54", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19172", "title": "Tuesday Wrap-Up", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "50686", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 18:04:54", "content": "<strong>LOCAL AND REGIONAL</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/webster-groves-students-form-club-to-celebrate-don-knotts-work/article_1a0fbbbc-c518-5f4c-84f6-9cda00033c16.html\">The people happiest to read these news are in Kirkwood.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/st-louis-hospital-alerts-police-after-teen-shows-up-with/article_67d0088a-9332-11e1-beff-0019bb30f31a.html\">Of course the hospital called the cops</a>.\u00a0 It's a relatively unknown Federal law for an ER to do so, when someone presents with a gunshot wound.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.ksdk.com/news/article/318299/3/Local-Occupy-protesters-gather-outside-Peabody-Opera-House\">Local Occutards used May Day to protest Peabody Coal, for the paucity of income taxes they pay</a>.\u00a0 I am not aware of them being upset at GE and AAPL.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 You get one guess to why the <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/rams-plan-for-dome-delivered-to-st-louis-agency/article_5a1b946c-9340-11e1-998c-0019bb30f31a.html\">Rams' plans to the CVC to renovate the Edward Jones Dome are sealed</a>.\u00a0 If you need more than one guess, then I hereby revoke your oxygen consumption privileges.\r\n\r\n<strong>NATIONAL</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/rubio-says-gop-credit-card-looked-bad-082337720.html\">Yes, it \"looked bad,\"</a> but at least HE didn't let company credit cards be used by black subordinates at a lesbian bondage boobie bar...cough cough...Michael Steele...cough cough.\r\n\r\nWhat's grinding me about Rubio is that Alex Jones has an article today that has Rubio going to Treasonstock (Bildeberger) at the end of this month.\u00a0 Now, this is Alex Jones, so I'll have to corroborate that with another source before I actually whole hog believe it.\u00a0 But if Rubio does, that is one shark he will never be able to un-jump.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.nytimes.com/2012/04/29/opinion/sunday/terrorist-plots-helped-along-by-the-fbi.html?_r=1\">That's what most \"terrorist plots\" are these days, a result of sting operations</a>.\u00a0 When the matter gets to court, the thorny issue is if the infiltrator became a provocateur, whether he was just listening or actually planning.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Speaking of sting operations.\u00a0 <a href=\"http://dailycaller.com/2012/05/01/occupiers-try-to-blow-up-a-bridge-near-cleveland/\">Yeah, sure, they're just like the Tea Parties</a>.\u00a0 I get the feeling that the case against these Occutards is real, because all the U.S. Attorneys who will be prosecuting this case work under the Occutard-In-Chief.\u00a0 But there might be the possibility that this is all a result of overzealous infiltrators.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.lvrj.com/news/suspect-arrested-in-double-slaying-sexual-assaults-149274255.html\">Man arrested in \"savage\" double beating -- Guess the race.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 She got results in Cleveland and Detroit.\u00a0 What that means is that she either ordered cheating, countenanced it, or was a willing beneficiary of it.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.suntimes.com/12238690-417/cps-names-interim-chief-education-officer.html\">Therefore, Chicago would hire her.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Have you ever heard of a county government that wants its county to go out of existence?\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/politics/clout/chi-preckwinkle-wants-to-eliminate-unincorporated-areas-in-cook-county-20120430,0,7781750.story\">Yeah, Cook County, Illinois</a>.\u00a0 I couldn't believe it, either.\r\n\r\nSt. Louis County was actually fearful of this sort of thing, that the entire county would be part of an incorporated municipality that it would essentially cease to exist.\u00a0 Those fears stopped in the mid-1990s when the attempt to incorporate all of heretofore unincorporated South County into Southpointe went down in flames.\u00a0 And since St. George is now no longer in existence, the trend seems to be going in the other direction.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 They say he ripped it off from MSNBC, <a href=\"http://www.washingtontimes.com/blog/inside-politics/2012/apr/30/new-obama-slogan-has-long-ties-marxism-socialism/\">but he really got it from Marx</a>.\u00a0 Which means MSNBC stole it from Marx.\r\n\r\nRemember a few months ago when the Generic Republican took some heat for saying something about \"America for Americans,\" which was supposed to be too much like a Klan mantra?\r\n\r\n<strong>MISC</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-2137214/Rihanna-set-star-Fast-And-The-Furious-6-sultry-villain.html\">This is why I've been advising people to call that operation \"Gunrunner.\"</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 How repulsive is Dan Savage?\u00a0 (Not to be confused with Michael Savage)\u00a0 PEREZ HILTON (not to be confused with Paris Hilton) <a href=\"http://www.breitbart.com/Big-Hollywood/2012/04/30/Perez-Hilton-Dan-Savage\">has come out against him.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 What was their first clue?\u00a0 <a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/police-tap-teen-theft-chefs-lamborghini-004153521.html\">That a 17-year old was driving a Lamborghini</a>.\u00a0 There's no 17-year old who can afford what insuring a 17-year old driving a Lamborghini would cost, much less the note, taxes, gas, maintenance.", "categories": ["Uncategorized"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:05:30", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19174", "title": "Fun With Tuesday Headlines", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "114964", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 18:05:30", "content": "<strong>Breitbart:\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.breitbart.com/Big-Hollywood/2012/04/28/levinea\">Adam Levine Threatens To 'Lose My Sh*t' If Obama Not Re-Elected</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThat alone is worth the price of voting for the Generic Republican, as long as I have a front row seat to the event.\r\n\r\n<strong>AP:\u00a0 <a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/mariah-carey-nick-cannon-renew-wedding-vows-010753605.html\">Mariah Carey and Nick Cannon renew wedding vows</a></strong>\r\n\r\nI didn't even know they were married.\u00a0 When was the last time either one of them did anything professionally noteworthy?\r\n\r\n<strong>Reuters:\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/04/30/tagblogsfindlawcom2012-freeenterprise-idUS298626847220120430\">FL Motel Goes All-Nude to Boost Bottom Line</a></strong>\r\n\r\nProblem:\u00a0 The kind of people who will use this motel really need boosts in their own bottom lines.\r\n\r\n<strong>AP:\u00a0 <a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/brennan-describes-us-chooses-drone-targets-210647817.html\">Brennan describes how US chooses drone targets</a></strong>\r\n\r\nCheck with the ADL and SPLC.\u00a0 <a href=\"http://lewrockwell.com/grigg/grigg-w239.html\">I'm not kidding.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Yahoo:\u00a0 <a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/ann-mitt-romney-theres-wild-crazy-man-124652100--abc-news-politics.html\">Ann on Mitt Romney - 'There's a Wild and Crazy Man in There'</a></strong>\r\n\r\nYeah, I know.\u00a0 He once went right through that stop sign like it wasn't there.\u00a0 (Yes, the #RebelRomney hashtag on Twitter has already been done)\r\n\r\n<strong>The Blaze:\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.theblaze.com/stories/serving-the-synagogue-of-satan-farrakhan-says-joining-u-s-military-is-fighting-for-the-enemy/\">Farakhan Says Joining Army Is Fighting 'for the Enemy'</a></strong>\r\n\r\nThere is a part of me which hopes that a lot of black Americans believe this.", "categories": ["Fun With Headlines"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:09:04", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19184", "title": "But IQ Doesn't Exist", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1522852", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 18:09:04", "content": "<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/harold-ford.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19185\" title=\"harold-ford\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/harold-ford.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"325\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/man-gets-life-for-carjacking-woman-shooting-st-louis-cop/article_922048f4-92ef-11e1-a394-001a4bcf6878.html\">P-D</a>:\r\n<blockquote>His public defender, Felicia Jones, asked for less than 37 years, citing his lower-than-average intelligence, the physical and emotional abuse that he suffered at the hands of his father at an early age and the resulting Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder.</blockquote>\r\nDon't take this logic too far, otherwise <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Bell-Curve-Intelligence-Structure-Paperbacks/dp/0684824299/\">people will be getting ideas.</a>\r\n\r\nIn case you were wondering, he got life in Federal prison.\u00a0 He's 46 now, just got out of the state pen for doing 18 of a 20 bid for another carjacking, and even if he only got 37 years, the Federal truth-in-sentencing law is five-sixths, so he wouldn't have gotten out until age 76.\u00a0 Odds are he would have died before that.\u00a0 He would have gotten life either way, and has been doing life on the installment plan.\u00a0 I don't take Miss Jones as the brightest bulb in the box.\r\n\r\nPTSD is what his victims are suffering.", "categories": ["Black Crime", "St. Louis Local"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 02:41:57", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19199", "title": "Everybody Forgot 1993", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1069274", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-01 20:41:57", "content": "Back then, labor unions opposed NAFTA.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.steinreport.com/archives/seiu_files_nafta_complaint_against_alabama.html\">Dan Stein</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>SEIU Files NAFTA Complaint Against Alabama</strong>\r\n\r\n\"The Service Employees International Union continued its fight against Alabama immigration law HB 56 on Monday by filing a complaint with the Mexican Department of Labor, calling the law discriminatory and in violation of the North American Free Trade Agreement,\" the Huffington Post writes. \"SEIU coupled with the Mexican National Association of Democratic Lawyers in issuing the complaint, which says HB 56 violates NAFTA's North American Agreement on Labor Cooperation.\"</blockquote>\r\nAnd now, labor unions are using something which they once opposed to oppose measures in the best interest of their members.\r\n\r\nExcept I think the SEIU has been bought off by the cheap labor lobby to drive down wages.\u00a0 That, and <a href=\"http://countenance.wordpress.com/2011/12/01/does-this-read-like-the-biography-of-a-labor-union-leader/\">the biography of the head of the SEIU reads more like a corporate CEO than a union leader.</a>", "categories": ["Foreign Trade", "Immigration", "Organized Labor"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 13:10:29", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19202", "title": "A Pair of George Zimmerman Community Award Winners", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1878073", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 07:10:29", "content": "Just to give credit where credit is due, I'll have to name that award the Rev. Jed DeValleyism George Zimmerman Community Award.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Two grannies, perhaps great-grannies, versus \"Sergio Fernando Solorzano-Vasquez.\"\u00a0 I won't give it away, <a href=\"http://www.myfoxny.com/story/18021569/elderly-sisters-fight-off-carjacker http://countenance.wordpress.com/2012/05/01/but-iq-doesnt-exist/\">but the grannies won.</a>\r\n\r\nThe grannies don't hold any hostility toward their assailant, but \"hope they never see him again.\"\u00a0 I don't think that's much of a problem, as Mr. Solorzano-Vasquez is on the same track as <a href=\"http://countenance.wordpress.com/2012/05/01/but-iq-doesnt-exist/\">this genius.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.wsfa.com/story/17997141/13-year-old-suspect-killed-during-robbery\">Somewhere in Birmingham</a>, a middle school football team will be without its quarterback this coming season.\u00a0 So sad, cue violins.\u00a0 Makes you wonder just how he fell in with the wrong crowd.\r\n\r\nFear not, we'll eventually find out that he was just out on a Skittles run.", "categories": ["Black Crime", "Hispanic Crime"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 16:29:57", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19204", "title": "Silence in a Pill", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "714507", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 10:29:57", "content": "5:\r\n<blockquote><a href=\"http://www.ksdk.com/news/world/article/318383/28/High-school-teacher-accused-of-giving-student-Xanax\"><strong>Adam Jones accused of giving student Xanax</strong></a>\r\n\r\nCouncil Bluffs, IA (KPTM/CNN) - A high school teacher in Iowa is accused of giving a student the prescription drug Xanax.\r\n\r\nAdam Jones, 40, of Council Bluffs was arrested on Friday.\r\n\r\nStudents at Thomas Jefferson High School say they can't believe one of their favorite teachers is being charged for giving drugs to a student.\r\n\r\n\"I didn't think that actually happened, I just thought it was some rumor going around,\" said student Rachel Autera.\r\n\r\nInvestigators say they believe Adam Jones offered the prescription drug Xanax to one of his students, who in turn accepted several of the pills. It's a prescription drug that helps people with anxiety, but can be taken illegally to feel relaxed.</blockquote>\r\nHow dare a teacher give one of his students Xanax to keep her quiet.\u00a0 That's what Ritalin is for.", "categories": ["Education", "Health Care"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 16:32:09", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19206", "title": "For All to See", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "649292", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 10:32:09", "content": "<a href=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/dania-suarez.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19207\" title=\"dania-suarez\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/dania-suarez.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"286\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/news/world/colombian-hooker-dania-suarez-pose-nude-article-1.1070529\">She's going to show us the assets that were heretofore only for the purview of Secret Service agents.</a>\r\n\r\nI don't think I'll bother.\u00a0 I think I can infer her financial statements with just her cash flow reports, if you grok the metaphor.", "categories": ["Uncategorized"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 16:33:40", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19209", "title": "Price Hike", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "282286", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 10:33:40", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/opinions/opinion/quebecs-university-students-are-in-for-a-shock/article2418431/\"><em>Canada Gay and Male</em></a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Quebec\u2019s university students are in for a shock</strong>\r\n\r\nIt\u2019s a little hard for the rest of us to muster sympathy for Quebec\u2019s downtrodden students, who pay the lowest tuition fees in all of North America. Even if the government has its way \u2013 no sure thing if the Parti Qu\u00e9b\u00e9cois gets back in power \u2013 they\u2019ll still have the lowest tuition fees in North America. The total increase would amount to the cost of a daily grande cappuccino.</blockquote>\r\nExcept a grande cappuccino at any coffee house in Montreal, including the generic one whose logo contains the visage of a suggestively naked long-haired white woman, isn't cheap.\u00a0 When you throw in the required taxes in Canada, the social justice tax, the global warming tax, the refugee resettlement support tax, the anti-hate tax, the AIDS treatment tax, and the self-esteem tax, that cup of grande cappuccino is an expensive proposition.\u00a0 One of those every day for a year adds up to real money.", "categories": ["Canada", "Education"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 16:34:38", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19211", "title": "Just What American Society Needs", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1966831", "tags": ["Racism Schmacism"], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 10:34:38", "content": "Yet another form of \"racism\" to fret about.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/la-na-nn-hipster-racism-20120501,0,6134047.story\">C-Trib</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Trayvon Martin, Kony 2012, L.A. riots -- and now 'hipster racism'</strong>\r\n\r\nThe Trayvon Martin case, the\"Kony 2012\" phenomenon, the L.A. riots anniversary.... The conversation about race in America never went away. Now a new discussion about so-called hipster racism has brought the talk to the millennials, and it's gotten a little awkward.\r\n\r\nAmong the questions: Is hipster racism real? Is it any different from more traditional racism? Or is all this talk just the byproduct of a generation that barely remembers Rodney King and O.J. Simpson and has no idea how to talk about race?\r\n\r\n\"When did acknowledging that other cultures are different than yours become racism?\" Kellen Powell wrote at Street Carnage on Monday, home to some of the most contentious criticism happening over the last couple weeks on edgier millennial-aimed outlets. Powell added, \"I\u2019m from Vancouver BC, where we don\u2019t have black people.\"</blockquote>\r\nLucky you.\r\n\r\nThis \"hipster racism\" bullshit seems to be nothing more than young SWPLs manifesting their hatred of their working class racial brethren by throwing themselves into a climate of faux diversity.\r\n\r\nI'll modify RJP's axiom just a little bit:\u00a0 Just about everyone under 30 is useless.", "categories": ["Uncategorized"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 17:21:39", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19213", "title": "Composite Flames", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1915103", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 11:21:39", "content": "\"Composite\" -- A fancy way of saying \"fiction.\"\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2012/05/obama-ny-girlfriend-was-composite-character-122272.html\">Politico</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Obama: 'New York girlfriend' was composite</strong>\r\n\r\nOne of the more mysterious characters from President Obama's 1995 autobiography Dreams From My Father is the so-called 'New York girlfriend.' Obama never referred to her by name, or even by psuedonym, but he describes her appearance, her voice, and her mannerisms in specific detail.\r\n\r\nBut Obama has now told biographer David Maraniss that the 'New York girlfriend' was actually a composite character, based off of multiple girlfriends he had both in New York City and in Chicago.</blockquote>\r\nFunny, we've never heard from any of these alleged \"girlfriends.\"\u00a0 You would think that any ex of the sitting President would want to parlay that into her fifteen minutes of fame.\r\n\r\nI think someone will fill in the blanks below in the comment section.", "categories": ["Uncategorized"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 19:11:23", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19215", "title": "Keeping the Hip-Hop Generation In Check", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1418130", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 13:11:23", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.miamiherald.com/2012/04/28/v-fullstory/2778395/all-eyes-on-miami-beach-this-memorial.html\"><em>Miami Herald</em></a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>All eyes on Miami Beach this Memorial Day weekend</strong>\r\n\r\nTerrance Smith hasn\u2019t had much difficulty selling South Beach as a Memorial Day weekend destination this year. The promoter, who since 2001 has pumped up Miami Beach as the spot to be for several hundred thousand members of what he calls the \u201chip-hop generation,\u201d says bookings for hotel rooms remain as popular as ever \u2014 despite police-involved shootings during the weekend last year.\r\n\r\n(snip)\r\n\r\nLicense plate readers that use multi-angle scanners to record vehicle tags will be placed along the Julia Tuttle and MacArthur causeways to record just about every car that drives into South Beach. Recorded tags will be entered into a database that police will use to find outstanding warrants, cars reported stolen, expired registrations and other potential violations. Vehicles with tags that kick back violations to police will be stopped.</blockquote>\r\nI get the feeling that lot of open warrants and cases will be resolved that weekend.\r\n\r\nThough I don't think they need to look at individual license plates per se -- Just look for the chrome spinners, and the cars whose bodies are inordinately high or low relative to the pavement.\u00a0 There's the dead giveaway.\r\n\r\nAll else fails, the cops can just build a barbed wire fence around South Beach while the revelers are there.\u00a0 If the thugs won't go to prison, bring the prison to the thugs.\r\n\r\nThis article uses the word \"bacchanal\" to describe this merriment.\u00a0 Party Cove is also a bacchanal, but for some odd reason, it's never violent.", "categories": ["Black Crime"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 19:12:59", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19217", "title": "\"Hazing\"", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1147651", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 13:12:59", "content": "<a href=\"http://gma.yahoo.com/famu-hazing-charges-expected-drum-major-robert-champions-135558074--abc-news-topstories.html\">ABC</a>:\r\n<blockquote>Criminal charges are expected to be filed today against members of the Florida A&amp;M University marching band who were involved in the hazing death of drum major Robert Champion last November.\r\n\r\nChampion, 26, was a member of the college's famed \"Marching 100\" band when he collapsed and died Nov. 19 on a bus parked outside an Orlando, Fla., hotel after a football game. The death was ruled a homicide and police said hazing contributed to his death.\r\n\r\n(snip)\r\n\r\nSome band members have said that Champion died after participating in a rite of passage called \"crossing bus C,\" a ritual where new band members are beaten as they walk from the back to the front of the bus.</blockquote>\r\nYou can call it \"hazing\" or a \"rite of passage\" if you want.\u00a0 As for me, I'm going to call it what it is:\u00a0 Gang initiation.\r\n\r\nNot once does the news text mention that Florida A&amp;M is an HBCU.\u00a0 They do give us a vic pic, so I guess the implication that they want us to walk away with, until we do the five seconds of research on Wikipedia to show otherwise, and/or see the mugs of the suspects, is that the doers are white.", "categories": ["Black Crime", "Education"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 20:33:54", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19219", "title": "Now You Know Why I Wanted Out of Town on Doobie Day", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1019205", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-02 14:33:54", "content": "Ensconced out in the middle of nowhere with my eighty-something uncle who disowned his own druggie daughter, <a href=\"http://www.ksdk.com/news/world/article/318506/28/Man-left-in-DEA-holding-cell-for-five-days-describes-ordeal\">there's no way this could have happened to me.</a>\r\n\r\nYes, he's going to get millions.\u00a0 But millions to a government that raises and spends trillions is like pocket change to you and me.\u00a0 This shit is going to keep happening until either the stakes are raised into the multiples of billions, and/or these kinds of lawsuits can result in Federal agents being fired and losing their pensions on court order.\r\n\r\nI wonder where all the bigmouth ACLU and Amnesty International types are on this matter.\u00a0 You know, send observers down to Club Gitmo to see how the terroristical boogie woogies are being \"abused,\" i.e given Ensure, and also the best food they ever ate, and actual health care, to put them in the best health of their otherwise miserable pathetic useless lives.\r\n\r\n<strong>UPDATE</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.boston.com/news/nation/articles/2012/05/03/ca_man_left_in_cell_4_days_just_tried_to_survive/\">The lawyers are suing for $20 million</a>, the Congressman from the area, the son of my preferred Republican candidate in 2008 is getting involved, and the DEA section chief for San Diego is \"deeply troubled.\"\r\n\r\nLame.\r\n\r\n<strong>UPDATE II</strong>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/lanow/2012/05/uc-san-diego-student-dea-jail-outrage.html\">Issa, Boxer now in.</a>\u00a0 Perhaps we're getting somewhere.\u00a0 But I still won't believe it until some DEA people get fired and lose their pensions.", "categories": ["Abuse of Power", "Police &#038; Law Enforcement"], "likes": []}
