{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 15:36:28", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19239", "title": "No Bureaucratic Task Is Too Herculean For the Sake of Civil Rights", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1593439", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 09:36:28", "content": "Back in the old days, when men were men and women were women, coed colleges had two kinds of dorms -- Men went that way, and women went that way.\u00a0 Simple as that.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://cnsnews.com/news/article/dartmouth-dorm-assignments-will-not-be-limited-traditional-gender-binary\">Thank goodness we're beyond that anachronistic thinking.</a>\r\n\r\nThis scheme might be a bureaucratic nightmare to administer, but I'm sure that it will be a labor of love (and at least a high five-figure salary) for all involved.\u00a0 OTOH, not doing so would be tantamount to intolerance.\r\n\r\n(Insert a comment by Miguel about sheep pens in the dorm showers here)", "categories": ["Culture Wars", "Education"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 15:38:36", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19241", "title": "OBL's Last Words", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "508706", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 09:38:36", "content": "\"Occupy the Crusaders.\"\r\n\r\nNaaah, not quite.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://news.yahoo.com/bin-ladens-last-words-online-131109811.html\">AP</a>:\r\n<blockquote>WASHINGTON (AP) \u2014 In letters from his last hideout, Osama bin Laden fretted about dysfunction in his terrorist network and crumbling trust from Muslims he wished to incite against their government and the West.\r\n\r\nA selection of documents seized in last year's raid on bin Laden's Pakistan house was posted online Thursday by the U.S. Army's Combating Terrorism Center. The documents show dark days for al-Qaida and its hunkered-down leader after years of attacks by the United States and what bin Laden saw as bumbling within his own organization and its terrorist allies.\r\n\r\n(snip)\r\n\r\nIt said the personal files showed that, during one of the most significant manhunts in history, bin Laden was out of touch with the day-to-day operations of various terrorist groups inspired by al-Qaida. He was \"not in sync on the operational level with its so-called affiliates,\" researchers wrote. \"Bin Laden enjoyed little control over either groups affiliated with al Qaida in name or so-called fellow travelers.\"</blockquote>\r\nThis is why killing him was more psychological and retributive than substantive.\r\n\r\nMost embarrassing:\r\n<blockquote>Until the end, bin Laden remained focused on attacking Americans and coming up with plots, however improbable, to kill U.S. leaders. He wished especially to target airplanes carrying Gen. David Petraeus and even President Barack Obama, reasoning that an assassination would elevate an \"utterly unprepared\" Vice President Joe Biden into the presidency and plunge the U.S. into crisis.</blockquote>\r\nI wonder how Biden felt after having read that.\u00a0 He ran for President himself in 1988 and 2008, had multiple terms in the Senate, was considered a foreign policy expert (<a href=\"http://countenance.wordpress.com/2008/08/23/the-gravitas-pick-who-wants-to-put-america-into-a-grave/\">even though he was nothing more than a globalist-traitor hack</a>), and yet he had to take a back seat to the well-tanned chatterbox.\u00a0 I'm hardly a Joe Biden fan, but he would be a slight upgrade over the present occupant of 1600 Penna. Ave.\r\n\r\nIn related news, <a href=\"http://cnsnews.com/news/article/wh-official-al-qaeda-morale-low-some-members-giving-going-home\">AQ is on the rocks</a>.\u00a0 Fine as far as that goes.\u00a0 But remember, terrorism is a means to the end for these types, not the end itself.\u00a0 One of the reasons AQ and terrorism in general is becoming passe is because they don't need terrorism to spread Shari'ah Law, when they have Obama, his judicial appointments, his Justice Department and his media minions to do it for them.\r\n\r\nIn more related news, <a href=\"http://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/al-qaeda-calls-massive-forest-fires-montana/story?id=16263981#.T6KgunmQkr5\">the AQ glossy mag \"Terrorism for Dummies\" is back in print</a>, though it's said not to be as \"snarky\" as its previous iteration.\u00a0 I'm glad to know that people are analyzing AQ propaganda for its sarcasm value.\u00a0 Also, they want to set forest fires in Montana, though they might not actually need to light the match -- They can just have their buddies in the Mexican drug cartels do it.", "categories": ["Terrorism"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 15:40:14", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19243", "title": "Felon Swap", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "817912", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 09:40:14", "content": "A lot of people \"convicted of certain C and D felonies\" are really hard core habitual criminals.\u00a0 The guilty plea on the C or D felony was a result of a plea bargain, which probably resulted in an A or B felony charge being wiped away, in exchange for a long term on the C or D felony.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/political-fix/bill-to-trim-missouri-s-prison-population-clears-legislature/article_5a6fc718-9493-11e1-8e41-0019bb30f31a.html\">I hope the people studying this issue took that into consideration.</a>\r\n\r\nI think what the state is up to is that they'll get 'em convicted of the felony, then wait around for them to be caught in possession of a firearm, and then the Yankee government can house 'em for several years.\u00a0 Do their life on the installment plan on the Yankee government's dime.", "categories": ["Missouri"], "likes": []}
