{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 15:43:19", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19248", "title": "Dr. O'Neal", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "1363063", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 09:43:19", "content": "<a href=\"http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/headlines/2012/05/shaquille-oneal-earns-ph-d-in-education/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-19249\" title=\"shaq\" src=\"http://countenance.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/shaq.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"349\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThat's ABC's version.\u00a0 The headline was surely written by someone who doesn't hold a Ph.D. in grammar.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sun-sentinel.com/sports/fl-shaq-barry-university-degree-20120501,0,1675344.story\">Now for a more elucidating version, from the <em>South Florida Sun-Sentinel</em></a>:\r\n<blockquote>Because of O'Neal's hectic schedule in recent years, professors had to fly to him for one-on-one classes, some of which took place in Cincinnati, Orlando, Los Angeles and New York. Kopp said the travel was at O'Neal's expense.\r\n\r\n\"We found it more efficient to go to him,'' said Kopp, who noted that O'Neal also took classes on campus and via video conferencing. These days, the former South Florida resident lives in the Orlando area.</blockquote>\r\nTranslation:\u00a0 This school basically handed him a Ph.D. on a silver platter, because they wanted the publicity.\r\n\r\nAnd I will never consider his Ph.D. in the same league as Sam Francis's Ph.D.", "categories": ["Athletics and Sports", "Education"], "likes": []}
