{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 02:21:34", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19260", "title": "Thursday Wrap-Up", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "568294", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 20:21:34", "content": "<strong>LOCAL AND REGIONAL</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/st-louis-county-modot-swap-responsibilities-for-some-roads/article_631cbbec-32b4-56ba-ba5b-498583c0eac6.html\">MoDOT taking over the Page-Olive Connector, the Maryland Heights Expressway and the Earth City Expressway</a>.\u00a0 This paves the way for it to be commissioned as an extension of MO 141, meaning that designation will constitute a de facto beltway from Arnold to Earth City, with most of it either four or six lane divided.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 I must be getting old, because when I was their age, <a href=\"http://fox2now.com/2012/02/22/man-accused-of-shooting-friend-in-head/\">\"friendship\" didn't constitute shooting someone in the head.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/lemay-area-to-get-million-casino-backed-recreation-center/article_4c9a65d9-a8f1-5e59-984d-cd4236d64d17.html\">Why do I get the feeling that Lemay is eventually going to regret this?</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.ksdk.com/news/world/article/318441/18/Gov-Nixon-endorses-Clay-for-Mo-congressional-bid\">Dear Russ:\u00a0 Give it up.\u00a0 Before you embarrass yourself.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/suburban-journals/metro/news/chicken-legislation-fails-to-cross-road/article_8a8d0793-7c9e-5022-a0e2-51abce876977.html\">No live chickens in my dear ole Ballwin.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/govt-and-politics/illinois-considers-charging-kids-for-riding-school-buses/article_83e67cff-91e6-597d-8829-a51a1cb64fc0.html\">It might soon cost you if your kid rides the school buses in Illinois</a>, and he or she isn't on the free lunch program.\r\n\r\nAdding insult to <a href=\"http://countenance.wordpress.com/2009/09/15/belleville-bus-beating-some-dare-call-it-a-hate-crime/\">hate-fueled injury.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>NATIONAL</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.myfoxhouston.com/dpp/news/local/120419-robbery-suspect-shot?obref=obinsite\">This happened at a Luby's Cafeteria</a>.\u00a0 IIRC, the shooting which resulted in Texas finally getting CCW also happened at a Luby's.\u00a0 I'm guessing it's some big regional chain with a big presence in Texas.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Queue pandemonium inside the head of one Sarah Brady.\u00a0 <a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424052702304868004577378421787264242.html\">Obama wants to make it easier for non-Americans to buy American-made firearms</a>.\u00a0 How about making easier for Americans to buy American-made firearms?\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 The Feds' case against the Cleveland Occutards is already falling apart.\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.thesmokinggun.com/documents/fbi-informant-shaquille-azir-756123\">Turns out the stool pidgeon is a multiple time loser</a>.\u00a0 That's what most \"informants\" are -- People who have relatively minor brushes with the law, so the fuzz turns them around on various groups of interest.\u00a0 These snitches have a direct incentive to hurry up and produce \"results\" by provoking terrorist plots, because the fuzz is holding the Sword of Damocles of the original charges over their heads.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 LOL!\u00a0 <a href=\"http://dailycaller.com/2012/05/01/antiquated-boston-law-banned-native-americans-from-boston-until-2005/\">Until 2005, it was technically a crime for the Dime Store Indian to set foot in the biggest city in her own state.</a>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Speaking of which, <a href=\"http://thepeoplescube.com/peoples-blog/cher-endorses-elizabeth-warren-t8942.html\">Cher endorsed Elizabeth Warren</a>.\u00a0 Mainly out of tribal loyalty.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://justoneminute.typepad.com/main/2012/05/a-paper-of-cowards.html\">A good theory</a> why the newspaper in Norfolk, Virginia covered up the hate-fueled assault against their own reporters.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Legally, no.\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.theatlantic.com/national/archive/2012/04/what-right-do-schools-have-to-discipline-students-for-what-they-say-off-campus/256476/\">But they better get used to this sort of thing</a>, because it's good practice for the real world.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 Who said this?\r\n\r\n<em>\u201cAt first I thought it was, but I don\u2019t think so,\u201d [*****] said in an interview Monday night on [*****]. \u201cTo me, to take a fourth-grader or a sixth-grader or a high school student, and say you\u2019re going to stay more than six hours \u2014 we need quality instructions.\u201d</em>\r\n\r\nThis sounds like a George W. Bush malapropism.\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.suntimes.com/12240280-417/daley-longer-school-day-isnt-the-answer.html\">Except when it's not.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>INTERNATIONAL</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/world/2012/may/02/romney-british-pm-obama-london?INTCMP=SRCH\">Make no bones about it</a> -- CaMORON will at the very least not endorse Romney, and may even endorse Obama.\u00a0 That's because the \"Conservative\" Party in Britain isn't.\u00a0 It's mostly a bunch of Olympia Snowes on the front benches and at \"best\" a bunch of Sean Hannitys on the back benches.\r\n\r\n<strong>MISC STUFF</strong>\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.t-g.com/story/1843748.html\">I wouldn't have spent it.</a>\u00a0 It's probably got a lot of numismatic value.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/blind-golden-retriever-befriends-dog-hospital-guide-article-1.1070177\">Chicken soup for the soul</a>.\r\n\r\n*\u00a0 <a href=\"http://sports.yahoo.com/news/crash-survivor-plans-play-michigan-131138595--spt.html\">More chicken soup for the soul.</a>", "categories": ["Uncategorized"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 02:56:19", "language": "en", "author": "141553", "url": "http://countenance.wordpress.com/?p=19273", "title": "Redeployment", "blog": "142127", "post_id": "461599", "tags": [], "blogname": "Countenance Blog", "date": "2012-05-03 20:56:19", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.stltoday.com/news/local/crime-and-courts/metro-east-officials-tout-program-to-keep-teens-out-of/article_d78fa6df-581f-5188-ac32-7e7ed55425f1.html\">P-D</a>:\r\n<blockquote><strong>Illinois officials tout program to keep Metro East teens out of prison</strong>\r\n\r\n(snip)\r\n\r\nRedeploy offers hometown therapy, substance abuse treatment and mental health care and more. Caseworkers also provide career counseling and field trips to successful enterprises.\r\n\r\n(snip)\r\n\r\nMelodee Hanes, the acting administrator for the U.S. Department of Justice's Office of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention, attended and said, \"Keeping kids out of jail is really the right thing to do.\" She asked, \"Think back to when you were 16? Did you ever make a bad decision?\"</blockquote>\r\nYes, I did.\u00a0 And believe me, that was the worst burrito I ever ate.\u00a0 It wasn't until I was out of college that I worked up the courage to eat another burrito.\r\n\r\nJust in case that snarky sentence went over your head, I cringe over dismissing criminal behavior as a \"bad decision.\"\u00a0 <a href=\"http://countenance.wordpress.com/2009/12/15/linguistic-linguini/\">I ranted about a similar thing a few years ago</a>, and \"bad decision\" is very similar to \"choices\" insofar as linguistic linguine.\u00a0 Yes, people make bad decisions, but the connotation of that is that all possible decisions are legitimate, but the one you made just didn't work for you.\u00a0 It's impossible to make a \"bad decision\" when you commit a crime, because the law takes that particular action out of the universe of legitimate decisions.\r\n\r\nI also remember the exact number of crimes I committed because I lacked hometown therapy, drug treatment, mental health care, career counseling and field trips to businesses:\r\n\r\nZero.\r\n\r\nThe photo and caption?\u00a0 'Nuff Said.\u00a0 Speaking of bad decisions, he was 15 and she was 17...", "categories": ["Black Crime", "Illinois &#038; Metro East", "Linguistic Linguini"], "likes": []}
