{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 08:54:54", "language": "en", "author": "145954", "url": "http://doods.wordpress.com/?p=587", "title": "PCCI welcomes inclusion of disaster risks management in environment assessment", "blog": "146457", "post_id": "813843", "tags": ["PCCI"], "blogname": "Gotchablog", "date": "2012-04-30 09:54:54", "content": "<div>The influential Philippine Chamber of Commerce and Industry (PCCI) has welcomed the inclusion of concerns on climate change and disaster risks management in the country's environment impact assessment (EIA) system, but cautioned this must not become an added burden to new investors.</div><div><br />An EIA is a corporate action plan in complying with local environment protection and management laws required by the DENR for new investment projects in the country. It paves the way for the issuance or rejection of an environment clearance certificate, the first major step before an investment project is allowed to be put on the ground.</div><div id=\"yiv1094638068yui_3_2_0_23_1335700714016143\">\u00a0</div><div>Pura Pedrosa, Policy and Planning Division Chief of EMB told the PCCI that dealing with natural hazards brought about by the changing climate conditions in the country must also be considered in an investor's environment impact plan.</div><div>Projects to be covered by the new order will be big investment projects that range from agricultural plantations to thermal power plants. Small enterprises are exempted from securing environment clearance certificates prior to going into business.</div><div>Pedrosa explained that in considering future natural disasters, applicants for environment clearances need not make their own research but may rely on researches already made by government agencies like the disaster vulnerability map being prepared by DENR and the climate change impact projected up to the year 2050 prepared by the weather bureau.</div><div>Several companis have expressed concern that due to the lack of scientific knowledge, there is bound to be a lot of judgment calls on the parts of environment regulators in determining if an environment plan prepared by a company passes the added requirements of mitigating the impact of climate change.</div><div>This may lead to longer red tape, and worse, rejection of investment projects if the guidelines are not clear to investors.</div><div>\u00a0</div><div>PCCI suggested that if there is still room for further refinement of the guidelines, its own experts will be willing to sit down with environment officials to clear things up before the new order is fully implemented.</div><div>Pedrosa agreed that further consultation will be made with the private sector on the technical guidelines attached to the order.</div>", "categories": ["News"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 08:38:21", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=624", "title": "Without the chips", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1984386", "tags": ["chocolate chips", "dessert", "food", "magimix gelato chef 2200", "Mint ice-cream recipe", "simple ice-cream machine recipe"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 08:38:21", "content": "I love mint ice cream but never liked the chocolate chips in it. So, I used to spit them out, pick them out.... just never liked them. In Verona, Italy they have very creamy mint ice-cream without the choc chips, oooooh how I miss them. A bit far to travel for that right now. Couldn't resist making a batch myself. So I bought the Magimix Gelato Chef 2200 and I am on my way to a lovely batch of choc chips free mint ice-cream. My first time!!! It should be easy I think, since there is no pre freezing involved. Just turn it on, and away it churns.\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/6eicecream3.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/6eicecream3.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"6Eicecream3\" width=\"640\" height=\"640\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-630\" /></a>\r\n\r\nRecipe:\r\n200ml milk\r\n150ml double cream\r\n75g GUITTARD GREEN MINT CHIPS (all the way from San Fransico - thank you Sweetie)\r\n2 eggs\r\n\r\n1, Melt choc chips in bowl add cream and milk a bit at a time and stir to combine.\r\n2, Whisk the eggs with a little cream until creamy yellow..\r\n3, Combine the two mixture and allow to cool.\r\n4, Pour all into the machine and wait for it to be done...\r\nYummy!\r\n\r\nWhat if you haven't got those mint chips?\r\nUmm. Do this:\r\nMake mint syrup with 6 table spoons of superfine sugar and 10 fresh large sprigs of mint leaves.\r\nPut 4 table spoon of water, mint leaves and sugar in a pot and heat until sugar is dissolved completely.\r\nLeave to cool.\r\n\r\n1, Whisk eggs with half a cup of sugar until it forms creamy yellow ribbon.\r\n2, Slowly add your mint syrup.\r\n3, Add milk &amp; Cream to this mixture whisking with electric mixer the whole time.\r\n4, Pour all into machine and wait for it to be done.\r\n\r\nBest results: scrap out ice-cream into plastic tubs and freeze for another hour. It will become harder like store bought ice-cream.\r\nSooooo yummy!\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0793.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0793.jpg?w=300\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0793\" width=\"300\" height=\"224\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-634\" /></a>", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 14:24:10", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=640", "title": "Dark Chocolate Ice cream the cheating way", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "243430", "tags": ["Chocolate ice-cream homemade", "Dark Chocolate ice-cream", "Easy dark chocolate ice-cream", "Green and Black 70%"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 14:24:10", "content": "<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0790.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0790.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0790\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-642\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/bitterchocice-greamwcam.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/bitterchocice-greamwcam.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"bitterchocice-greamwcam\" width=\"640\" height=\"480\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-641\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0794.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0794.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0794\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-649\" /></a>\r\n\r\n3 organic egg yolks\r\n2/3 cups of sugar\r\n100g 70% Green &amp; Black Dark chocolate (broken up into bits)\r\n4 heaped table spoon of Valrhona Dark Chocolate powder\r\n1 cup organic millk\r\n1 cup single cream\r\n\r\nWhisk the yolks with sugar until it forms yellow ribbons\r\nIn a saucepan put some water and put a ceramic or glass bowl over it.\r\nPut the broken pieces of dark chocolate in the bowl and melt on medium heat.\r\nWhen the chocolate is melting, add the dark chocolate powder into it, and stir\r\nAdd 1 teaspoon salt into this and stir.\r\nSlowly add 1 cup of milk into the chocolate mixture, stir with wooden spoon\r\nWhen all combined, remove bowl from heat and slowly whisk this hot chocolate mixture into your egg mixture (beating with electric mixer the whole time)\r\nWhisk in the cream on low speed.\r\nStrain out bits and bubbles and leave in the fridge for a good 20 mins before you put it in your machine.\r\n\r\nWith the Gelato Chef 2200, it takes about 30 mins.\r\nI then, transfer the ice-cream into plastic tub, and freeze in freezer for another 1 hour before serving.\r\n\r\nUmmm... really very yummy.\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0796.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0796.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0796\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-654\" /></a>", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 15:12:56", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=644", "title": "Experimenting with basic moist cake recipe", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1053291", "tags": [], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 15:12:56", "content": "What can one do with plain cake recipe? Tweak it with flavours and fruits and jams of course!\r\n\r\nBasic Moist cake recipe:\r\n1 cup of butter\r\nhalf cup of sugar\r\n3 eggs\r\n2 cups of self rising flour\r\n1/3 cup of water\r\n1 tablespoon vanilla extract\r\n\r\nAdd ons:\r\n2 table spoon of East India Company Orange Blossom syrup\r\n1 table spoon of Passion fruit and Orange jam - dissolved in 1/3 cup of water\r\nor \r\nDark Chocolate powder?\r\nor raspberries crushed?\r\n\r\n\r\nZest of one orange\r\n150g Buttercream icing\r\n250g Cream Cheese\r\n\r\nPreheat oven to 180\u00baC\r\nput paper cups into cupcake pans\r\n1, Cream butter and sugar.\r\n2, Beat in eggs, one at a time\r\n3, Add Passion fruit and OJam syrup.\r\n4, Add Orange Blossom syrup\r\n5, Add water.\r\nBeat on medium speed until combined\r\nFold in sifted flour.\r\n\r\nDistribute in cupcake pan and bake in middle of oven for about 12 mins, until wooden stick comes out clean.\r\nCool on wire rack.\r\n\r\nMake your buttercream icing normally\r\nAdd this to your straight out of fridge cream cheese and beat with electric mixer until combined\r\nStir in orange zest.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/ccpflvexp.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/ccpflvexp.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"ccpflvexp\" width=\"640\" height=\"857\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-645\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 22:27:24", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=656", "title": "Evening drink ", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1368005", "tags": ["Chia chin Lin", "cocktail recipe", "cocktail recipes", "Malibu coconut", "Old Tree Cocktail", "Peach Nectar", "Summer berry cocktail"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 22:27:24", "content": "This is something I invented for a friend, who fondly talks about her memories of hot evenings in Portugal where they drank jugs of red coloured cocktails filled with berries and red liquid on some breezy roof top.\r\n\r\n50ml Malibu poured over ice cubes.\r\n50ml Peach Nectar.\r\nFilled half the glass with with La Mortuacienne Mandarin Orange, or Fanta red.\r\nTop up with soda water or sparkling water.\r\nAdd summer berries and stir to taste.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0601.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0601.jpg?w=224\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0601\" width=\"224\" height=\"300\" class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-657\" /></a>\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 22:33:45", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=659", "title": "Moroccan evening drink", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1217218", "tags": [], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 22:33:45", "content": "I am not sure if this is what they will serve in Morocco, but this is what reminds me of the rose flavoured things they love over there.\r\n\r\n50ml Citron Vodka\r\n25ml East India Company Rose cordial or Rose water.\r\nIce cubes\r\nSoda water or sparkling water\r\n100ml Lychee juice\r\n\r\nPour everything over ice and stir then serve.\r\n\r\n\r\n", "categories": [], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 22:44:25", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=661", "title": "4 Tier Coffee Cake", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "218471", "tags": ["3 tier cake", "cake", "coffee", "coffee cake recipe", "cream cheese icing", "easy coffee cake", "layered coffee cake"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 22:44:25", "content": "I used to make chocolate cake for our family's Sunday dinners at Grandpa's. Everyone loves the sweet treat after a scrumptious feast. Then one evening, my auntie Jackie asked for coffee cake. I love coffee cake too, but at the time, I wasn't very competent in making one that I would feed it to my entire family. So, after many many trails, I tweaked this recipe and made up my own. It's absolutely uber YUM!\r\n\r\n1 cup of butter\r\nhalf cup of sugar\r\n3 eggs\r\n2 cups of self rising flour\r\n1/3 cup of cooled expresso + 3 teaspoon of instant coffee.\r\n1 tablespoon vanilla extract\r\n\r\nFollow the recipe of <a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/2012/05/01/experimenting-with-basic-moist-cake-recipe/\">basic moist cake</a>, but use the coffee instead of water.\r\nBake in round or square cake tins at 180\u00baC for 15mins or until wooden stick comes out clean.\r\n\r\nWhen cake is cool, slice in to 3 layers.\r\nUse a wet knife.\r\n\r\nIcing:\r\n250g Basic Buttercream icing + 250g Cream Cheese \r\nWhisk until blended, add 3 tablespoons of instant coffee dissolved in a single expresso.\r\nAdd to cream cheese mixture\r\nStir through, leave in plastic tub inside fridge for 30 mins.\r\nOtherwise too soft to spread.\r\n\r\nEnjoy.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0768.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0768.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0768\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-662\" /></a>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:00:18", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=667", "title": "Fantaccino \u00a9rocket4rocket", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "341093", "tags": ["kids cocktails"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 23:00:18", "content": "Fantaccino, has no coffee in it. I was in Melbourne, and buying coffee beans in Victoria Market. While chatting with the owner of the stall, he tells me how good his beans are especially for cappuccino, then I asked him if he has ever tasted a Fantaccino, of course he hasn't, and not even heard of it. What is it? Fanta with coffee? No.\r\nIt can be served to little kids. My nephews loves it.\r\nIt is something that I created and gave it the name. I made this when I was a kid.\r\nI will share it with you, but please give me credit for it, and please don't sell it!\r\n\r\n1, Go get one cup of soft serve from McDonalds\r\n2, A can of Fanta orange\r\n3, Ice cubes\r\n4, optional slices of strawberries\r\n\r\nAdult version: Add 50ml Malibu over the strawberries stir and let strawberries soak in it for an hour. Pour over the whole thing and stir it.\r\n\r\nIn a tall glass, put your soft serve in first, then add the ice cubes.\r\nPour Fanta over it, stir it until it foams up to the rim.\r\nAdd slices of strawberries if you like.\r\nPut 2 straws and drink up!\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0493.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0493.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0493\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-668\" /></a>\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:06:02", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=672", "title": "Another red cocktail ", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1401477", "tags": [], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 23:06:02", "content": "This one I made for P2. \r\n\r\n1 can of Tropical Fanta \r\n25ml of Malibu\r\n25ml of limoncello\r\n25ml of peach nectar\r\n3 slices of nectarine \r\nIce\r\n\r\nPour all liquid over ice cubes, stir, top with nectarine slices and serve.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/wetevening2.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/wetevening2.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"wetevening2\" width=\"640\" height=\"853\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-673\" /></a>", "categories": [], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:15:20", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=675", "title": "Spiked Longan cocktail ", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "477766", "tags": ["dried longan", "longan drink", "old tree bakery uk", "old tree bakery uk cocktail", "old tree uk"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 23:15:20", "content": "My friend needed an alternative cocktail with an oriental twist, so I created this especially for her. We tried it, and it was really delicious.\r\n\r\nA handful of dried <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Longan\">Longan</a> \r\nJust enough water to cover them in a saucepan.\r\nSimmer on low heat until you get a thick brown syrup.\r\nStore in the fridge until needed.\r\n\r\n50ml of Longan syrup\r\n50ml of Gordon's Gin\r\nPoured over ice cubes\r\nTop up with Ginger Ale or ginger beer.\r\nServe immediately\r\n\r\nThe photo may not look as yummy, but it really is.\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_06741.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_06741.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0674\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-677\" /></a>\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:30:38", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=679", "title": "Winding down with a glass of elegance &amp; a good night kiss", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "828821", "tags": ["east india company rose cordial", "rose cordial", "rose water", "sealed with a kiss"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 23:30:38", "content": "I am obsessed with the delicate taste of rose. First it was cubes of turkish delight, then it was Laduree's pale pink rose milk shake and ice-cream. Then I found this cordial and went on a mad adventure of creating all these rose flavoured food.\r\n\r\nHere is a very simple refreshing summer drink for ladies.\r\n\r\n50ml Rose cordial poured over crushed ice cubes, add soda water and stir.\r\nSo nice and refreshing on a hot summer's afternoon, or a warm evening.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0798.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0798.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0798\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-680\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0799.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0799.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0799\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-681\" /></a>\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0801.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0801.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0801\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-682\" /></a>\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:48:22", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=684", "title": "Staple items in my kitchen", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "719889", "tags": [], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 23:48:22", "content": "<a href=\"http://www.theeastindiacompanyfinefood.com/product/41/cordials.htm\">Rose Cordial</a>\r\nBetty Crocker French Vanilla Cake Mix\r\nButter \r\nLegbar eggs\r\nMalibu\r\nGin\r\nAbsolute Citron Vodka\r\n<a href=\"http://www.thespiceshop.co.uk\">Herbs and spices from Notting Hill</a>\r\nSteal Cut quick cooking oats - if pre-soaked overnight, it makes the best porridge in the world.\r\nPink Rock salt\r\nSoda water\r\nPlain yogurt - I use this for chicken. Yes, chicken.\r\nJersey Milk - makes the best cafe latte ever. I call it the milk that u can chew on.\r\nBrown sugar for making chewy chocolate chip cookies\r\nComvita Manuka Honey - One spoonful a day really keeps the doctors away.\r\nGinger - Sliced and boiled in water, drink everyday and keep your hay fever symtoms down.\r\nCinnamon - Spoonful of the powder mix with honey and hot water keeps your heart healthy and lowers your cholesterol.\r\nElder Flower Cordial - also good for hay fever.\r\nCouscous - Quickest grain - faster than cooking rice\r\nTaiwanese black sesame - to make food with, and keeps your hair looking black and shiny\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["Serious Eats"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 23:55:28", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=686", "title": "Best steak under \u00a36", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "154156", "tags": [], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-01 23:55:28", "content": "My mother and Granny shops at Harrods. Ever since I was a kid, I have seen my granny use green or white harrods food hall bags as garbage bags, that's how many bags she has under her sink. Both of them said, why shop somewhere else when you can be sure of getting the best in Harrods? Many will think that only rich people buys groceries in Harrods, but my mom told me that you can get meat half price if you go just before closing time. So, that's what I have been doing.\r\n\r\nI got 2 pieces of the best steak their butcher have and it was only \u00a310.\r\n\r\nIn a very hot pan, heat some olive oil and a big knob of butter.\r\nDry your steak, and cut crosses on both sides.\r\nFry in hot pan, 2 mins on both sides.\r\nServe with potatoes and parsnips mash.\r\nIf you like peas, that too.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0613.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0613.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0613\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-687\" /></a> ", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 00:00:25", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=689", "title": "Brownie cookie from mix", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "810075", "tags": [], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-02 00:00:25", "content": "One box of Brownie mix\r\nAdd one cup of plain flour to mix, and reduce water to 1/3 cup\r\nFollow instruction on box.\r\n\r\nScoop mixture onto baking sheet\r\nBake as instructed.\r\n\r\nMake some vanilla cream icing\r\nSandwich the icing and add a few raspberries between 2 cookie.\r\nYou are in for a treat.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0652.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0652.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0652\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-690\" /></a> ", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 18:14:13", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=692", "title": "Home made Ice cream experiment update", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "570399", "tags": ["heavy cream vs. whipping cream home made ice cream", "Home made mint ice cream", "Ice cream machine experiment", "Ice cream machine recipe"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-03 18:14:13", "content": "My first try on making the mint ice cream was with Double Cream (heavy cream), then I read in an ice cream recipe book that heavy cream gives your ice cream a buttery texture and taste, might be a bit heavy. So I alternated the cream with Whipping cream this time.\r\nThe verdict? I think I should stay with the heavy cream, because the whipping cream is lighter, and reduces the time required to firm the ice-cream in my freezer, but regarding the taste? It is a lot lighter and not as luxury as when using the heavy cream.\r\n\r\nPhoto: Dark Chocolate ice cream with Mint ice cream\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0810.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0810.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0810\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-693\" /></a>\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 18:28:45", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=696", "title": "coconut ice cream", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1682802", "tags": ["Coconut cream", "Coconut ice cream", "Home made coconut ice cream"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-03 18:28:45", "content": "150ml full cream milk\r\n200ml coconut cream (unsweetened canned)\r\n25ml Malibu Rum\r\n150g sugar\r\n1 egg\r\n\r\nWhisk egg and sugar until it forms ribbon, combine coconut cream and milk and then slowly add to egg mixture beating on low speed the whole time while you are adding. Stir in the rum. Pour into your ice cream maker and wait... YUM\r\n\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/coconut.jpg\" alt=\"coconut\" class=\"size-full wp-image-702\" />\r\n\r\nWhen done, you can chop mango pieces and stir it through your not yet firm ice cream, scoop into tubs and freeze until firm.\r\nOther things you can add to this:\r\nToasted almond flakes, toasted coconut shreds....umm..", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 00:41:12", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=706", "title": "African nanny corn from Francesca's memories", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "386512", "tags": ["african fried corn", "corn kernels"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-04 00:41:12", "content": "My memories of strange adventures, strange foods were heard from other girls during my eye widening and wonderful boarding school years. For many nights, girls from a diversity of background told each other stories of our own childhood, or holidays. My friend Francesca told me about this delicious fried corn her nanny used to make for her and her brother when they lived in Africa. She said, it was delicious, and she described each corn kernel fried in butter until slightly black. I was amazed how she could have remembered how it was made, or perhaps she didn't. I roughly remembered it was butter, corn kernels and a hot pan. The way she described it made my mouth water. \r\n\r\nIt wasn't until many years later, that I have tried making it.\r\nHere is what I did.\r\n\r\nIn a dry hot pan, drop in a knob of butter.\r\nQuickly toss in corn kernels (best to use fresh ones, and not canned.)\r\nStir fry it until slightly burnt blackish brown on some sides.\r\nSprinkle Paprika and salt &amp; freshly ground pepper to taste.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/fcorn.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/fcorn.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"fcorn\" width=\"552\" height=\"474\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-707\" /></a>\r\n\r\nI hope I have done her fond memories of her African nanny's creation justice.\r\n\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 00:52:41", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=709", "title": "Cousin Diane's potato crisps &amp; it's foil packets", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1156845", "tags": ["Chips packets", "crisps packets", "Crushed crisps cooking", "Simple dinner", "Smart kitchen storing", "Vegetable stay fresh"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-04 00:52:41", "content": "My cousin Diane lives in the USA, and I have always thought they are an entirely different clan. Their ways of living are sometimes smart, sometimes strange. Anyhow, this is what she have told me and I tried it and thought it was really brilliant.\r\n\r\nSave your foil crisps packets after you have finished the crisps. Veggies stays fresh in them much longer than just sitting in the fridge.\r\n\r\nOK, here is what you can do with the crisps besides munching them in front of the tele.\r\nCrush a whole packet of crisps any flavour. (I like to use BBQ flavour)\r\nDip chicken thighs in egg, then coat them in the crushed crisps.\r\nI also double dip them, so once again, into the egg, then into the crushed crisps.\r\nNow pre heat oven to 200\u00baC and bake until golden brown.\r\n\r\nYum!\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 17:22:29", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=711", "title": "Bad day recovery Low fat chocolate cake ", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "1329668", "tags": ["Low fat chocolate cake recipe", "using yogurt chocolate cake recipe"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-04 17:22:29", "content": "Council tax first reminder note arrived, in red - didn't I already set up direct debit last year? I DID!!! how come it is telling me that I have missed an instalment??\r\n\r\nPrint out of First Luggage required main ticket for mom's bags didn't go so well.. Complicated bits of docs to be stuck on luggage, but pouch not provided! Driver came to collect them, but just took all the documents in a bunch. What's the point of sending complicated instruction to customers when the other end doesn't follow them???\r\n\r\nWe have entered the E-receipt world since 2003.. and stupid boss demands paper receipts - I just haven't got one to give! ERRRRRGGGHHHH...\r\nTold him one billion times already! NO RECEIPTS don't ask any more!\r\n\r\nDemanded to have a scanned statement from accountant last week, still haven't got one.\r\n\r\nNeed to eat chocolate cake:\r\n\r\nLow fat, low sugar chocolate cake. Since it is low fat and low sugar, I can have cream and chocolate sauce on it, can't I?\r\n\r\nso here we go:\r\n\r\n1 2/3 cups flour\r\n1/2 cup sugar (can use half white sugar and Splenda if desired)\r\n2/3 cup unsweetened baking cocoa, sifted\r\n1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda\r\n1 teaspoon salt\r\n1/2 cup applesauce\r\n1 1/2 cups skim milk yogurt (or use low-fat or fat-free sour cream)\r\n1 tablespoon vanilla\r\n4 egg whites\t (or use 2 whole eggs)\r\n\r\n\r\nSet oven to 180\u00b0F.\r\n\r\nGenerously grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.\r\n\r\nIn a medium bowl sift the flour with cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.\r\n\r\nIn another bowl beat the sugar with egg whites and vanilla until well combined.\r\n\r\nMix in the yogurt and applesauce until thoroughly combined.\r\n\r\nMix the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and beat on low speed until just combined.\r\n\r\nTransfer to prepared baking dish.\r\n\r\nBake for about 30-35 minutes or until cake tests done (watch closely, do not over bake!).\r\n\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0821.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0821.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0821\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-712\" /></a>\r\n\r\n", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 17:31:47", "language": "en", "author": "146384", "url": "http://rocket4rocketblog.wordpress.com/?p=714", "title": "Wonderful world of eggs", "blog": "146885", "post_id": "76155", "tags": ["fried turkey egg", "Turkey eggs"], "blogname": "The Hungry Artist", "date": "2012-05-04 17:31:47", "content": "If you love to eat eggs as much as I do, I recommend you try legbar eggs. Their shell is of a calming pale blue colour, and it's yolk is deep orange yellow. Full of flavour better than ordinary hen's eggs. I love them anyway u cook them, I will eat it. \r\nThen a few days ago, I saw these speckled turkey eggs. Umm.. would it be just as nice? I got some to try.\r\nSee photo:\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0819.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0819.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0819\" width=\"640\" height=\"856\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-716\" /></a>\r\n\r\nTheir shell is tough, need to really smash it to open it. Yolk is surprising - pale cream colour. I wonder why.\r\nA little skeptical about larger birds' eggs as the last duck egg I tried, the flavour was a little too strong for me, but then the goose egg was a real treat. I feel like a fox, talking about eggs like this.\r\n\r\nAnyway, so I cracked the turkey egg in a hot pan with butter, and added one legbar egg for good measure. See photo:\r\n<a href=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0820.jpg\"><img src=\"http://rocket4rocketblog.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/img_0820.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"IMG_0820\" width=\"640\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-715\" /></a>\r\n\r\nTurkey egg has a somewhat sweet full bodied flavour in their yolks, and the whites are tough like a goose egg's. But I must say, it's quite nice.\r\nWouldn't mind having another one.", "categories": ["I Cook"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-04-30 21:00:46", "language": "en", "author": "146478", "url": "http://thetimehascome.wordpress.com/?p=4237", "title": "The Heart of a Servant - Mark 10:32-45", "blog": "146978", "post_id": "342382", "tags": ["Faith", "God", "Gospel of Mark", "Humble", "Humility", "Jesus", "Kingdom of God", "podcast", "Servanthood", "Serving", "Troy Church of Christ"], "blogname": "The Time Has Come", "date": "2012-04-30 16:00:46", "content": "<img style=\"visibility:hidden;width:0;height:0;\" src=\"http://c.gigcount.com/wildfire/IMP/CXNID=2000002.0NXC/bHQ9MTMzNTgyMDUzNTAyMSZwdD*xMzM1ODIwNTQ1OTEyJnA9MTM2ODIxJmQ9Jm49d29yZHByZXNzJmc9MSZvPTFlZTk4YzRkN2E5/MjQ2ZjliMTNjMTdkMmNiZmJlNzhlJm9mPTA=.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"0\" height=\"0\" border=\"0\" /><a href=\"http://thetimehascome.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/4-29-12-053-001.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-4240\" title=\"4-29-12.053.001\" src=\"http://thetimehascome.files.wordpress.com/2012/04/4-29-12-053-001.jpg?w=150\" alt=\"\" width=\"150\" height=\"112\" /></a>\"You know that those who are regarded as rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them, and their high officials exercise authority over them. Not so with you. Instead, whoever wants to become great among you must be your servant, and whoever wants to be first must be slave of all. For even the Son of Man did not come to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for many.\"\r\n\r\n- Jesus, Mark 10:42-45 (NIV'84)\r\n<div id=\"divInfo\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>\u00a0[gigya width=\"290\" height=\"65\" src=\"http://sermon.net/swf/ma.swf\" quality=\"high\" flashvars=\"poid=119903225&amp;d=http://www.sermon.net/\" align=\"middle\" wmode=\"transparent\" allowScriptAccess=\"always\" ]</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>", "categories": ["Church of Christ", "Jesus", "Troy Church of Christ"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 14:24:32", "language": "en", "author": "146478", "url": "http://thetimehascome.wordpress.com/?p=4243", "title": "Two great thoughts for parents, youth ministers, and teachers", "blog": "146978", "post_id": "168493", "tags": ["Accomplishments", "Children", "Daughters", "Dreams", "Fathers", "Goals", "Mothers", "Parents", "Sons", "Teachers", "Teens", "Youth Ministers"], "blogname": "The Time Has Come", "date": "2012-05-01 09:24:32", "content": "From my good friend, James Kinnaird, whom God has gifted with a great \"big picture\" heart and mind for others:\r\n<blockquote>There's only one frustrating aspect to teaching Life Skills classes and Relationship classes. Having to deconstruct the \"I'm not good...smart...fit...rich...cute...enough\" mindset. Sad part is when kids hear that mess from various adults in their lives. In the name of being realist or practical, we can actually quash the dream and goals of those who look up to us. We adults have to commit to fanning the flame of vision and setting faith-inspired goals in the hearts and minds of teens. By the way, adults, it's AN AWESOME thing if the kids we influence do better than us...that's what we're supposed to be about.</blockquote>\r\nFrom Alex Harris, author of\u00a0<em>Do Hard Things: A Teenage Rebellion Against Low Expectations</em>:\r\n<blockquote>\u201cUnfortunately we often get praise for things that weren't particularly difficult to achieve. If we focus on the props and encouragement of those who have low expectations for us, we become mediocre. It can be challenging to set our sights on excellence, particularly when we're hearing that we're already there. One of life's greatest lessons, which we all must learn, could be expressed in the phrase 'That was nothing. Watch this.' Challenge yourself and others to call the normal things normal and save that word excellent for things that really are.\u201d</blockquote>", "categories": ["Family", "Life", "Quotes"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 20:49:55", "language": "en", "author": "146478", "url": "https://thetimehascome.wordpress.com/?p=4246", "title": "The Gospels and the Gospel", "blog": "146978", "post_id": "1730873", "tags": ["Gospel", "Jesus", "Quotes"], "blogname": "The Time Has Come", "date": "2012-05-02 15:49:55", "content": "<blockquote>If we are tempted for even a passing moment to wonder if the Gospels preach the gospel, then we have fallen from the apostolic gospel. Why? It was the apostolic generation that called Mark (and probably Matthew) the \u201cgospel.\u201d Why? Because the gospel is the completion of Israel\u2019s Story in the Story of Jesus, and that is precisely what the Gospels in fact do.\n\u2014 Scot McKnight, <em>The King Jesus Gospel</em></blockquote>", "categories": ["Jesus", "Quotes"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-01 00:11:46", "language": "en", "author": "148330", "url": "http://rojotransitorio.com/?p=5270", "title": "Nicanor Parra: el antipoeta", "blog": "148794", "post_id": "38457", "tags": ["Alejandro Jodorowsky", "Imaginaci\u00f3n", "Literatura", "Nicanor Parra", "Poes\u00eda"], "blogname": "Rojo Transitorio", "date": "2012-05-01 02:11:46", "content": "[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"350\" caption=\"Nicanor Parra: el hombre imaginario\"]<a href=\"http://fav.me/d492ikr\"><img alt=\"Nicanor Parra: el hombre imaginario\" src=\"http://th04.deviantart.net/fs70/PRE/f/2011/249/6/4/don_nica_by_baztardillo-d492ikr.png\" title=\"Nicanor Parra: el hombre imaginario\" width=\"350\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://xsantotomas.files.wordpress.com/2011/11/img_open_quote.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"img_open_quote\" width=\"45\" height=\"41\" style=\"vertical-align:baseline;\" />El hombre imaginario\r\nvive en una mansion imaginaria\r\nrodeada de arboles imaginarios\r\na la orilla de un rio imaginario\r\n...\r\nDe los muros que son imaginarios\r\npenden antiguos cuadros imaginarios\r\nirreparables grietas imaginarias\r\nque representan hechos imaginarios\r\nocurridos en mundos imaginarios\r\nen lugares y tiempos imaginarios\r\n...\r\nTodas las tardes tardes imaginarias\r\nsube las escaleras imaginarias\r\ny se asoma al balcon imaginario\r\na mirar el paisaje imaginario\r\nque consiste en un valle imaginario\r\ncircundado de cerros imaginarios\r\n...\r\nSombras imaginarias\r\nvienen por el camino imaginario\r\nentonando canciones imaginarias\r\na la muerte del sol imaginario\r\n...\r\nY en las noches de luna imaginaria\r\nsue\u00f1a con la mujer imaginaria\r\nque le brindo su amor imaginario\r\nvuelve a sentir ese mismo dolor\r\nese mismo placer imaginario\r\ny vuelve a palpitar\r\nel coraz\u00f3n del hombre imaginario<img src=\"http://xsantotomas.files.wordpress.com/2011/11/img_close_quote.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"img_close_quote\" width=\"45\" height=\"41\" style=\"vertical-align:top;\" /></p>\r\n\r\nAntipoema <a href=\"http://cvc.cervantes.es/literatura/escritores/parra/antologia/hombre.htm\" title=\"El hombre imaginario en el Centro Virtual Cervantes\" target=\"_blank\">El hombre imaginario</a> (Nicanor Parra)\r\n\r\n<h2>Las casualidades de la vida</h2>\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"150\" caption=\"Parranda larga\"]<a href=\"http://www.alfaguara.com/es/libro/parranda-larga-antologia-poetica/\"><img alt=\"Parranda larga de Nicanor Parra\" src=\"http://www.alfaguara.com/uploads/imagenes/libro/portada/201003/portada-parranda-larga-antologi-poetica_grande.jpg\" title=\"Parranda larga de Nicanor Parra\" width=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<em>Nicanor Parra</em> llega a mi vida por una serie de casualidades acentuadas, de aquellas que, secuela tras secuela, te hacen centrar la atenci\u00f3n reiteradamente en algo o alguien. \r\n\r\nLa primera rese\u00f1a suya me llega a trav\u00e9s de un autor al que adoro (<a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alejandro_Jodorowsky\" title=\"Alejandro Jodorowsky en la Wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">Alejandro Jodorowsky</a>) el cual, a su vez, adora a <em>Nicanor</em>. Por tanto, es en un <a href=\"http://www.siruela.com/catalogo.php?opcion=buscar&amp;id_libro=950&amp;completa=S\" title=\"La danza de la realidad en Siruela\" target=\"_blank\">libro</a> de <em>Jodorowsky</em> donde empiezo a notar las primeras cosquillas que producen las letras de <em>Nicanor</em>. \r\n\r\nPosteriormente, descubro el d\u00eda de mi aniversario que le han otorgado (que no entregado) el <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Premio_Cervantes\" title=\"Premio Cervantes en la Wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">premio Cervantes</a>. \r\n\r\nVarios meses m\u00e1s tarde, en el <a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/D%C3%ADa_Internacional_del_Libro\" title=\"D\u00eda internacional del libro en la wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">dia internacional del libro</a>, mientras hago cola en una sucursal bancaria, fijando mi atenci\u00f3n en un diario que alguien ha dejado abierto en cierta (y casual) p\u00e1gina, me entero que ese mismo d\u00eda le hacen entrega del premio Cervantes. \r\n\r\nM\u00e1s tarde, y puesto que se trata del <a href=\"http://www.ediciona.com/sant_jordi.php\" title=\"Dia de Sant Jordi en Ediciona\" target=\"_blank\">d\u00eda de Sant Jordi</a>, me acerco a mi librer\u00eda de confianza en <em>Barcelona</em> para auto-regalarme unos cuantos libros. Tengo suerte y encuentro todo lo que busco. \r\n\r\nMientras me encuentro en una de las colas, listo para pagar, oigo que una se\u00f1ora dice (m\u00e1s bien grita) a su marido que la otra cola es menos larga y que haga el favor de encolarse donde toca. Me doy por aludido y, aunque no suelo hacerlo, me cambio de cola junto a la pareja, comprobando y agradeciendo que la se\u00f1ora en cuesti\u00f3n estaba en lo cierto. \r\n\r\nMientras avanzo lentamente en la nueva cola, voy hojeando algunos de los libros que se encuentran en los estantes adjuntos... \u00a1Anda, <a href=\"http://www.alfaguara.com/es/libro/parranda-larga-antologia-poetica/\" title=\"Parranda Larga de Nicanor Parra\" target=\"_blank\">Parranda Larga</a> de <em>Nicanor Parra</em>! lo cojo y lo hojeo, las hojas vuelan, una cae ante mis ojos... \"El hombre imaginario\"... leo con atenci\u00f3n... ya he decidido que un d\u00eda es un d\u00eda y que voy a sumarlo a la cesta de mi compra. \r\n\r\nLa vida, mi vida, funciona as\u00ed: por casualidades. \r\n\r\n<h2>Yo de mayor quiero ser antipoeta</h2>\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"150\" caption=\"Nicanor Parra\"]<a href=\"http://fav.me/djqe6l\"><img alt=\"Nicanor Parra\" src=\"http://fc05.deviantart.net/fs10/i/2006/131/c/c/Nicanor_Parra_by_PMalkovich.jpg\" title=\"Nicanor Parra\" width=\"150\" /></a>[/caption]\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicanor_Parra\" title=\"Nicanor Parra en la Wikipedia \" target=\"_blank\">Nicanor Parra</a> es uno de aquellos hombres que valora <strong>el Arte de la Ciencia y la Ciencia del Arte</strong>. Licenciado en Ciencias Exactas y F\u00edsicas, sabe que todo esp\u00edritu cient\u00edfico lleva en su interior un poeta, o incluso mejor: un <strong>antipoeta</strong>. Ya se ha creado la <strong>etiqueta</strong>. Todo genio debe crear una y, a ser posible, asign\u00e1rsela.   \r\n\r\nEl <strong>antipoeta</strong> es un catalizador de la <strong>antipoes\u00eda</strong>, alguien que sabe invocar los esp\u00edritus contrarios a la corriente preponderante. \r\n\r\nEl <strong>antipoeta</strong> est\u00e1 ah\u00ed para que el \u00e1rbol no crezca torcido. El <strong>antipoeta</strong> no cumple su palabra si no que cambia los nombres de las cosas. El <strong>antipoeta</strong>, como todo <strong>antipoeta</strong> que se estime a s\u00ed mismo, debe tener su propio diccionario.\r\n \r\nYo de mayor quiero derruir y construir mi coraz\u00f3n. Ning\u00fan techo, ning\u00fan suelo, tan s\u00f3lo puertas y ventanas... Yo de mayor quiero ser <strong>antipoeta</strong>.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>El poeta es un hombre como todos, un alba\u00f1il que construye su muro: un constructor de puertas y ventanas. (Nicanor Parra)</blockquote>\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote>A lo m\u00e1s que se puede aspirar / Es a dejar dos o tres frases en \u00f3rbita / Que yo sepa don Mario dej\u00f3 al menos una: / La muerte y otras sorpresas // \u00a1Se\u00f1or m\u00edo, la frasecita!\r\n(Dedicado a la muerte de Mario Benedetti, Nicanor Parra)</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bitacoras.com/anotaciones/nicanor-parra-el-antipoeta/27634701\"><img src=\"http://widgets.bitacoras.com/votar/mini/nicanor-parra-el-antipoeta/27634701\" alt=\"votar\" title=\"Votar esta anotaci\u00f3n en Bitacoras.com\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;border:0;\" /></a>", "categories": ["Rese\u00f1as"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-03 07:59:20", "language": "en", "author": "148330", "url": "http://rojotransitorio.com/?p=5302", "title": "El sentido de la vida", "blog": "148794", "post_id": "550514", "tags": ["Cuento", "Ense\u00f1anzas", "Espiritualidad", "Paulo Coelho", "Positividad"], "blogname": "Rojo Transitorio", "date": "2012-05-03 09:59:20", "content": "[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hikADxCjdNE]\r\n<p class=\"aligncenter\"><em>El sentido de la vida</em> seg\u00fan <a title=\"Paulo Coelho TV en YouTube\" href=\"http://www.youtube.com/user/paulocoelhoTV\" target=\"_blank\">Paulo Coelho</a>. Subt\u00edtulos (CC) en castellano</p>\r\n\u00bfCu\u00e1l es <a title=\"Una misi\u00f3n\u00a0oculta\" href=\"http://rojotransitorio.com/2012/02/13/una-mision-oculta/\">nuestra misi\u00f3n</a> en esta vida? No busquemos la respuesta en el exterior. Observemos en nuestro interior. Centr\u00e9monos en nuestro coraz\u00f3n. \u00bfQu\u00e9 nos dice?\r\n<h2>La semilla: un sue\u00f1o</h2>\r\nTodo sentido de la vida tiene en su inicio un <strong>sue\u00f1o</strong>: esa es la <strong>semilla</strong> de toda obra que deseemos ofrecer al mundo. Y tales semillas suelen crecer en los mundos de la imaginaci\u00f3n.\r\n\r\nDesgraciadamente, a veces, ese sue\u00f1o anda enterrado bajo capas de apat\u00edas, miedos y frustraciones. Pero un sue\u00f1o es un sue\u00f1o y siempre estar\u00e1 ah\u00ed. Si cavamos lo suficientemente profundo en nuestro <strong>coraz\u00f3n</strong>, reaparecer\u00e1.\r\n\r\nEn tal caso, si el sue\u00f1o se encuentra cerca de su superficie vital, nuestra existencia, podremos escuchar con nitidez como retumba, como se repite con una intensidad cada vez m\u00e1s evidente. Nuestro coraz\u00f3n nos habla. En ocasiones, chilla con voz alta y clara. Los latidos de nuestro sue\u00f1o son audibles incluso desde la mism\u00edsima vigilia.\r\n\r\nY nuestro sue\u00f1o cristalizar\u00e1 gracias a la <strong>fe</strong>\u00a0y a la <a title=\"El Dios de los\u00a0valientes\" href=\"http://rojotransitorio.com/2012/03/28/el-dios-de-los-valientes/\">valent\u00eda</a> que vertamos en \u00e9l. La fe y la valent\u00eda nos permiten creer en algo de naturaleza eterea, mientras la pertinaz\u00a0raz\u00f3n nos murmura que no es posible.\r\n<h2>El alimento: el amor</h2>\r\nUna vez tengamos claro cu\u00e1l es nuestro\u00a0(<strong>verdadero</strong>) sue\u00f1o\u00a0tenemos que alimentarlo con <strong>amor</strong>. Porque el amor por aquello que hacemos rellena nuestra labor de una sana <strong>alegr\u00eda</strong> que nos desborda y se transmite a los que nos acompa\u00f1an en la consecuci\u00f3n de nuestro objetivo vital.\r\n\r\nTal como apunta <em>Coelho</em>, no se trata de un amor rom\u00e1ntico, ni siquiera de uno fraternal o maternal/paternal. Hablamos de una <strong>pasi\u00f3n</strong> y un <strong>entusiasmo</strong>\u00a0capaces de alumbrar nuestro sue\u00f1o en los momentos de mayor oscuridad. Una energ\u00eda que hace brillar y re\u00edr el astro celeste que ilumina nuestro camino. Un <a title=\"Llamadme por mis verdaderos\u00a0nombres\" href=\"http://rojotransitorio.com/2012/03/12/llamadme-por-mis-verdaderos-nombres/\">amor</a> y un respeto por todas las cosas: las peque\u00f1as y las grandes, las que nos indignan y las que nos ilusionan.\r\n<h2>La labor: la perseverancia</h2>\r\nLa <strong>elaboraci\u00f3n</strong> de nuestro sue\u00f1o nos requiere al 100% y nos obliga a la <strong>perseverancia</strong>. Sin perseverancia (y sin amor) no podemos invocar a la (buena)\u00a0<strong>suerte</strong>. Pero no se trata de un azar, se trata de una <a title=\"Suerte o\u00a0azar\" href=\"http://rojotransitorio.com/2012/04/11/suerte-o-azar/\">suerte</a> que permite crear las condiciones para transmutar nuestro sue\u00f1o en realidad. Con ambos ingredientes, y de forma sorprendente, esas circunstancias de incierto\u00a0origen ser\u00e1n <strong>atra\u00eddas</strong> a nuestra vida.\r\n\r\nEl verdadero alquimista, aquel que consigue que el universo <strong>conspire</strong> a su favor, sabe que la perseverancia y el amor son fundamentales para esa <strong>alquimia</strong> que extiende los l\u00edmites de nuestro coraz\u00f3n y abraza el coraz\u00f3n del universo.\r\n<h2>El fruto: una catedral ofrecida al mundo</h2>\r\nComo resultado de la semilla, del alimento y de la labor, obtendremos el fruto m\u00e1s precioso: nuestra catedral, aquella que ofrecemos a nuestra vida, y al mundo. Esa catedral puede tomar una multitud de apariencias pero, en cualquier caso, conforma el verdadero sentido de nuestra vida.\r\n\r\nEl sentido de mi vida ha estado largo tiempo enterrado, pero ya puedo sentir sus latidos cerca de mi superficie. Mi catedral, aquella que ofrecer\u00e9 a mi vida, son los <a title=\"Los cuentos del\u00a0futuro\" href=\"http://rojotransitorio.com/2012/02/05/los-cuentos-del-futuro/\">cuentos del futuro</a>. Unos cuentos que desean, a su vez, plantar semillas en cada una de las personas que los lean. Semillas que permitan a la humanidad\u00a0so\u00f1ar, imaginar y construir un futuro diferente, uno responsable y respetuoso. El fruto de la convicci\u00f3n presente es el futuro so\u00f1ado.\r\n<blockquote>Si se siembra la semilla con fe y se cuida con perseverancia, s\u00f3lo ser\u00e1 cuesti\u00f3n de tiempo recoger sus frutos. (<a title=\"Thomas Carlyle en la wikipedia\" href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Carlyle\" target=\"_blank\">Thomas Carlyle</a>)</blockquote>\r\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"450\"]<a href=\"http://www.todocoleccion.net/ficha-foto-foto-iglesia-santa-maria-mar-archivo-mas-barcelona~x24985427\" target=\"_blank\"><img title=\"Una catedral: Santa Maria del Mar\" src=\"http://www.galeriade.com/Braid44/data/media/39/Santa_Maria_del_Mar_2.0.jpg\" alt=\"Una catedral: Santa Maria del Mar\" width=\"450\" /></a> Una catedral: Santa Mar\u00eda del Mar (Barcelona)[/caption]\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bitacoras.com/anotaciones/el-sentido-de-la-vida/27680945\"><img src=\"http://widgets.bitacoras.com/votar/mini/el-sentido-de-la-vida/27680945\" alt=\"votar\" title=\"Votar esta anotaci\u00f3n en Bitacoras.com\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;border:0;\" /></a>", "categories": ["Art\u00edculos"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-04 22:40:53", "language": "en", "author": "148330", "url": "http://rojotransitorio.com/?p=5365", "title": "Dos universos", "blog": "148794", "post_id": "1179985", "tags": ["M\u00fasica", "Poes\u00eda"], "blogname": "Rojo Transitorio", "date": "2012-05-05 00:40:53", "content": "[youtube=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VQrnD1_34z4]\r\n\r\n<p class=\"aligncenter\"><img src=\"http://xsantotomas.files.wordpress.com/2011/11/img_open_quote.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"img_open_quote\" width=\"45\" height=\"41\" style=\"vertical-align:baseline;\" />Infinita ingenuidad,\r\nilusi\u00f3n centesimal,\r\nme cre\u00eda tan capaz\r\ncon mi c\u00e1psula de Albal.\r\nMi torpeza fue total,\r\nde tan grande es demencial,\r\nno detecto una se\u00f1al,\r\nnunca encontrar\u00e9 el lugar\r\ndonde al fin me entienda.\r\n...\r\nMe perd\u00ed en mi universo .. \u00bfy t\u00fa?\r\n...\r\nNo volver\u00e9 a hacerlo m\u00e1s, \r\nno he encontrado respuestas.<img src=\"http://xsantotomas.files.wordpress.com/2011/11/img_close_quote.gif\" alt=\"\" title=\"img_close_quote\" width=\"45\" height=\"41\" style=\"vertical-align:top;\" /></p>\r\nExtracto de la letra de <a href=\"http://www.musica.com/letras.asp?letra=1642656\" title=\"Letra de Universos Infinitos de Love of Lesbian\" target=\"_blank\">Universos infinitos</a>, <a href=\"http://blogoflesbian.com/\" title=\"Blog de Love of Lesbian\" target=\"_blank\">Love of Lesbian</a>\r\n\r\n<h2>Universos (im)posibles</h2>\r\n\r\nDos universos aglomerados,\r\nconvocados por el deseo,\r\nimbricados por la pasi\u00f3n,\r\nlim\u00edtrofes en su frontera. \r\n...\r\nLa amistad, tu sexo y el m\u00edo, el cuidado. \r\nAlg\u00fan elemento se perdi\u00f3 en mi universo. \r\n\u00bfCu\u00e1l se perdi\u00f3 en el tuyo? \r\n...\r\nEl disentimiento ya me atendi\u00f3, \r\nme prest\u00f3 demasiada atenci\u00f3n. \r\nNo se la devolv\u00ed. \r\nS\u00ed se la devolv\u00ed. \r\n...\r\nLa amistad, nuestro sexo. \r\nAlg\u00fan elemento se perdi\u00f3 en tu universo. \r\n\u00bfCu\u00e1l se perdi\u00f3 en el m\u00edo?\r\n...\r\nDos universos dispersos, \r\nalejados en la confluencia, \r\nperdidos en la fatiga,\r\ndesatendidos por un sue\u00f1o.\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote>La camarader\u00eda no es m\u00e1s que la mitad de la vida: la otra mitad es el amor, una cosa tan diferente de aquella, que podr\u00eda uno imaginarse que fue creada para otro universo. (<a href=\"http://es.wikipedia.org/wiki/G._K._Chesterton\" title=\"G. K. Chesterton en la Wikipedia\" target=\"_blank\">Gilbert Keith Chesterton</a>)</blockquote>\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_5369\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://open.spotify.com/album/2H8D7PqqvSyjrqZjbFxVYQ\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://xsantotomas.files.wordpress.com/2012/05/love-of-lesbian-cuentos-chinos-para-ninos-del-japon-album-art-52885.jpeg\" alt=\"Cuentos chinos para ni\u00f1os del Jap\u00f3n en Spotify\" title=\"Cuentos chinos para ni\u00f1os del Jap\u00f3n en Spotify\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" class=\"size-full wp-image-5369\" /></a>China y Jap\u00f3n: dos universos[/caption]\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://bitacoras.com/anotaciones/dos-universos/27715608\"><img src=\"http://widgets.bitacoras.com/votar/mini/dos-universos/27715608\" alt=\"votar\" title=\"Votar esta anotaci\u00f3n en Bitacoras.com\" style=\"vertical-align:middle;border:0;\" /></a>", "categories": ["Rese\u00f1as"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-02 06:47:36", "language": "en", "author": "139752", "url": "http://byronsharp.wordpress.com/?p=648", "title": "Getting emotional about brands - the real New Coke story", "blog": "149129", "post_id": "495484", "tags": [], "blogname": "Marketing Science", "date": "2012-05-02 06:47:36", "content": "I was recently asked a question by an astute member of the audience: \"what about New Coke?\"\n\nThe implication being, that if consumers rarely feel deep emotional bonds towards the brands they buy then why the rejection of New Coke?\n\nIt was a very good question. \n\nOn the spot I answered that one of the few times that people do get emotional about brands is when you take something away from them, particularly when you do it in a very public noticeable way.  Psychologists talk about the endowment effect, how people tend to place a much higher value on something they already have than something they are offered.  Also people are much more adverse to loss than they are attracted to gains.\n\nI think this is a pretty reasonable answer but it turns out that there is more to the New Coke story...., read on...\n\nThe story of New Coke is now a marketing legend.  Covered by many a textbook and still regularly referred to by marketing consultants. The story goes like this..... worried by 'The Pepsi Challange' taste test Coca-Cola executives decided to change Coke to make it sweeter and more likely to win in blind taste tests with consumers. So a new formula was devised and in a bold move Coca-Cola's time-honoured taste was changed and launched with national advertising and publicity. Cans carried the message \"New\". But the American public hated the idea of a classic like Coke being tampered with. They complained and refused to buy. Coca-Cola realised their mistake and brought back \"Classic Coke\" which quickly became the norm and \"New Coke\" was phased out of production.  It was considered a huge marketing mustake, although some conspiracy theorists proposed that it was all part of a master plan by Coca-Cola corporation to get publicity. So goes the  legend but the real story isn't so neat. \n\nCoke's share price actually went up when it introduced the flavour change. Earlier Coke bottlers gave the CEO of Coke a standing ovation when he announced their plans. Sales did not dive when the new formula was introduced, they rose. So the degree of consumer backlash has been exaggerated, and wasn't immediate.  Resistance came from the South, around Atlanta Coca-Cola Corporation's home. Here were people who felt they owned part of Coke, who felt current management didn't have the right to change things. And here consumer backlash was highly visible to Coke executives many of whom lived in the South. \n\nThe legend that developed later served Coke well. The idea that Americans loved Coke so dearly that they demanded its return and were reminded of their love.", "categories": ["Business"], "likes": []}
{"date_gmt":"2012-05-05 07:41:53", "language": "en", "author": "150222", "url": "http://theotherthomasotter.wordpress.com/?p=1341", "title": "Closing a social transaction. Musings on e-commerce and copyright.", "blog": "151122", "post_id": "888908", "tags": ["art", "Brad Rose", "copright", "gapingvoid", "Ineverfinishanyth", "Law"], "blogname": "Vendorprisey", "date": "2012-05-05 08:41:53", "content": "A couple of days ago via Microsoft's arbiter of all things cool,\u00a0\u00a0<a href=\"https://twitter.com/#!/stevecla\">Steve Clayton</a>,\u00a0 I saw this <a href=\"http://wecreate.bigcartel.com/\">poster</a>.\u00a0\r\n\r\n<img src=\"http://media-cache4.pinterest.com/upload/132715520239204937_TDx5Cfc7_c.jpg\" alt=\"Pinned Image\" />\r\n\r\n(If you like it, buy it too).\r\n\r\nThe poster has gone viral, no doubt bringing a wry but slightly painful\u00a0smile to anyone filling in travel expenses or CRM system screens, or thinking about tidying the garage.\r\n\r\nWithin\u00a0\u00a0a couple of\u00a0 clicks I was able to\u00a0contact \u00a0the artist, <a href=\"http://wecreatestudio.co.uk/\">Brad Rose</a>,\u00a0and via the collective art website, <a href=\"http://bigcartel.com/\">Big Cartel</a>,\u00a0order and pay for the print.\u00a0\u00a0It will be gracing my office wall \u00a0some unspecified time in the future when I get around to having it framed. \u00a0\r\n\r\n\u00a0The Internet and social media allow me to discover what I think is cool art, interact with the artist and buy their stuff.\u00a0The world of art and crafts is being fundamentally reshaped by the Internet and social media.\u00a0 I can very easily find stuff I like,\u00a0 appreciate who and how it is made, and perhaps buy their product.\u00a0 It would have been easy to just print out the poster without buying it, but I quite like the idea of paying the creator for the the grin that this will bring to people's face when they visit my office.\u00a0 I don't need the threat of copyright infringement to know this. Discover, engage, and own.\r\n\r\n\u00a0In a rather weird circular way, I first got into buying poster art online with Hugh, of <a href=\"http://gapingvoid.com/\">gapingvoid fame</a>, a close friend of Steve.\u00a0\r\n\r\nBTW <a href=\"http://typeprocesslanguage.tumblr.com/\">Brad's site</a> is a fascinating tour of typography. One day I might actually try and learn something about typography. It will be an ideal weapon to use against wine bores at dinner parties.\r\n\r\n\u00a0similar post on my Gartner blog.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;", "categories": ["art", "music"], "likes": []}
